ed a little encouragement to get back into the game; Super Trainer Rick is YOUR kind of trainer! His advice, which ranges from general gym observations to actual workouts geared toward specific areas of the body, can be applied by both men and women. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">Super Trainer Rick is the link toward adopting fitness as a lifestyle, to feeling better about yourself and to start turning heads! There are NO EXCUSES! NONE.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">For intense personal training, contact Rick at supertrainerrick1@yahoo.com.</span></span></p>','r.jpg','image/jpeg',24562,'2011-12-12 21:24:18'),(5,'talesfromthedate','do-not-reply@talesfromthedate.com','fd2a27181a1051de64aa5a90e7d1704cc86bb7958864a5441b349003708be859abf526ddd1237f1b82afa56b740793410b8c6ab2ff50770467b54e32d9f1c9fa','TVjwAqATCAdP1XfKPPe','5a159d80e0a443b9f69078806f083fee1adf92d1a02976ad3028136ba01f5780da4c97cbaccbbd1ad2183ddaf4f689ff39f5df442e53f23ea1191253f7bce9bf','2011-07-30 03:17:03','2011-12-13 18:55:29',1,'TALES FROM THE DATE','talesfromthedate','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hello World,</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This is Tales From The Date: an edgy, observant blog </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">(if we say so ourselves) </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">about navigating the NYC dating scene to bring a fresh perspective to this undoubtedly unique, infinitely confusing world.&nbsp;We are young, single and have dated a vast and ecclectic number of characters, some truly amazing and others...no comment. We are not experts, but we\'ve grown wise the good old fashioned way: by dating. Lots.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Dating in New York City at times seems like having access to a 24/7 all-you-can-eat buffet. Spoiler alert: your eyes are bigger than your stomach. The endless variety dictates that when your options are so many, you can never bring yourself to make a single one. The hipster looks good (when he showers), the investment banker is a real crowd pleaser, and of course, of-age students are always fun. You end up wanting them all, yet we venture to guess, considering you&rsquo;re reading a dating blog, you come away with none. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">We like to hook people up, introduce friends of friends, and spark romances; we are your best wingman. But we&rsquo;ve never had much luck as our own. And that&rsquo;s the problem. Surrounded by millions of possible Mr./Ms. Right&rsquo;s, over-stimulated (not in a good way), and admittedly, a little lonely, maybe it&rsquo;s time to get out of our heads and go to bed. New York doesn&rsquo;t sleep, and New Yorkers shouldn&rsquo;t sleep with anyone other than whomever they want. But because you&rsquo;ve probably been doing that for weeks, months, possibly years, instead of thinking it&rsquo;s the dating scene that&rsquo;s the problem, maybe it&rsquo;s the &ldquo;whomever they want&rdquo; that&rsquo;s the problem. We\'re not prudish, and casual sex is a dish best served piping hot, but we\'re starting to think that it&rsquo;s not what&rsquo;s going on between the sheets but what&rsquo;s going on in between my ears that is tripping a lot of us up. We have so many amazing choices at our disposal, yet oftentimes we drag our feet over the menu items we don&rsquo;t actually want to eat (pun slightly intended). </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">That hipster looks good when he showers, but he doesn&rsquo;t really shower that much. That investment banker is kind of a douche&hellip;and bad in bed. And that student is more than a little immature: how many times can you play beer pong until it all gets old? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Are there more \"Specials\" to choose from on the Love Menu?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Common sense states that anything worth having is going to be a lot of work. Sage: if someone is worth the effort, we gladly roll up our proverbial sleeves and put our backs into it. But somewhere along the line, a lot of us forgot the difference between work that defines us and work that destroys us. We aim to never work in the latter sense a single day of our lives. When something is easy&mdash;because it&rsquo;s right&mdash; it feels serendipitous, whimsical, and even, ahem, romantic. We&rsquo;re New Yorkers, and we work every single day of our lives. We work for respect, cabs, promotions, seats on the subway, personal space, reservations, connections, barstools...it&rsquo;s exhausting. Why work for Mr./Ms. Wrong? Maybe we\'re naive, but we hold on to the faith that love is supposed to be free. And all we have to do is find the person who isn&rsquo;t going to charge us for it.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Having choice isn&rsquo;t a problem, it&rsquo;s awesome. But it might be time to start being honest with ourselves: Has the New York &ldquo;sell yourself&rdquo; mentality rubbed off on you to the point where dates play out more like business meetings and the result is a second date with a person who is paper perfect but not necessarily spectacular? Things that seem complicated have a funny way of being really simple. We are all looking for that person that fits comfortably. Like a perfectly broken in pair of rainbow flip flops, those jeans that make your ass look amazing, or even that pair of &ldquo;do me&rdquo; underwear that never fail to impress even the most jaded, disillusioned of lovers. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Keep working. Just make sure you&rsquo;re working for something and someone you actually want who\'s working just as hard for you. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Tales From The Date</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: medium;\"><br /></span></p>','cs_logo.png','image/png',26545,'2011-10-18 22:16:05'),(6,'music','music@connectingsexes.com','b7eb5279c21e23d0bfcddf3d598a47e56dfe0951da0bcb6f73a9776ff58288343079d10e097b7ccc4a17704d0577648aa515c6a290f0458cc55c2bd3948c3dbd','UT8sYsuTG1UIQlp4ot','01ddd25ec863ef1630ce36db733633880f3c886791fed1a1cf4fe6da3d58f1090e89f468773e99b0815c6dcf2e620c8e0c2cf459c42f144b713db2ab1301d598','2011-10-18 21:27:51','2011-12-25 23:46:39',1,'Music',NULL,'<p>Music makes any day better. It allows us to reminisce, express emotions, laugh, cry, get fired up, remember those we lost, belt out Cindy Lauper, and generally celebrate life. Our music blog attempts to cover the intersections between dating and music...and there are many!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','screen-shot-2011-12-12-at-4.13.45