INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (5,'Training vs. Working Out','<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Are you training or working out for your next date?</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: medium;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\">What is the difference between training and working out? I\'m noticing the difference in the fitness industry as of late, More and more people are starting to train and not just work out. What\'s the difference you may ask? well working out usually means that you\'re just trying to lose body fat, which isn\'t always a bad thing. But a good deal of the time people are looking to lose weight to impress someone, or they\'re trying to get ready for a wedding or birthday, or just something where they want to impress someone.</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse;\">These people usually fail! </span></span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: medium;\">Now training means, that you\'re probably not just trying to lose weight but to build muscle, or&nbsp; to raise your ability level so that you can be better at some athletic endeavor even if it\'s just in the gym. That person usually gets much&nbsp; better and has longer lasting results. And you\'re going to have more fun and be less prone to stop working out! So we will give you the tools, to raise your ability level. your fitness level and to attract that man or woman of your dreams!</span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-07-30 16:02:35','2011-12-09 06:47:36',4,'screen-shot-2011-07-30-at-11.59.32-am.png','image/png',119437,'2011-08-14 06:46:17',1,'2011-08-14 06:46:56',1,'training-vs-working-out','Training vs. Working Out'),(8,'Peak vs. Notch Lapel','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"color: #666666; line-height: 19px; font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Have you ever wondered what the different type of suit or jacket lapels were called?&nbsp;<br />Well here are the two basic choices, on the left we have a&nbsp;<strong>PEAK LAPEL</strong>, and on the right we have a&nbsp;<strong>NOTCH LAPEL</strong>.&nbsp;<br /><br />The notch lapel is probably the most recognized and most versatile suit lapel Over the years it has changed position on the jacket but will never go out of style. This is your everyday suit that will last you for years and work in every situation.&nbsp;<br /><br />The peak lapel is a little more fashion forward but adds a great amount of style and sophistication to the jacket. I try to get our clients into a slim peak on their second suit with us. This is great for when you have a big presentation and want to stand out a bit more. This would also be great to wear for a night out or even on your wedding day. The peak lapels help give you a greater presence!&nbsp;<br /><br /><br />Either way you can&rsquo;t really go wrong, but now you know what I will be talking about when I am trying my best to switch you into the slim peak lapel.</span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-07-30 16:14:20','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'screen-shot-2011-07-30-at-12.12.57-pm.png','image/png',257328,'2011-08-14 06:51:14',0,'2011-09-12 21:34:49',1,'peak-vs-notch-lapel','Peak vs. Notch Lapel'),(9,'Worst Date Ever','<p><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Dating can best be described as a rodeo. Online dating could be described as a rodeo where the rider is partially blindfolded and drunk on opportunity, lust, desperation, or in some cases Jack Daniels. We have all been there. Excited, styled hair, perfect heels and a pocket full of greenbacks. Only to discover your date is (fill in the blank).&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">We are looking for your best..errr worst dating stories! Please submit them to our Twitterfeed @connectingsexes or via our Facebook page.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Looking forward to some high flying drama.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">-The ConnectingSexes Team</span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-07-30 16:24:43','2012-01-09 21:28:40',5,'screen-shot-2011-07-30-at-12.24.03-pm.png','image/png',197220,'2011-08-14 06:44:40',0,'2012-01-09 21:28:40',1,'worst-date-ever','Worst Date Ever'),(12,'Gold Trench & Burberry Body','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 11px;\"><strong>All You Need for Fall is a Gold Trench &amp; Burberry Body</strong><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 11px;\"><strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\">Burberry&nbsp;</strong>wanted to create a feminine, timeless and effortlessly sensual fragrance to complement their edgy and distinctively British fashion house, and the formula does not disappoint.&nbsp;<strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\">Burberry Body&nbsp;</strong>launches today, and with a face like&nbsp;<strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\">Rosie Huntington-Whiteley</strong>, you know it&rsquo;s going to be sexy. See her campaign photos after the jump.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: x-small;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 10px; line-height: normal;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 11px;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\">&ldquo;Burberry Body is the next chapter in our history, and a launch we are all so excited about,&rdquo;&nbsp;<strong style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\">Christopher Bailey</strong>, Burberry Chief Creative Officer, said. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s the Burberry world translated into a scent, embodying every facet of the brand including our music, collections, scent, platforms and communities.&rdquo;<span style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\"><br /><br />Read more:&nbsp;<a style=\"background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: transparent; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; vertical-align: baseline; color: #003399; text-decoration: none; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; border-width: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;\" href=\"http://fashionindie.com/all-you-need-for-fall-is-a-gold-trench-burberry-body/#ixzz1WjJ2fIcJ\">http://fashionindie.com/all-you-need-for-fall-is-a-gold-trench-burberry-body/#ixzz1WjJ2fIcJ</a></span><br /></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-01 19:13:13','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'fi1.jpg','image/jpeg',39072,'2011-09-01 19:13:12',1,'2011-09-01 19:13:26',1,'gold-trench-burberry-body','Gold Trench & Burberry Body'),(13,'Fall Fabrics','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">First look at Fall fabrics</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">While a lot of you were huddled in a corner waiting for Irene to come through I was out there making sure you would be properly suited this fall.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">I headed to my super fabric guy in downtown LA and picked up the first 4 of this fall&rsquo;s one button club fabrics.&nbsp;It&rsquo;s just the start of what will be a very exciting fall for Evolution of Style, so stay tuned for more! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">For a custom fashion experience check out www.evolutionofstyle.com&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; text-autospace: none;\">&nbsp;</p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-09-01 19:22:47','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'evoblog-fabricshopping_thumb.jpg','image/jpeg',62254,'2011-09-01 19:22:46',0,'2011-09-12 21:35:06',1,'fall-fabrics','Fall Fabrics'),(15,'Top 11 Classiest Fashion Schools in the World   ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Welcome to our month of Fashion Education. To start you off in the right direction, let&rsquo;s examine your choice of design university, or more importantly, the fashion schools of choice. Certain alma maters produce an exceptional level of talent, consistently. Let us see where you stand, and who stands out as your alumni and professors. (Note: we are only looking at schools that speak English. Paris has burned.)</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/top-11-classiest-fashion-schools-in-the-world/#ixzz1X4KZuzEy\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #003399;\">http://fashionindie.com/top-11-classiest-fashion-schools-in-the-world/#ixzz1X4KZuzEy</span></a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-05 20:26:24','2011-10-23 12:29:40',2,'ilovefashion.jpg','image/jpeg',18510,'2011-09-05 20:26:24',0,'2011-09-12 21:29:34',1,'top-11-classiest-fashion-schools-in-the-world','Top 11 Classiest Fashion Schools in the World   '),(17,'Doing Nothing vs. Doing Nothing','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">There&rsquo;s a scene in <em>Forgetting Sarah Marshall</em> &ndash;one that could only be described as iconic- in which Paul Rudd&rsquo;s character is trying in vain to teach Jason Segal how to surf. Paul goes back and fourth in a seemingly idiotic fashion, further confusing his already bewildered student. Don&rsquo;t try to surf, Jason, don&rsquo;t do it; the less you do, the more you <em>do</em>. The funniest part of that scene, ironically enough, is that&rsquo;s actually solid advice. One can learn a lot about dating and relationships from surfing. In the world of dating it seems that the less you try and force a relationship with someone the more they seem to want one with you. I&rsquo;ll spare the masses the &ldquo;we want what we can&rsquo;t have&rdquo; diatribe; we all know this to be very true. But rather the more you let your instincts drive your involvement with your potential partner(s), the more organically &ndash;and therefore fruitfully- the relationship grows. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">However, there is a distinct difference between doing &ldquo;nothing&rdquo; and just straight-up doing nothing. Stay tuned for some term definitions&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Check it out @ </span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=59nrQPo53xo\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=59nrQPo53xo</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-05 20:40:29','2012-01-09 21:28:20',5,'russell_brand_in_forgetting_sarah_marshall_wallpaper_6_1280.jpg','image/jpeg',1175696,'2011-09-05 20:40:27',0,'2012-01-09 21:28:20',1,'doing-nothing-vs-doing-nothing','Doing Nothing vs. Doing Nothing'),(18,'Doing Nothing vs. Doing Nothing (con\'t)','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Doing \"Nothing\" = Good Investments </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The person you&rsquo;re dating is (hopefully) amazing but they are not perfect. Don&rsquo;t build this debilitating illusion in your love drunk head because the only thing you&rsquo;ll wake up with is a hangover. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This puts undue pressure on another human being and you&rsquo;re going to be entirely disappointed; and it&rsquo;ll be entirely your fault. When I meet a guy and it&rsquo;s utter, excruciating love-at-first-sight, all I want to do is give him everything; my body, my time, my loyalty, everything. These are major investments I&rsquo;m applying towards someone who I &ndash;admittedly- don&rsquo;t know very well&hellip; not to mention this is a recession. The more investments you make, the more invested you become and the less opportunity you give the other person to invest in you. Let your natural instincts determine the appropriate time to hit certain relationship milestones. Acting prematurely is an expression of insecurity so remember that premature equals immature, and immature equals replaceable. Replaceable, by the way, is the opposite of permanent.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Doing Nothing = You Did Nothing&nbsp;</strong></span><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&ne; Good Market Performance</span></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">When you do absolutely nothing in a relationship -especially during the crucial early stages- either out of disinterest or fear of coming on too strong, you are sending a blatant message to the other person that you are either disinterested or fearful&hellip; unattractive on both counts. To quote Mr. Rudd, &ldquo;that&rsquo;s not it at all&rdquo;. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;m not trying to suggest that the director of <em>Forgetting Sarah Marshall</em> was utilizing Paul Rudd&rsquo;s stereotypical &ldquo;surf bum&rdquo; character to communicate deep, insightful theories on human relationships. But the metaphor still stands. Sometimes great advice can be delivered in the most unexpected of vehicles, whether it be an aging surf instructor or a blog post. We are all confused, we are all at a loss for understanding, but we are all in the same position in the lineup; some of us just catch more waves.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-06 11:19:23','2012-01-09 21:28:04',5,'russell_brand_in_forgetting_sarah_marshall_wallpaper_6_1280.jpg','image/jpeg',1175696,'2011-09-06 11:19:21',0,'2012-01-09 21:28:04',1,'doing-nothing-vs-doing-nothing-cont','Doing Nothing vs. Doing Nothing (con\'t)'),(19,'No Time? NO EXCUSES!! ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Just got back from a little vacation at Disneyworld. It was an incredible place but I noticed immediately that there were so many OBESE people with children that were overweight as well. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">But also, whether it was in the hotel or in the park, men and women came up to me saying they simply don&rsquo;t have the time to get to the gym. My answer to them was if you don&rsquo;t have time just get started at home! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Start with ten-minute workouts (because everyone has ten minutes to spare!) and fill that time with three exercises; push-ups, sit-ups and squats. Do 50 reps per exercise in a circuit form, meaning do as many reps for one exercise, keep track of that rep count and go to the next movement&hellip; do this until you get to 50 and you did it! Quick and simple!! Do this at least 3 times a week and you are guaranteed results! And yes ladies, the same goes for you! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Think no bra strap fat, flat abs and toned ass and legs! So stop bullshitting yourselves! NO EXCUSES!!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by Super Trainer Rick</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: small;\"><strong>Edited by a.g, Editor-in-chief </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">For intense personal training sessions email Rick at supertrainerrick1@yahoo.com</span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-06 11:27:06','2011-10-23 12:29:40',4,'images.jpg','image/jpeg',6623,'2011-09-06 11:27:06',0,'2011-10-17 20:27:35',1,'no-time-no-excuses','No Time? NO EXCUSES!! '),(20,'The Stars Align at Venice Film Festival','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Though not quite as glamorous as the<strong> Cannes Film Festival</strong>, but still a stiletto and a half above <strong>Sundance,</strong> the <strong>Venice Film Festival</strong>&lsquo;s red carpet is proving a delight this year, thanks to <strong>Madonna</strong> and her <em>W.E.</em> star <strong>Andrea Riseborogouh</strong> and the always reliable <strong>Kate Winslet</strong>, among others.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; color: black; font-size: large;\"><br /> Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/the-stars-align-at-venice-film-festival/#ixzz1XAgZRfwk\"><span style=\"color: #003399;\">http://fashionindie.com/the-stars-align-at-venice-film-festival/#ixzz1XAgZRfwk</span></a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-06 11:35:04','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'madonna-we-vionnet.jpg','image/jpeg',49894,'2011-09-06 11:35:04',0,'2011-09-12 21:29:53',1,'the-stars-align-at-venice-film-festival','The Stars Align at Venice Film Festival'),(22,'Assholes, Party of 2','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Jim Morrison once wrote, &ldquo;I drink so I can talk to assholes, this includes me&rdquo;. Considering his well-recorded love of the bottle, I&rsquo;m guessing he had to talk to a lot of assholes. I&rsquo;m no legendary rock star but I&rsquo;ve talked to a lot of assholes, dated a fair amount, and even took one home to mom. And whose fault is that? Mine. Assholes I say? This includes me. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Bad dates require alcohol. But adding said substance to the mix is often the catch 22 for the over 21, as while it&rsquo;s entirely necessary it also builds superficial chemistry. You&rsquo;re on the date and you know there will never be a second one, so you order a stiff drink to numb yourself out of survival. All of a sudden their bad jokes are &ldquo;funny&rdquo; and that awkward demeanor goes from uncomfortable to nearly charming&hellip; flash forward a couple hours and your head is pounding harder than he was the night before. Welcome to the walk of shame, not the stride of pride. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Drink on a bad date but proceed with caution: real chemistry is intoxicating while fake chemistry requires intoxication. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-07 02:37:24','2012-01-09 21:27:47',5,'drunk.png','image/png',20796,'2011-09-07 02:38:40',0,'2012-01-09 21:27:47',1,'assholes-party-of-2','Assholes, Party of 2'),(24,'Fashion Week How To: Getting On Lists','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">The fashion scene is one that can be difficult to get yourself into,&nbsp;especially&nbsp;in a huge market such as <strong>New York City</strong>. It can hard to get your foot in the proverbial door when there is a&nbsp;literal PR girl at the door with a list that you&rsquo;re not on.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">There are a couple ways of getting yourself invited to these selective functions some of which are pretty obvious but it&rsquo;s always good to know that these ways work. Keep reading to find out how to get those invites filling up your inbox.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">read more:&nbsp; </span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\';\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/fashion-week-how-to-getting-on-lists/\">http://fashionindie.com/fashion-week-how-to-getting-on-lists/</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','fashionindie','2011-09-07 03:19:19','2011-10-23 12:29:40',2,'bouncer_holding_a_guest_list_bld019348-e1315321821301.jpg','image/jpeg',29218,'2011-09-07 03:19:19',0,'2011-09-12 21:31:05',1,'fashion-week-how-to-getting-on-lists','Fashion Week How To: Getting On Lists'),(25,'Top 3 Break-Up Songs','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Music heals. Whether you&rsquo;re in the acceptance, anger or denial phase of a break-up, these songs got your back&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">1.<span style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>No Woman, No Cry by Bob Marley &amp; The Wailer&rsquo;s </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><em>My fear is my only courage/ So I&rsquo;ve got to push on through</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><em><br /></em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Whether you fear being alone or being without the one you love, own those emotions. &nbsp;Re-build your ego and re-invent yourself. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Hear the rest: </span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jGqrvn3q1oo&amp;feature=fvwrel\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jGqrvn3q1oo&amp;feature=fvwrel</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">2.<span style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>1000 Faces by Joe Budden </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><em>Next time beauty&rsquo;s heading towards me I plan to dodge/ Until I know it&rsquo;s not being used as a camouflage</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><em>&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">We&rsquo;ve all experienced significant others that leave a significantly bad taste in our mouth (pun intended) due to the fact that they couldn&rsquo;t seem to commit to one version of themselves &ndash;let alone commit to us. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hear the rest: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6fSiH7ybVQQ\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6fSiH7ybVQQ</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">3.<span style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Perfect by The Smashing Pumpkins </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><em>Strangers down the line/ Lovers out of time/ Memories unwind </em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">One of the most difficult parts of any break-up is accepting that your partner is gone. This is a major change, which can send the best of us on a downward spiral. But that&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s called falling in love. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: tre