image/jpeg',1878140,'2011-09-07 05:33:20',0,'2012-01-09 21:27:21',1,'top-3-break-up-songs','Top 3 Break-Up Songs'),(26,'Six Pairs of Fall Riding Boots for City Slickers ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Horse-riding isn&rsquo;t a standard activity that comes to mind when thinking of NYC, but urban dwellers sure can play the part when it comes to the look. <strong>Riding boots </strong>are a fall staple that never go out of style, and we have six pairs that would love to find a happy home in your closet. Trust us, investing in a pair of these is money well-spent, even if you&rsquo;re not ready to get back in the saddle.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/six-pairs-of-fall-riding-boots-for-city-slickers/\">http://fashionindie.com/six-pairs-of-fall-riding-boots-for-city-slickers/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Times;\">&nbsp;</span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-07 05:46:22','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'picture-22-250x307.png','image/png',77760,'2011-09-07 05:46:21',0,'2011-09-12 21:32:11',1,'six-pairs-of-fall-riding-boots-for-city-slickers','Six Pairs of Fall Riding Boots for City Slickers '),(27,'How To Be a Bombshell ','<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Bridget Bardot</strong>. <strong>Marilyn Monroe</strong>. <strong>Sophia Loren</strong>. These are the glamorous women we turn to when we want to turn. Minus the occasional, copious amounts of plastic surgery in their later years, these are the gals we look at for bodacious beauty rituals and tastefully seductive fashion sense. As the elegance of Hollywood quickly fades, we tend to forget what a true glamour queen actually looks like. Not ones to be absentminded about the belles of yore, here&rsquo;s FashionIndie&rsquo;s guide on <strong>how to be a bombshell</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/how-to-be-a-bombshell/\">http://fashionindie.com/how-to-be-a-bombshell/</a> </span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-07 20:59:06','2011-10-23 12:29:40',2,'22-6-250x324.jpg','image/jpeg',30096,'2011-09-07 20:59:06',0,'2011-09-12 21:32:56',1,'how-to-be-a-bombshell','How To Be a Bombshell '),(28,'How To Sneak Into A Fashion Party ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Yesterday we taught you how to<a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/fashion-week-how-to-getting-on-lists/\"> diplomatically get on the list</a>. Today we&rsquo;re going to show you how to crash any fashion party.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Keep reading to find your way in: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/how-to-sneak-into-a-fashion-party/\">http://fashionindie.com/how-to-sneak-into-a-fashion-party/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-08 00:41:51','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'28club-span-articlelarge2-210x136.jpg','image/jpeg',12211,'2011-09-08 00:41:51',0,'2011-09-12 21:33:24',1,'how-to-sneak-into-a-fashion-party','How To Sneak Into A Fashion Party '),(29,'The Rebound RelationSHIT','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong>Re-la-tion-SHIT</strong> [ri-ley-shuh n- shit] <em>noun</em>: An involvement with another person(s) that is characterized by a distinctly shit, or subpar, quality. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">We&rsquo;ve all been there. Playing the role of rebound girl/guy is essentially playing the fool; but just like that song by The Main Ingredient so observantly stated everybody plays the fool sometimes. It&rsquo;s factual&hellip; and it&rsquo;s definitely cruel. The chemistry will be palpable, attraction remarkable, but the timing will be so shitty that it will bring out the worst in all parties involved. It isn&rsquo;t anyone&rsquo;s fault per se: it&rsquo;s just a fact of dating life. Should you find yourself in such a SHITuation here&rsquo;s a 3-part &ldquo;survival&rdquo; guide&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>1. The only assumption that can, and should, be made</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Assume nothing except that the honeymoon phase will be short, sweet and straight to the point. It&rsquo;ll be amazing, passionate, everything you&rsquo;ve ever wanted&hellip; for a month max. But then it happens; shortly after you start having sex they will realize that they cannot turn you into their former lover. And you will realize that you were relevant for about as long as this sentence. But who doesn&rsquo;t love being a footnote on someone&rsquo;s relationship history? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Times;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">stay strong and stay tuned for further survival tips... </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-08 09:57:39','2012-01-09 21:27:04',5,'mr_7f8d97411ddf53.jpg','image/jpeg',46802,'2011-09-08 09:57:38',0,'2012-01-09 21:27:04',1,'the-rebound-relationshit','The Rebound RelationSHIT'),(30,'The Rebound RelationSHIT (con\'t)','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\">2. Not-So-Great Expectations<br /></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">Don&rsquo;t expect anything. And I mean absolutely nothing. Don&rsquo;t even expect an orgasm. Seriously&hellip; Don&rsquo;t. Expectations lead to disappointment. A person on the rebound knows they&rsquo;re emotionally unavailable and the last thing they want is to feel like they are failing yet another person. So the moment you let on that you are either displeased with the current involvement or you want more is the moment your quirks become annoying, flaws become apparent and exit becomes imminent. You are good luck Chuck in this particular shit scenario. And just like the movie <em>Good Luck Chuck</em>, nothing about this role is funny. </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\">3. Exits Signs</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">When the inevitable occurs and they begin to phase you out, you&rsquo;ll notice. They&rsquo;ll make their wavering interest apparent. The point is to get you to dump them. While you&rsquo;ll hope for a graceful exit on their part -one that includes &ldquo;it&rsquo;s not you, it&rsquo;s me&rdquo; speeches (side note: it really is them)- what you&rsquo;ll likely get is (drum roll please)&hellip; nothing. Except, of course, a broken heart. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">Yes, there are exceptions to every rule but love and life are both such a gamble to begin with,the safer bet is that you are in fact the rule&hellip; not the exception.&nbsp; I guess the only lasting advice on such a topic is don&rsquo;t idealize these people, and don&rsquo;t set up expectations they can&rsquo;t possibly live up to. Being someone&rsquo;s rebound is an incredibly painful &ndash;albeit effective- way to learn some hard life lessons. But, you know, relationSHIT happens. </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-11 15:32:45','2012-01-09 21:26:45',5,'mr_7f8d97411ddf53-1.jpg','image/jpeg',46802,'2011-09-11 15:32:45',0,'2012-01-09 21:26:45',1,'the-rebound-relationshit-cont','The Rebound RelationSHIT (con\'t)'),(31,'Justin Bieber on Love and Style ','<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva;\"><strong>Justin Bieber</strong>&nbsp;(teenage swoonfest) invited us to join him at&nbsp;<strong>Dolce &amp; Gabbana</strong>&nbsp;to raise money for&nbsp;<strong>Pencils of Promise&nbsp;</strong>on Fashion&rsquo;s Night Out<strong>. &nbsp;</strong>Every purchase made at the store gave a lucky girl access to an autograph and photo with the Biebster himself. &nbsp;200 eleven year olds, thousands of dollars worth of&nbsp;<strong>Dolce &amp; Gabbana,</strong>&nbsp;and one Fire Marshall visit later, Biebs was ready to chat a about his future love life, his views on style, and his biggest fashion splurge.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/justin-bieber-talks-to-us-about-love-and-fashion-at-dolce-gabbana/\">http://fashionindie.com/justin-bieber-talks-to-us-about-love-and-fashion-at-dolce-gabbana/</a> </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','fashionindie','2011-09-11 15:42:12','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'fashion-fashions-night-out--1069627712_v2.grid-4x2.jpg','image/jpeg',15985,'2011-09-11 15:44:58',0,'2011-09-12 21:33:41',1,'justin-bieber-on-love-and-style','Justin Bieber on Love and Style '),(32,'Is Your Personality Making You Fat?','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Debating the battle of the bulge is America\'s favorite pastime. In fact, the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://ca.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/31_eating_well.html\">weight-loss</a></span> industry is a cash cow simply because losing weight is so darn difficult and keeping that weight off is often harder.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Until recently, weight-loss experts have focused on behavior as the biggest factor in weight gain and obesity. The conventional wisdom is that people who have weight problems simply eat too much and move too little. But now psychologists have taken an educated look at a long-term study to ask questions about what underlying psychological forces motivate such self-destructive behavior. Could <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/top_10/fitness/top-10-tips-for-preventing-weight-gain.html\">weight gain</a> </span>have less to do with bad habits and more to do with personality type?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/health_500/508_weight-and-personality.html\">http://www.askmen.com/sports/health_500/508_weight-and-personality.html</a></span></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-11 16:04:07','2011-10-23 12:29:41',4,'508_weight-and-personality-1049436-flash-1049436-flash.jpg','image/jpeg',12556,'2011-09-11 16:04:07',0,'2011-09-12 21:28:57',1,'is-your-personality-making-you-fat','Is Your Personality Making You Fat?'),(33,'5 Beauty Quick-Fixes to Survive the Rest of Fashion Week','<p><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Coming up on the halfway point of<strong> New York Fashion Week</strong>, our bags are stuffed with designer cheat sheets, various shades of lip gloss and the general mess of stuff we&rsquo;ve accumulated over the past five days. What else is in our bags? Beauty products that help us survive the day by maintaining our usual fabulousness. Here are <strong>5 quick-fix beauty products </strong>that will freshen your look in no time at all.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/5-beauty-quick-fixes-to-survive-the-rest-of-fashion-week/\">http://fashionindie.com/5-beauty-quick-fixes-to-survive-the-rest-of-fashion-week/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-12 21:40:22','2011-10-23 12:29:41',2,'6458-000052-210x154.jpg','image/jpeg',8856,'2011-09-12 21:40:21',0,'2011-09-12 21:40:38',1,'5-beauty-quick-fixes-to-survive-the-rest-of-fashion-week','5 Beauty Quick-Fixes to Survive the Rest of Fashion Week'),(34,'Beating the Freshman 15','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Going away to school can be dangerous on the waistline. The dorm dining hall is like a giant, all-you-can-eat buffet. And let\'s be real, the food choices at most campuses are not healthy. On top of that, many students don\'t have access to a kitchen, and will ultimately eat all of their meals out. It\'s no wonder most of us <a href=\"http://www.fitsugar.com/4117944\">gain some weight</a> when going off to college, though the infamous \"freshman 15\" is <a href=\"http://www.fitsugar.com/3619387\">really more like 10 pounds</a>. And don\'t be fooled &mdash; weight gain isn\'t reserved to first-year students only. The eating habits you develop during your first year away can stay with you through college and beyond.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Whether you\'re eating in a dining hall or cooking for yourself in your first apartment, a few simple strategies can help you avoid that first-year college weight gain. Here are my tips for eating healthy while you\'re away at school.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.fitsugar.com/10-Healthy-Eating-Tips-Avoid-Freshman-15-4366083\">http://www.fitsugar.com/10-Healthy-Eating-Tips-Avoid-Freshman-15-4366083</a></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-12 21:52:01','2011-12-09 06:47:37',4,'408212635v0_480x480_front_color-white_padtosquare-true.jpg','image/jpeg',38037,'2011-09-12 21:52:00',0,'2011-09-12 21:52:52',1,'beating-the-freshman-15','Beating the Freshman 15'),(35,'Get Laid... Not \"Like\"ed','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I love Facebook. Don&rsquo;t get me wrong. Google won&rsquo;t be getting this + 1 anytime soon (however, anyone is free to send me an invite if they so choose). But treat Facebook like a casual hookup. Use it, enjoy it, but respect it&rsquo;s potential for drama and always leave a little mystery. I&rsquo;ve found that Facebook -amazing as it is- not only has the capacity to bring out our inner creeper but it also has a tendency to make people feel unnecessarily shitty about themselves. We are force-fed our &ldquo;friends&rdquo; triumphs and their every happy moments are chronicled on our newsfeeds, leading a lot of us to believe that our lives are boring and therefore empty and meaningless. Your life is only boring and meaningless if you&rsquo;re always on Facebook. Go out and explore NYC, meet actual friends, make some real stories&hellip; and try not to make every interesting observation a status update (guilty). And for the love of God, only stalk when absolutely necessary. Trust me, its not good looks. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Facebook is a powerful tool that connects people and provides them with a platform for sharing information; a way to make the world a smaller place. But if Facebook is confining your world to the world-wide-web, it may be time to re-evaluate. If you like someone don&rsquo;t just sit from the comfort of your computer screen and &ldquo;like&rdquo; their bullshit, attention-seeking statuses. Besides, Facebook should be getting you laid&hellip; not &ldquo;like&rdquo;ed. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">If you liked this go &ldquo;like&rdquo; us on Facebook at ConnectingSexes :) &nbsp;</span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-13 08:18:49','2012-01-09 21:26:25',5,'computer_nerd-13821.jpg','image/jpeg',52937,'2011-09-13 08:18:49',0,'2012-01-09 21:26:25',1,'get-laid-not-likeed','Get Laid... Not \"Like\"ed'),(36,'Don\'t Like Sex? Wear Crocs ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;ve said it once and I&rsquo;ll say it again: a piece of my soul dies every time I see a good-looking man wearing Crocs. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">When I was at NYU there was this coffee spot that was rumored to be the hang out of choice among the hot grad students. So, of course, I quickly became a regular. One day I was sitting at my usual table when out of my peripherals I saw a total smoke show: Blonde hair, blue eyes, nice smile, maybe 6&rsquo;2&rdquo;, athletic build&hellip; this particular 9 was the whole nine. So, determined to get my grown man on I plotted to walk over and leave him my number before I strutted out of the place. I grabbed a napkin and scribbled my digits on it followed by a coy -or so I thought- &ldquo;call me :)&rdquo;.&nbsp; As I was heading over towards him I saw them. I saw the Crocs. Bright blue&hellip; with a shearling trim. I was gutted. I was also without options. ABORT MISSION. I repeat, ABORT MISSION.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I know this sounds superficial but whatever. We are talking about footwear inspired by those worn in prisons, mental institutions and on gardening shows. If you ask me when it comes to Crocs, a little superficiality goes a long way. So gentlemen: I love you but if you want to get it in the Crocs are out. Don&rsquo;t say you weren&rsquo;t warned. And ladies: you&rsquo;re welcome&hellip; you&rsquo;re very welcome. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">written by a.g, Editor-in-chief</span></strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-09-13 10:50:40','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'post-4-crocs-2.jpg','image/jpeg',36969,'2011-09-13 11:21:35',0,'2011-10-17 20:30:36',1,'dont-like-sex-wear-crocs','Don\'t Like Sex? Wear Crocs '),(37,'Dieters Can & Should Drink Beer... Cheers ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">Take heed all you beer lovers. It is now a proven fact that beer -- yes, BEER -- can provide the same <a id=\"itxthook0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrsta itxthook\" style=\"border-bottom: 0.075em solid darkgreen; font-weight: normal; font-size: 100%; text-decoration: underline; padding-bottom: 1px; color: darkgreen; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/45_eating_well.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span id=\"itxthook0w0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">health</span><span id=\"itxthook0w2\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">benefits</span></a> as <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/25_eating_well.html\">wine</a>. No matter what type of ale you prefer, studies show that drinking beer in moderation (up to 2 drinks a day for us guys) can and will reduce your chances of strokes, as well as heart and vascular disease.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: large;\"> It\'s called the <em>French Paradox</em> -- the link between the low rate of heart disease among the French and their fat-laden <a id=\"itxthook1\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrsta itxthook\" style=\"border-bottom: 0.075em solid darkgreen; font-weight: normal; font-size: 100%; text-decoration: underline; padding-bottom: 1px; color: darkgreen; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/45_eating_well.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span id=\"itxthook1w0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">diet</span></a> was a daily dosage of red wine. Well, there\'s no denying the results of that study. But what the public <em>doesn\'t</em> know is that the health <a id=\"itxthook2\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrsta itxthook\" style=\"border-bottom: 0.075em solid darkgreen; font-weight: normal; font-size: 100%; text-decoration: underline; padding-bottom: 1px; color: darkgreen; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/45_eating_well.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span id=\"itxthook2w0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">value</span></a> of beer has been known, documented and applied for centuries. But there are folks out there who don\'t want you to know about it (I wonder why). </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/45_eating_well.html\">http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/45_eating_well.html</a></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-13 11:04:01','2011-12-09 06:47:37',4,'screen-shot-2011-09-15-at-5.31.10-pm.png','image/png',499069,'2011-09-15 21:31:38',0,'2011-09-15 21:31:49',1,'dieters-can-should-drink-beer-cheers','Dieters Can & Should Drink Beer... Cheers '),(39,'A Trend Right Above the Cut ','<p><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Spring looks nipped and tucked, gaping for places for limbs. Cut out shoulders, rib cages, thighs, all sorts of body parts are left exposed as designers like <strong>Prabal Gurung</strong> and <strong>Graeme Armour</strong> are clipping away.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/cut-that-out-now-this-trend-is-exposing/\">http://fashionindie.com/cut-that-out-now-this-trend-is-exposing/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-13 11:13:36','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'prabal-gurung-spring-2012-ready-to-wear.jpg','image/jpeg',72244,'2011-09-13 11:17:31',0,'2011-09-13 11:17:50',1,'a-trend-right-above-the-cut','A Trend Right Above the Cut '),(41,'Street Art for the Urban Explorer ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Culture-bots all over NY have an opinion about their favorite spots to oggle street-art and this zeitgeist reporter is no different. This year has been an especially exciting time for the country&rsquo;s most controversial canvasses. Between the Banksy documentary, news that graffiti mecca 5 Pointz will be closing, and the &ldquo;Art in the Streets&rdquo; exhibition at LA&rsquo;s Museum of Contemporary Art (MOCA), the walls and buildings in the five boroughs have been getting just as much attention as any runway during fashion week. We&rsquo;re here to help you feel included in the conversation &ndash; to make sure that you can throw down with an avenue (or two) that boasts tags, colors, and something truly special or unique. In the spirit of the <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/museum-know-how-when-you-have-to-make-small-talk-about-art-and-your-idea-of-culture-is-vintage-simpsons-episodes/\">museum round-up</a>&nbsp;we presented a few weeks ago, here are some noteworthy spots to view urban Picasso&rsquo;s throughout New York.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/street-art-faves-photos-to-entice-the-urban-explorer/\">http://fashionindie.com/street-art-faves-photos-to-entice-the-urban-explorer/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-16 00:08:28','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'kenmare-560x420.jpg','image/jpeg',98629,'2011-09-16 00:08:27',0,'2011-09-16 00:09:07',1,'street-art-for-the-urban-explorer','Street Art for the Urban Explorer '),(42,'Metabolism Myths: Part 1 ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">It&rsquo;s seems like every fitness-expert wannabe has a website proclaiming he knows the secret way to turn your body into a <em>FAT-INCINERATING BLAST FURNACE!</em></span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Yeah, right.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Some myths about boosting metabolism are so prevalent that they&rsquo;ve been repeated again and again via best-selling <a id=\"itxthook0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrsta itxthook\" style=\"border-bottom: 0.075em solid darkgreen; font-weight: normal; font-size: 100%; text-decoration: underline; padding-bottom: 1px; color: darkgreen; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/bodybuilding_900/960_popular-metabolism-myths-part-1.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span id=\"itxthook0w0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">fitness</span></a> books and popular magazines. You&rsquo;ll hear personal trainers and nutrition counselors spew this information, as well.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Don&rsquo;t believe it.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/bodybuilding_900/960_popular-metabolism-myths-part-1.html\">http://www.askmen.com/sports/bodybuilding_900/960_popular-metabolism-myths-part-1.html</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><br /></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-16 00:14:28','2011-10-23 12:29:41',4,'mythbusters1-e1307083047119.png','image/png',100645,'2011-09-16 00:14:28',0,'2011-09-16 19:08:17',1,'metabolism-myths-part-1','Metabolism Myths: Part 1 '),(44,'How To Break Up... With Yourself ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Most people have some kind of baggage. The severity of said baggage varies drastically but you&rsquo;ll be hard pressed to find a person completely devoid of issues, daddy or otherwise. But if you&rsquo;re anything like yours truly, you have a difficult time separating Church and State. My relationship history reads like a Greek tragedy and the reason for this is simple: I, like many others, can&rsquo;t seem to get out of my own head and out of my own way. So the time has come to break up&hellip; with myself. It&rsquo;s not you, it&rsquo;s me. Literally. So, if you have found yourself in a similar situation here&rsquo;s a guide to get you through the 4 stages of this break with self&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The &ldquo;Denial&rdquo; Phase</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Deny yourself the right of self-pity. Pity equals pitiful, which equals unappealing. Studies have shown that unappealing people have less sex. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The &ldquo;Bargaining&rdquo; Phase </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Don&rsquo;t take anything you can get, whether you&rsquo;re looking for a relationship or a potential rebound slampiece. When you&rsquo;re on the rebound, even from yourself, the tendency to look for love in all the wrong places is both strong and debilitating. You just got out of a messed up relationship so when you&rsquo;re talking to that talent that reminds you of the kind of person you would have dated in the past, you&rsquo;re really just missing yourself and your old, familiar habits. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The phases continue, stay hungry... <br /></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-16 01:54:23','2012-01-09 21:26:05',5,'dear_john.jpg','image/jpeg',46190,'2011-09-16 01:54:22',0,'2012-01-09 21:26:05',1,'how-to-break-up-with-yourself','How To Break Up... With Yourself '),(45,'How To Break Up... With Yourself (con\'t)','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>The &ldquo;Anger&rdquo; Phase</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Be angry that you likely let something stupid, like a text &ldquo;conversation&rdquo; that was lost in interpretation, get in the way of an opportunity with someone. There&rsquo;s nothing in life as tragic as a missed opportunity, and yet a lot of us miss them on a daily basis because we&rsquo;re too busy over-thinking. As far as the texting goes I&rsquo;d tell the girls that what he wrote is precisely what he meant and to the guys I&rsquo;d say just write back as soon as you can (we measure interest on how promptly you reply). Just saying&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>The &ldquo;Acceptance&rdquo; Phase</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Accept that you&rsquo;ve royally screwed things in the past with people (ALL of us have) and you can&rsquo;t change that. You can, however, change from here on out. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Take responsibility for your part in situations that didn&rsquo;t go your way and learn from them. Thinking things through logically is never a bad idea, but being all thought and no living generally brings about poor results. I&rsquo;m right there with you. It&rsquo;s easy to preach from my wifi tower but we all have trouble putting word into action. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-16 17:36:16','2012-01-09 21:25:46',5,'breaking-up.jpg','image/jpeg',17792,'2011-09-16 17:36:16',0,'2012-01-09 21:25:46',1,'how-to-break-up-with-yourself-cont','How To Break Up... With Yourself (con\'t)'),(46,'Eat & Be Sexy ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Rather than shelling out for that ultra-hydrating anti-aging exfoliator, reach for the fridge instead. You can affect the way you look by what you <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt_400/449_foods-that-improve-your-looks.html\"><span class=\"itxtrstitxtrstspanitxthookspan\"><span style=\"color: darkgreen; text-decoration: none;\">eat</span></span></a>. Adding a few varied ingredients to your <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/\">diet</a> is easy, practical and an inexpensive way to improve your looks (brightening your eyes, preventing hair loss and clearing up your skin). Check out our guide to the&nbsp; foods that can turn you into someone&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt_400/449_foods-that-improve-your-looks.html\"><span class=\"itxtrstitxtrstspanitxthookspan\"><span style=\"color: darkgreen; text-decoration: none;\">attractive</span></span></a> dinner date.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt_400/449_foods-that-improve-your-looks.html\">http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt_400/449_foods-that-improve-your-looks.html</a></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-16 18:58:03','2011-10-23 12:29:41',4,'449_foods-that-improve-your-looks-flash-1040651-flash.jpg','image/jpeg',11232,'2011-09-16 19:01:17',0,'2011-09-16 19:01:48',1,'eat-be-sexy','Eat & Be Sexy '),(47,'SHOE ENVY: The Fall Edition ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Visions of color blocking just in time for fall, the red sole never looked so delicious. Red, green and tan leather come together in perfect harmony for the <strong>Christian Louboutin </strong>Leather Lace-Up Colorblock Peep Toe Ankle Boots, and we&rsquo;re hovering like vultures for the stacked, 5.5 inch heel and Italian-made design.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: </span><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/shoe-envy-christian-louboutin-leather-lace-up-colorblock-peep-toe-ankle-boots/\">http://fashionindie.com/shoe-envy-christian-louboutin-leather-lace-up-colorblock-peep-toe-ankle-boots/</a></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-19 13:25:42','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'picture-41.png','image/png',156556,'2011-09-19 13:25:41',0,'2011-09-19 13:26:21',1,'shoe-envy-the-fall-edition','SHOE ENVY: The Fall Edition '),(48,'Tips From A Surfer ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Surfing is my passion and it\'s a true labor of love. But I have found that labor and love often come hand in hand. It&rsquo;s a full time job keeping myself happy let alone another person. But few other jobs could possibly be more rewarding than making The One happy. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Like the search for that perfect person, when you surf, a lot is left out of your hands. The elements have to cooperate all at once and it&rsquo;s nearly impossible to predict. But every once in a while it happens: it goes off. The waves seem like they&rsquo;ve travelled thousands of miles from the center of the ocean just for you. You see the wave begin to form, you know it&rsquo;s yours and you&rsquo;re going to fight for it. It&rsquo;s a gut feeling that is impossible to put into words and yet we all know this unmistakable sensation, similar to that loss of breath when in spite of our better judgments we fall in love. You catch it and all of a sudden you&rsquo;re in it -apart of it. For a few seconds life is as it should be: simple, exhilarating and impossibly beautiful. But it&rsquo;s also fleetingly beautiful.&nbsp; You paddle back out to the line up and keep your eye on the horizon for another toy from God, as <strong>Clay Marzo</strong> so aptly put it. It may be a matter of minutes if it&rsquo;s firing but that may also be your only wave that session. But even if it is your only wave, consider yourself lucky. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Waves are the power of the harnessed elements. Dating can be a powerful tool in the quest for elements of personal happiness. Harness the surfer mentality and go with the flow. Enjoy someone for who they are. Pick your waves carefully, and go big. But sometimes, when all you want to do is go big, you just have to go home. But no worries... there&rsquo;s always another swell coming. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-19 13:39:04','2012-01-09 21:25:27',5,'spicoli-fast-times-ridgemont-high-surf-no-dice.jpg','image/jpeg',27549,'2011-09-19 13:39:04',0,'2012-01-09 21:25:27',1,'tips-from-a-surfer','Tips From A Surfer '),(49,'Be The Sack... She\'ll Come To You ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;m not sure if I&rsquo;m late to the game on this particular issue but I realized that unlike white pants, boat shoes are worn after Labor Day. In a controversial decision by the judges (ok, just me), it has been determined that boat shoes are kind of hot. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Maybe it&rsquo;s my hidden love of the prepstar* that&rsquo;s to blame but I think I&rsquo;m going to go ahead on jump on the \"boat shoe\" bandwagon. They look great when guys are wearing pants, shorts, nothing&hellip; plus they remind me of Summer and I&rsquo;m not ready to say goodbye to it just yet. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Gentlemen, my only advice is that if you&rsquo;re going to rock the infamous boat shoe don&rsquo;t overdo to the whole Brooks Brothers, Martha&rsquo;s Vineyard vibe- not that there&rsquo;s anything wrong with said vibe, let&rsquo;s just stick to doses. The boat shoe carries a preppy punch stronger than Bradley Cooper in <em>Wedding Crashers</em>. And like Bradley Cooper in <em>Wedding Crashers</em>, if you rock the boat shoe she will come to you&hellip; because you&rsquo;re the Sack. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">*<strong>prepstar</strong>, <em>noun</em>: (a) A preppy person that actually pulls off the look and therefore causes you to feel extreme sexual attraction towards them; (b) A preppy person that does not pull off the look but believes vehemently that they do and therefore causes you to feel extreme disdain towards them. <strong>For the record</strong>, I like option (a)&hellip; but I&rsquo;ve confused the two before, happens to the best of us. &nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">written by a.g, Editor-in-chief</span></strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-09-20 05:44:15','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'005wdc_david_conrad_002.jpg','image/jpeg',55861,'2011-09-20 05:44:14',0,'2011-10-17 20:30:50',1,'be-the-sack-shell-come-to-you','Be The Sack... She\'ll Come To You '),(50,'The Ins on \"Weird\" Workouts ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;m not one to get into workout trends early on but there are a few &ldquo;alternative&rdquo; forms of exercise that I&rsquo;ve either attempted or made an integral part of my lifestyle. There are also a few of these fitness trends that I could easily have done without. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>&ldquo;Weird&rdquo; workouts that actually work&hellip;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Surfing: A years long true obsession of mine. Give me one week of daily surfing and&nbsp; not only do I see the early signs of a lady &ldquo;v&rdquo;, but my ass also returns to its home state. The lady \"v\" -by the way- is the less obvious version of the male \"v\", which are those amazing \"v\" shaped muscles on the lower abdomen. Men caught rocking these bad boys are automatically increased by 2 points on the 1-10 scale, much the same way bi-sexual tendencies and double-jointedness raises a girls score. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Pole Dancing: I looked absolutely ridiculous, ended up with suspicious looking bruises on my inner thighs, but my pole dancing experience included a healthy balance of Lil&rsquo; Wayne and some serious working out. It&rsquo;ll get you tight exactly where you (and your significant other) want. Warning: sorry but pole dancing is not a spectator sport&hellip; I saw plenty of guys ask though. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>&ldquo;Weird&rdquo; workouts that didn&rsquo;t work out&hellip; for me </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hot Yoga: Just as the name suggests this is a yoga workout where you will be extremely hot, uncomfortable, and feel faint for the duration. I love yoga, but come on now&hellip; are you serious? Sidenote: a good guy friend of mine went to a hot yoga class with a girl he was trying to holla at. He ended up feeling so light headed he had to excuse himself midway. Obviously, he is not a fan of this particular trend either. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Trapeze: I didn&rsquo;t want to do it, but I did. And it kind of sucked. It was slightly painful and I realized the moment I was swinging through the air attempting some Wringling Bros. bullshit that maybe I should just get into running. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief </span></strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-20 06:39:23','2011-10-23 12:29:41',4,'pole-dance.jpg','image/jpeg',21349,'2011-09-20 06:39:23',0,'2011-10-17 20:26:33',1,'the-ins-on-weird-workouts','The Ins on \"Weird\" Workouts '),(51,'D&G Delivers Music Straight To Your Ears ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Even though we got a few days of sun over the weekend, we&rsquo;re still tired of hearing the rainfall outside our windows at the FashionIndie loft. Luckily, our favorite luxury Italian diffusion line <strong>D&amp;G </strong>has collaborated with <strong>Skullcandy</strong>, the coolest audio brand around, so we can drown out the gloomy sound with our favorite office tunes. Ranging in price from $50 &ndash; $200, there is a style for every budget.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/dg-delivers-music-straight-to-your-ears/\">http://fashionindie.com/dg-delivers-music-straight-to-your-ears/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-21 01:46:13','2011-10-23 12:29:41',2,'family-560x380.jpg','image/jpeg',27594,'2011-09-21 01:46:12',0,'2011-09-21 01:46:40',1,'dg-delivers-music-straight-to-your-ears','D&G Delivers Music Straight To Your Ears '),(52,'Long Story Short: He Didn\'t Get It In ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Allow me to take you on a stroll down memory lane, to a place called my worst date ever&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The guy was someone I knew back in high school. We ran into each other out of nowhere after not having seen one another in 4+ years. Crazy coincidental it was. The dawn of a beautiful, budding romance? Not exactly. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The date started out decently enough, conversation was a flowing (the beer helped, I&rsquo;ll be honest) and I, like many women, thought that perhaps I had found Mr. Right Now. He then proceeded to get inappropriately drunk and tell me that he could kick a 300-yard field goal (considering the magnitude of that lie I must have been drunker than I thought... because I believed him). While it is true that dates are for letting loose and getting to know someone a little better and apologies should never be made for getting ones drink on, this guy wasn&rsquo;t date drunk he was frat boy drunk. Not to mention he looked me dead in the eye and asked point blank if he was going to get laid that night seeing as this was the second time he&rsquo;d taken me out (wow&hellip; I mean, just wow). </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">What happened after involved some shattered expectations (on his end), a lot of bickering and ultimately an extremely awkward cab ride in which there were two stops&hellip; not one. This guy seriously thought he could negotiate sex, oral and otherwise. So I suppose the moral of this story is one for the guys: If she likes you, she knows she&rsquo;s going to bed you about 60 seconds after she meets you. There should be zero need for negotiation. It could happen after one date, after five&hellip; But please, for the sake of humanity don&rsquo;t ask. When it comes to sex, your mantra should NOT be &ldquo;ask and you shall receive&rdquo;. It&rsquo;s more like &ldquo;ask and you shall have to self-relieve&rdquo;. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-21 02:10:46','2012-01-09 21:25:09',5,'images-2.jpg','image/jpeg',5604,'2011-09-21 02:12:26',0,'2012-01-09 21:25:09',1,'long-story-short-he-didnt-get-it-in','Long Story Short: He Didn\'t Get It In '),(54,'Good Credit Score','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Seeing as I recently ranted about one of my worst dating experiences, it only seems fair to give big ups to one of my best&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This particular date took place a while back. The guy was a little older (highly recommended) and was clearly a good listener because he took me to a bar/restaurant on the water with some borderline epic, quasi-reggae spinning all night. The menu was characterized by a heavy seafood persuasion and a Corona was a perfectly acceptable beverage of choice. If you know me at all it should come as no surprise that he basically nailed it -in more ways than one. After some light beer and conversation we took a late night \"stroll\" on the beach... to quote The Lost Boyz, &ldquo;there&rsquo;s no need for me to stress the rest&rdquo;. Well-played, Sir&hellip; credit where credit is due.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Now, some people <em>may</em> be surprised to hear that a date as simple as the above-mentioned would make my &uuml;ber-honorable mention list, which is a smooth transition to next episode of my rant: there are plenty, and I mean plenty, of females out there that legitimately enjoy a relaxed, nonchalant date over an inappropriately expensive one, hands down. A lot of the guys that I talk to seem to think that the only way to be successful with women is to try too hard to impress them by spending excessive amounts of money. Women like that exist, no doubt. Trust me, those are the wrong kind of women. When you happen to meet a girl that simply enjoys your company and doesn&rsquo;t care about the theatrics, thank whatever God you pray to. But just because she&rsquo;s chill and doesn&rsquo;t expect you to go out of your way doesn&rsquo;t mean you should chill and never go out of your way. It&rsquo;s precisely that kind of female that deserves the ultra attention to detail. If she&rsquo;s cool give credit where credit is due.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: medium;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-21 22:26:58','2012-01-09 21:24:51',5,'beach-at-night.jpg','image/jpeg',5669,'2011-09-21 22:26:57',0,'2012-01-09 21:24:51',1,'good-credit-score','Good Credit Score'),(55,'Swiping The V-Card 101','<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Sex is \"a painful activity in which a man, using the stiffest and pointiest part of his pelvic region, repeatedly stabs a female in her crotch until he feels satisfied,\" according to urban dictionary.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I\'m going to have to disagree with this dim-witted definition, because when executed correctly, sex is one of the only drug-free ecstasies. However, if a boy has yet to swipe that V-card away from you, urban dictionary\'s definition is right on point. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">If you\'re one of those that have yet to have the pleasure of getting it in, I feel very, very sorry for you. Whether it\'s because you\'re saving it for &lsquo;that special someone\' (so corny), it\'s against your religion (understandable and respectable, this column doesn\'t pertain to you), or you\'re just more focused on your schoolwork (nerd), it\'s time to get a move on.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">If you want to have good sex before the world ends in 2012, I\'d start as soon as possible, even tonight if you can, because practice makes perfect.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.ubspectrum.com/opinion/swiping-the-v-card-101-1.2601123#.TnlZ5ubple4\">http://www.ubspectrum.com/opinion/swiping-the-v-card-101-1.2601123#.TnlZ5ubple4</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by Keren Baruch </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-22 20:56:12','2012-01-09 21:24:23',5,'virginity.jpg','image/jpeg',29872,'2011-09-22 23:05:07',0,'2012-01-09 21:24:23',1,'swiping-the-v-card-101','Swiping The V-Card 101'),(56,'Bone(r) To Pick ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Femi-Nazism* was never my thing and I have a healthy respect for men in general. But I have a bone to pick with you boys: I&rsquo;m sick and tired of worrying about whether or not I&rsquo;m &ldquo;leading&rdquo; a man on. If I want to have sex with you, it will be obvious. Like, I&rsquo;ll probably tell you (it&rsquo;s been known to happen). But I also&nbsp; genuinely enjoy the company of male friends and I think my company is worthwhile even if I&rsquo;m not bedding you. If you&rsquo;re a friend, I&rsquo;ll come hang out&nbsp; one-on-one and perhaps even crash at your place on occasion&hellip; on your couch. When I&rsquo;m making a sincere offer to pay for things, it&rsquo;s because I don&rsquo;t want to give you the impression that I&rsquo;m using you. Like Femi-Nazism, using men was NEVER my thing either. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">I completely understand that there is a basic neurological disconnect between us and biology is to blame: you are men and I am a woman. But I don&rsquo;t think the disconnect is as prolific as its made out to be. In truth, if you guys had to be honest I suspect you know deep down when a female actually thinks of you as a friend or as a friend with whom she wants to engage in some benefits. And I have found that a vast, concerning number of men tend to ignore this and proceed under the misguided belief that they can change her mind through &ndash;at times trivial- pursuit. Us women have our own version of this as well so don&rsquo;t worry&hellip; I&rsquo;m not targeting you.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">There are some basic signals that should be a huge indication of her more-or-less R-rated intentions: bedroom eyes, a smile that says &ldquo;I&rsquo;ll let you do things to me that may or may not be illegal in the state of New York&rdquo;, a subtle touch somewhere around the forearm or bicep (backs are for buddies)&hellip; I really shouldn&rsquo;t need to elaborate; we are all smart enough animals to know when it&rsquo;s a possible game on. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Another issue that needs delving into is that of attire. I&rsquo;m young and my body is young too. I haven&rsquo;t birthed any children (yet) and I stay reasonably active: basically, I may never look like this again. So yeah, I want to wear clothing that accentuates, not exploits, my assets. All persons should be encouraged to dress in a way that makes them feel sexy&hellip; I mean, why the hell wouldn&rsquo;t we? And what I&rsquo;ve never understood about guys who claim that a certain dress sense translates to DTF* is that the longer you allow yourselves to keep making this administrative error, the less likely women will continue to want to dress themselves in a way that is both visually and physically stimulating for you. Continue to make us feel uncomfortable, misunderstood and slutty and we&rsquo;ll soon begin to rock skirts inspired by the Church of Latter Day Saints, which hit us just below our tightly locked knees. It&rsquo;s common sense and really quite logical: you want something pretty to look at? Stop claiming that when we look pretty we&rsquo;re leading you on. Maybe we&rsquo;re just pretty. And that&rsquo;s a good thing for mankind.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Index</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Femi-Nazism: An extreme sect of feminism that advocates for more&nbsp; -not equal- rights. It&rsquo;s a sect. Most women are not like this so don&rsquo;t throw this term around loosely&hellip; pretty please :) </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">DTF: Down. To. F**k. As equally Self-explanatory as it is straight-forward: what prowlers, players and everything in between should be looking for in a person&hellip; right up there with good genes and a strong character. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-22 22:56:38','2012-01-09 21:24:07',5,'work.6766045.2.sticker-375x360.i-am-not-a-whore-v1.png','image/png',34098,'2011-09-22 22:56:38',0,'2012-01-09 21:24:07',1,'boner-to-pick','Bone(r) To Pick '),(57,'Gorilla Warfare ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Gentlemen, thank you for doing yoga. I love little more than coming to class and seeing you there on your mats. You add fun to my 90 minutes of serenity and stretching. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Your presence also indicates certain character traits: you like calm, you like fitness, and quite possibly, you are deep. To the players among you, it shows me you\'re not dumb: you know where the girls are, beyond the obvious bar scene. Further still, I know you will be in...shape.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">However&mdash;grateful as I am&mdash;your depth of soul and spirit, and your flexible physique will only get you so far. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">An anecdote from the other day to illustrate my point: strolling late into class was a sexy blonde dude in a black beater tank and shorts that looked like swim trunks&mdash;not yoga gear, which was fine. If you\'re in head-to-toe Lululemon, I suspect you\'ll ask me if I have a brother. Sexy tardy guy insisted on rolling his mat out next to mine, even after the teacher suggested another spot in the room. \"<em>Oooh</em>,\" I thought. \"Class was good&mdash;and now it\'s GREAT.\"&nbsp;I had visions of our post-yoga tea together.&nbsp;I sat up straighter and tightened my lower abs while my new next-mat neighbor took a seat on his just slightly in front of me. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">I had a full view of his horrific back-hair configuration: angel-wings of fur on each shoulder blade. As the hem of his shirt crept up during class, it revealed even more back hair. I doubt even Buddha would approve.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">I spent the rest of class ignoring his glances and bailed not one minute after it ended.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Guys, please: the gorilla look is not alluring. It is not the good kind of manly.&nbsp;It is revolting.&nbsp;It suggests you don\'t care for personal grooming&mdash;but you know (and we know) you love ladies who groom. Frankly, we wonder what\'s growing in your shorts when we see what\'s creeping on your back. Do everyone a favor and get yourself to any salon for a quick&mdash;and really not that painful&mdash;wax. Take a Tylenol and a shot of patron if you must. No one wants to run their fingers through your silky back hairs: NO one.&nbsp;You are far sexier with a bald back, looking not like <em>the</em> shag, but more like someone <em>to</em> shag.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Namaste.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she believes that men call, and little boys text.</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: small;\"><strong><br /></strong></span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-09-23 02:08:53','2011-12-13 03:30:13',3,'5399052_f248.jpg','image/jpeg',17580,'2011-09-23 02:08:53',0,'2011-12-13 03:30:13',1,'gorilla-warfare','Gorilla Warfare '),(58,'Top 5 Reasons Why Men From NY Deserve To Get It In ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;m not a native New Yorker but I have been here for a significant amount of time: long enough to know it&rsquo;s a pretty remarkable place, at least. And the top-notch level of quality pervasive among the New York male population has been the subject of my fascination since I was fresh off the Boeing (jet). While certain areas are renowned for their douche factor, I&rsquo;m confident when I say that the vast majority are not only doable, but also dateable. Highly dateable. Here are a few examples why&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">1. The accent: hard, rugged, and like a fine wine&hellip; they only get better with age. While I will admit that some versions of the New York accent are slightly unbearable, just hearing some of these Yankee boys say the word &ldquo;water&rdquo; makes me wet.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"> &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">2. A lot of the time they\'re <em>actually</em> as gorgeous and charming as they think they are. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">3. Most are either immensely book or street smart&hellip; or both. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph