nt-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Let&rsquo;s just say that for one moment <strong>TLC&rsquo;s</strong> scandalous show <a href=\"http://tlc.howstuffworks.com/tv/toddlers-tiaras\">Toddlers and Tiaras</a> starring the biggest little divas like baby Eden and baby Makenzie wasn&rsquo;t stirring up so much controversy.&nbsp; We could look past the creepy flippers and focus on all the glitz and glamour of these stylish little pageant queens. &nbsp;We know there is a lot of backlash against such young ones dressing up so much, but we can&rsquo;t help but secretly love the drag queen training from birth. &nbsp;What do you think of the little dolls?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/queens-of-everything-12-glamourous-toddlers-and-tiaras-moments-to-remember/\">http://fashionindie.com/queens-of-everything-12-glamourous-toddlers-and-tiaras-moments-to-remember/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-26 11:14:31','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'toddlers-tiaras-eden-9-210x296.jpg','image/jpeg',29620,'2011-09-26 11:14:31',0,'2011-09-26 11:14:46',1,'baby-divas-top-12-toddlers-tiaras-moments','Baby Diva\'s: Top 12 Toddlers & Tiaras Moments '),(63,'Power Meals For Powerful Men  ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">If you want to maintain an active lifestyle and perform your best, it&rsquo;s vital that you feed your body the quality nutrients it requires. Preparing your own classic standby meals is a great way to not only increase your enjoyment from eating but also treat your body right.<br /> <br /> In a world where far too many men are dining out or relying on convenience or <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt_100/145_eating_well.html\">fast food</a> for sustenance, it&rsquo;s time to revamp your cooking skills and create your own dishes.<br /> <br /> Here are 10 great power meals that every man should be able to make.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/top_10/fitness/top-10-power-meals-every-man-should-be-able-to-make.html\">http://www.askmen.com/top_10/fitness/top-10-power-meals-every-man-should-be-able-to-make.html</a></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-09-27 23:28:26','2011-10-23 12:29:42',4,'1311177171_top-10-power-meals-every-man-should-be-able-to-make_2.jpg','image/jpeg',181928,'2011-09-27 23:28:25',0,'2011-09-27 23:30:18',1,'power-meals-for-powerful-men','Power Meals For Powerful Men  '),(64,'Top Ten Trannys That Should Be On The Milan Runways ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">We at FashionIndie love a good tranny. (Not PC, we know and don&rsquo;t care.) Nothing would make us happier than to see &nbsp;tran everywhere we went. That being said we&rsquo;ve picked 10 werqing <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/category/womens-fashion/\">girls</a> that could&nbsp;definitely&nbsp;spice up the very mundane runways of Milan this season. And hell most of them can teach these 12 year old <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/category/womens-fashion/\">girls</a> a walking lesson. (Looking at you<a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/lindsey-wixson-takes-a-tumble-on-versace-spring-2012-runway/\"> Lindsey Wixson</a>)&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/top-ten-trannys-that-should-be-on-the-milan-runways/\">http://fashionindie.com/top-ten-trannys-that-should-be-on-the-milan-runways/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-27 23:47:46','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'tumblr_ln3ck7bk5n1qhr166o1_500.png','image/png',444138,'2011-09-27 23:47:45',0,'2011-09-27 23:49:01',1,'top-ten-trannys-that-should-be-on-the-milan-runways','Top Ten Trannys That Should Be On The Milan Runways '),(66,'The Rape Fantasy: One Time That \"No\" Means \"You Better\"','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Back in college while expanding my sexual horizons with my then boyfriend I jumped at the opportunity to dress up as a secretary and fulfill an alleged CEO/corporate hoe fantasy of his. How brave of him, I figured, to trust me enough to open up and express his deepest, darkest sexual desires (update: the secretary fetish was by no means as deep and dark as his desires went... I have a closet full of skeletons in the form of adult costumes for which he is entirely to blame). So I donned a skintight pencil skirt, blue button-up that was largely un-buttoned and my most corporate looking of hooker heels. I took his calls, organized his file cabinet and </span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">gave him the ride of his life&nbsp; -if I may say so myself- </span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">atop his IKEA dorm-room desk. Who knew bringing someone their coffee could bring them to orgasm? I aim to please&hellip; that&rsquo;s just how I get down. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Like any boyfriend should he asked me what one of my sexual fantasies was, to which I answered with what I reasoned to be a more-or-less&nbsp; commonplace response: I have a rape fantasy. He was taken aback but I was&nbsp; eventually taken against my will&hellip; exactly how I wanted it. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">A large number of men are surprised to hear that the rape scenario ranks #1 on the list of top female sexual fantasies. It&rsquo;s one of the bandwagons I&rsquo;ll get on, but only because its one of the bandwagons that gets me off. <strong>Women don&rsquo;t actually want to be raped, let me make that clear.</strong> It&rsquo;s more a deep-rooted, inherently animalistic urge to be dominated by a man. In a society overtaken by the metro-sexual, over-sensitive type male, many women just want men to be men (ladies: if the aforementioned is your type, we&rsquo;re just going to have to agree to disagree). And there is no greater display of masculinity than being taken -from behind or just in general- ravaged, and used entirely for our partner&rsquo;s pleasure. It&rsquo;s hot. Like, religious experience hot. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">We know you&rsquo;re not <em>actually</em> raping us (hopefully) and it&rsquo;s simply blissful to imagine that we\'re so irresistibly sexy that you simply will not take &ldquo;no&rdquo; for an answer. You don&rsquo;t have to rough her up and make it hurt per se (don&rsquo;t knock it till you try it), or go to any severe theatrical lengths, but there are definitely a few maneuvers that can be of great help in this particular situation. Namely: pin her arms behind her head, throw her into positions, pull her hair, grab her throat (gently), smack her ass, tell her that her pussy belongs to you&hellip; Seriously, just use your imagination. But think more along the lines of Angelina Jolie and Antonio Banderas in <em>Original Sin</em> and less Jodie Foster in <em>The Accused</em>. Sex is supposed to be fun and since rape fantasies are still slightly taboo, I&rsquo;d imagine that there is ample room here for misunderstanding. Communication, as always, seems to be key. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Now go fourth and conquer&hellip; her. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong>*</strong> I am referring to lovemaking </span><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">(or whatever you want to call it)</span><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"> between consenting adults. I do not condone rape, nor do I think it\'s in any way something not to be taken seriously. Rape is an egregious crime and I truly believe that the vast majority of women <em>and</em> men agree with me, 110%. But the fact still remains that The Rape Fantasy is one of the most frequently reported &ndash;albeit controversial- of female fantasies. It&rsquo;s a fantasy&hellip; as in it&rsquo;s fake. Please don&rsquo;t drop a dime and call the PC police on me. Seriously&hellip; there&rsquo;s enough of that going around as is.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-09-28 07:28:55','2012-01-09 21:22:52',5,'images-3.jpg','image/jpeg',4581,'2011-09-28 07:28:55',0,'2012-01-09 21:22:52',1,'the-rape-fantasy-one-time-that-no-means-you-better','The Rape Fantasy: One Time That \"No\" Means \"You Better\"'),(67,'Fashion\'s Got a New Vice ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&ldquo;As I&rsquo;m sure you know, being in a crowd while on acid is the worst thing in the world [<em>True</em>]. As I&rsquo;m sure you also know, fashion people are the worst people in the entire world [<em>Unfortunately, doubly true</em>].&rdquo; So begins <a href=\"http://www.vice.com/read/london-fashion-week-on-acid\"><em><span style=\"color: blue; text-decoration: none;\">Vice Magazine</span></em>&lsquo;s &ldquo;coverage&rdquo; of <strong><span style=\"color: blue; text-decoration: none;\">London Fashion Week</span></strong></a>. Sending a young girl named Elektra to <strong>Topshop Unique</strong>&lsquo;s spring 2012 runway show on acid is such a <em>Vice</em> thing to do &mdash; and <em>Vice</em> is sooooo 10 years ago that I didn&rsquo;t even realize it was still corrupting youth. But I&rsquo;m glad that someone is&hellip;besides <strong>Justin Bieber</strong>. <em>Vice</em>&lsquo;s experiment in experimentation proved successful enough, however, that those kooky kids are broadening their coverage of fashion&hellip;in their own unique way.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/fashions-got-a-new-vice/\">http://fashionindie.com/fashions-got-a-new-vice/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-09-28 13:56:12','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'vice-210x140.jpg','image/jpeg',7507,'2011-09-28 13:56:12',0,'2011-09-28 13:56:20',1,'fashions-got-a-new-vice','Fashion\'s Got a New Vice '),(69,'James Dean: A Fashion Retrospective ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Today, September 30th, 56 years ago, 24-year-old <strong>James Dean</strong> died in a car crash, prematurely ending a promising film career but cementing his status as a cinematic icon. Over the years, his legend only grows and his style has become as iconic as his acting roles. Just take a look at the season&rsquo;s runways and editorials where Dean&rsquo;s spirit looms large.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/james-dean-a-fashion-retrospective/\">http://fashionindie.com/james-dean-a-fashion-retrospective/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-01 11:35:27','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'dean1.jpg','image/jpeg',249598,'2011-10-01 11:35:26',0,'2011-10-01 11:36:08',1,'james-dean-a-fashion-retrospective','James Dean: A Fashion Retrospective '),(70,'Tom Ford Stops to Smell... The Roses ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Oh, <strong>Tom Ford</strong>, you dirty old man you. A chic and incredibly talented dirty, old man, but a dirty old man nonetheless. In <em>GQ Russia &ndash;&nbsp;</em><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/indie-newsroom-dior-to-hang-out-with-their-wang-out-tom-ford-keeps-it-classy-rihanna-upsets-irish-with-her-boobs/\" target=\"_blank\">the cover of which is a typically classy affair</a> &mdash; Ford smells some perfume strips from the butt cheeks of a naked female model. Just another day at work for Mr. Ford. My only grievance, why not a male model? </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/tom-ford-stops-to-smell-the-roses/\">http://fashionindie.com/tom-ford-stops-to-smell-the-roses/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-01 11:40:28','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'screen-shot-2011-09-30-at-11-41-33-am1-210x281.png','image/png',96442,'2011-10-01 11:40:27',0,'2011-10-01 11:40:46',1,'tom-ford-stops-to-smell-the-roses','Tom Ford Stops to Smell... The Roses '),(71,'Too Much of a Good Thing','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: small;\">Written by Lauren Chen </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">As a self-proclaimed magazine fetishist, I can&rsquo;t resist stopping to take a peek at some of my favorites &ndash; SELF, Glamour, StyleWatch and Allure &ndash; whenever I pass the newsstand. As I flip through their glossy pages and begin to fantasize about bikini tops, maxi skirts, denim shorts and floppy hats, article titles showcasing tips on weight loss and exercise routines jump out at me.<em>&ldquo;Drop 10, 20, 30 pounds!&rdquo;</em> one screams. &ldquo;<em>Get your best bikini bod!&rdquo;</em> another advertises. I think back to my own daily exercises, wondering how I can make the time to add these new routines to my regimen. <strong>Is it too much?</strong> I wonder. Furthermore, <strong>how do I know when it&rsquo;s too much?&nbsp;</strong>As health-conscious and constantly on-the-go collegiettes&trade;, <strong>it&rsquo;s often hard for us to gauge whether or not we&rsquo;re overdoing it and even harder for us to scale back</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>We&rsquo;ve all heard about watching how much we eat, but we rarely hear about watching how much we exercise.</strong> Turns out, it&rsquo;s just as important, because there really is such thing as having too much of a good thing.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://www.hercampus.com/health/too-much-good-thing-what-does-over-exercising-really-mean\">http://www.hercampus.com/health/too-much-good-thing-what-does-over-exercising-really-mean</a></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-10-01 11:49:54','2011-10-23 12:29:42',4,'aa6109ab.jpg','image/jpeg',36413,'2011-10-01 11:49:53',0,'2011-10-01 11:50:20',1,'too-much-of-a-good-thing','Too Much of a Good Thing'),(72,'Top 13 Random Ass Thoughts From This Weekend ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Ok, so my mind likes to wander to some weird places. Basically, you&rsquo;ll either think I&rsquo;m a genius or borderline mentally retarded (or whatever the hell the PC term is these days). Either option could be the case, we really aren&rsquo;t sure yet. In any event, hope you enjoy&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">1. The word &ldquo;panties&rdquo; should be banned from the English language. Don&rsquo;t even get me started on &ldquo;moist&rdquo;&hellip; or &ldquo;moist panties&rdquo; for that matter.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">2. Guys: If she gives you head, a finger bang does NOT an even &ldquo;score&rdquo; make.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">3. Sex addiction is not real. We are all sex addicts. If you&rsquo;re not addicted to sex, you haven&rsquo;t been doing it correctly. And I don&rsquo;t believe that something can be an addiction if everyone has it. Addiction denotes unusual. Sex &ldquo;rehab&rdquo; is for high profile individuals, such as politicians and David Duchovny, who were caught with their pants down (literally) and needed to do some damage control. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">4. Dirty talk is the shit. Get over yourself and start mouthing off. Seriously, you&rsquo;re not a whore: you&rsquo;re just talking like one for a few minutes. More than a few if you&rsquo;ve either a) found a winner or b) he took a Viagra&hellip; or any of the other various boner meds on the market today.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">5. A 10-minute post sex cuddling sesh is not only polite; it&rsquo;s obligatory unless she isn&rsquo;t a fan of the cuddle. And if she tells you she isn&rsquo;t a fan of the cuddle, she doesn&rsquo;t really like you. I have yet to meet a woman that doesn&rsquo;t love to be wrapped in some serious man arms after putting out&hellip; unless she could care less about the man attached to said arms. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">6. For whatever reason the birth control pill freaks me the f**k out. I mean, it&rsquo;s awesome for feminism or whatever (or so they want us to believe) but a daily dose of hormones? Hormones can turn a man into a woman and vice versa, that&rsquo;s weird. And no, my distrust has nothing to do with the Pope or my religion. So don&rsquo;t go there&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">7. News in America is comical. Since there isn&rsquo;t much hope for it at least make it more entertaining. Namely, the male anchors should be just as hot as the female ones. Seriously, I&rsquo;d like some morning wood with my morning coffee as well and no&hellip; Steve Doocy on FOX &amp; Friends isn&rsquo;t cutting it. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">8. Science and technology have achieved some truly astounding things. Yet childbirth and condoms still suck ass. Instead of spending tax-payer dollars on inventing fabricated ailments, such as restless leg syndrome, just so you can pedal even more medication to the American people, spend some time solving problems we actually deal with on a regular basis. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">9. Sexting your ex-boyfriend is probably a bad idea, but I can&rsquo;t really judge. There&rsquo;s no way he deleted that picture after his solo-love session out of &ldquo;respect&rdquo; for you. There&rsquo;s a reason he&rsquo;s a past tense lover and it probably has something to do with the fact that he didn&rsquo;t respect you. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">10.The only inconvenient truth that I&rsquo;ll buy is that you can&rsquo;t f**k your way into a relationship&hellip; sucks. But trust me, I\'ve tried. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">11.Being called &ldquo;law school cute&rdquo; is not a compliment. It&rsquo;s essentially the same as winning the gold-medal at the Special Olympics: either way, you still lose. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">12.There should only be two things that a person can do to make you want to punch them square in the face: tell you that &ldquo;everything happens for a reason&rdquo; and drive a PT cruiser. True story: I once saw a bright purple PT cruiser with that disgusting fake wood paneling around the sides&hellip; I bet that person owns a pair of Crocs and hasn&rsquo;t been laid since a Catholic was President. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">13.Body boarding is like sex: real easy lying down, now try standing up.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-03 11:11:05','2012-01-09 21:22:30',5,'random-thoughts.jpg','image/jpeg',20469,'2011-10-03 11:11:04',0,'2012-01-09 21:22:30',1,'top-13-random-ass-thoughts-from-this-weekend','Top 13 Random Ass Thoughts From This Weekend '),(73,'Kanye West\'s Freshman Womens Collection','<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Yesterday Kanye West debuted his first ever collection under his new label DW in Paris.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">We think the collection is pretty solid. What do you think?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/kanye-wests-first-ever-womens-collection/\">http://fashionindie.com/kanye-wests-first-ever-womens-collection/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-03 11:55:11','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'00020m-210x315.jpg','image/jpeg',15340,'2011-10-03 11:55:11',0,'2011-10-03 11:55:33',1,'kanye-wests-freshman-womens-collection','Kanye West\'s Freshman Womens Collection'),(74,'Real New Yorkers That Look (Really) Good ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: medium;\"><strong>Exhibit \"A\"</strong>: a man that got it right... good on ya, brah</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">New York City (and even the surrounding areas: Westchester County, I&rsquo;m talking to you) is teeming with men that know how to dress. And yet on a daily basis I see egregious crimes against fashion that stir anger, deplete my very soul and incite a possible citizen&rsquo;s arrest. If you&rsquo;re having issues in the attire department (you know who you are&hellip; and if you don&rsquo;t, just give up), take a look around at your fellow man and take some serious notes because class is in session&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Gentlemen of the jury, please note exhibit \"A\": good-looking male, early 20&rsquo;s, born and raised in New York&hellip; and it shows. Dress is casual spiff*, shoes are doper than last night&rsquo;s piff, and the most important aspect of all is he looks like he spent all of two minutes throwing together this particular ensemble. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Men tend to have it easy in the fashion department and I&rsquo;m ok with that as they\'re supposed to exude a certain carefree attitude when dressing themselves. Extreme lengths are for the extremely insecure. Keep it that way. Go with clothing that fits well, which means a loose fit that still shows her what you&rsquo;re rocking underneath it all. If you want to branch out and show some personality, stick to shirts and shoes. Cool shirt, cool shoes&hellip; you get serviced. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Index</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Casual Spiff: spiffy yet still casual. Therefore it&rsquo;s casual spiff. I&rsquo;m coining it. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief </span></strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-10-03 12:36:15','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'photo-2.jpg','image/jpeg',111496,'2011-10-03 12:44:14',0,'2011-10-17 20:31:18',1,'real-new-yorkers-that-look-really-good','Real New Yorkers That Look (Really) Good '),(75,'Planet Fitness: Where Guido\'s & Gunts Go To Die','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">When it comes to working out on the regular I have a tendency to go in phases. For months at a time I&rsquo;ll work out religiously, almost fanatically, and then follow that up with a few months hiatus. The gym and I have a love/hate relationship and I&rsquo;ll admit that I find it boring at times. Furthermore, if I don&rsquo;t have music&hellip; forget about it. But I have noticed that my general sense of well-being is far more pronounced during my &ldquo;on&rdquo; phases. Not to mention the fact that while many New Yorkers are now chilling out because its no longer &ldquo;beach season&rdquo;, surfers state-wide are amping up their workouts because unfortunately the only season less forgiving than that of &ldquo;beach&rdquo; is that of &ldquo;wet-suit&rdquo;: sucks some major d. So, in an attempt to up my endorphins and down my suit size I made the decision to get my increasingly fatter ass back at it. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Day 1: October 3<sup>rd</sup>, 2011<br /></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I was immediately reminded why I stopped getting my gym on. I&rsquo;ll elaborate&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The gym I attend is sketchy, doesn&rsquo;t have any classes, and is full of both guidos and law students: an undoubtedly interesting mix. However, the membership fee is a whopping $100 per year. Yes, you read that correctly. And yes, at Planet Fitness you get what you pay for. There are certainly some limitations that come with paying less per annum than my nightly bar tab&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Shorts, tank tops, or any article of clothing whatsoever that shows any trace, vague or otherwise, of tit/ass is a no go. EVERY. SINGLE. GUY will stare. Gawk actually. And it&rsquo;s incredibly uncomfortable. I once made the colossal mistake of wearing a baby tee (I mean, it wasn&rsquo;t July and oppressively hot or anything) and a middle-aged married man with more gunt* than Rosanne Barr stared so unapologetically I was forced to actually verbally communicate my discomfort to my fellow exerciser: awkward to say the least. I mean, take a moment to enjoy the view but go ahead and move on with your life after a few short seconds, Mr. old enough to be my father. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Additionally, the guido &ldquo;juice heads&rdquo; who are straight out of MTV&rsquo;s <em>Jersey Shore</em> jump on all of the machines like they\'re a roofied chick in Seaside and don&rsquo;t let anyone else get in on the cardiovascular action, even for a quick set (God forbid their GTL is inconvenienced in any way). I either have to go at 10 am with all the MILF&rsquo;s or 10 pm with all the losers that have nothing better to do if I want to get any kind of workout in. I&rsquo;m not a morning person and I have a partying habit to maintain so this means I don&rsquo;t have many windows of workout opportunities. Oh white people problems, how I hate thee&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">However, I will admit that simply lacing up my running shoes and setting foot in the gym after so long felt uplifiting -although slightly intimidating. So let\'s just ignore the fact that my treadmill performance was less than stellar but hey, at least I didn\'t pull a bitch move and get on the elliptical. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">A good way to get in a rut of any sort is to become inactive. My goal is to find some sort of balance so as to once and for all end this pattern of extremes that I see in my own workout habits and those of many people I know. The only way to go about fitness in general -whether it be exercise, diet or both- is to develop routines that are reasonable and can be maintained over the long term. Only then will fitness and health be an integral part of ones life and ultimately lead to a general sense of contentment- both internal and external. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">So for now I&rsquo;m just going to have to accept the uncomfortable stares, relentless guidos, and awkward call times as inalienable truths of my current fitness reality. But f**k it: the gym costs less than $10 a month. What did I expect, Equinox? Dare to dream&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Index</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Gunt: Gut that is so pronounced it morphs into ones -forgive my language- c**t. Generally seen on older women, it exists in male form as well. I&rsquo;ve seen it therefore I believe it&hellip; is gross. If you&rsquo;re rocking one: no bueno. Seriously, do something about it because no one wants to have sex with someone that appears to come with utters included. Unless they\'re into some kind of farm animal fetishim, in which case... get on with your bad self.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief </span></strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-10-03 20:44:36','2011-12-09 06:47:37',4,'jsronnie.jpg','image/jpeg',50548,'2011-10-03 20:44:36',0,'2011-10-17 20:25:24',1,'planet-fitness-where-guidos-gunts-go-to-die','Planet Fitness: Where Guido\'s & Gunts Go To Die'),(76,'How To Rock A Pocket Square ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The pocket square is&nbsp;definitely&nbsp;on of the most overlooked <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/category/mens-fashion-designers/\">mens</a>&nbsp;accessories&nbsp;today. This might be&nbsp;that&nbsp;many guys don&rsquo;t know how to properly wear the furnishings. We&rsquo;ve picked our best real life pocket square looks to help our confused brothers out.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/how-to-wear-a-pocket-square/\">http://fashionindie.com/how-to-wear-a-pocket-square/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-04 01:10:55','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'gqny64.jpg','image/jpeg',239716,'2011-10-04 01:12:08',0,'2011-10-04 01:12:39',1,'how-to-rock-a-pocket-square','How To Rock A Pocket Square '),(77,'Get Laid Even When The Game Is On ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Sometimes that unmistakable, unquenchab