tracted isn&rsquo;t going to be a marathoner in the sack. But a quickie, although twice as fast, can be twice as nice. Just keep your expectations in check and you&rsquo;ll be riding the pine in no time.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-04 02:01:32','2012-01-09 21:22:10',5,'victorias-secret-adriana-lima-football.jpg','image/jpeg',56895,'2011-10-04 02:01:31',0,'2012-01-09 21:22:10',1,'get-laid-even-when-the-game-is-on','Get Laid Even When The Game Is On '),(78,'5 Steps to Werqing the Highest Heel','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Walking right in a set of heels is hard werq. Every lady in this place knows it and will continue to rise 5 or 6 inches to the challenge so long as they look this good. While you may have your strutting solution in place, take these tips to make your sky high sashay even more comfortably graceful. They&rsquo;ll keep you looking like this <strong>Lindsey Wixson</strong> in&nbsp;<strong>Oscar de la Renta</strong>:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/5-steps-to-werqing-the-highest-heel/\">http://fashionindie.com/5-steps-to-werqing-the-highest-heel/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-04 10:13:10','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'christian-louboutin-point-shoes-403x560-210x291.jpg','image/jpeg',23579,'2011-10-04 10:13:10',0,'2011-10-04 10:14:00',1,'5-steps-to-werqing-the-highest-heel','5 Steps to Werqing the Highest Heel'),(79,'Johnny Depp Gets Raped ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Have you ever raped Johnny Depp? If you&rsquo;ve ever taken a fan photo or been on set at a photo shoot with him, he feels like you have.&nbsp;While discussing the experience of getting his photo taken, he tells Vanity Fair&rsquo;s Nick Tosches, <strong>&ldquo;Well, you just feel like you&rsquo;re being raped somehow. &nbsp;Raped&hellip; It feels like a kind of weird &mdash; just weird, man.</strong> Whenever you have a photo shoot or something like that, it&rsquo;s like, you just feel dumb. &nbsp;It&rsquo;s just so stupid&rdquo;. &nbsp;Interesting note to come from one of the world&rsquo;s most photographed men.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/johnny-depp-gets-raped/\">http://fashionindie.com/johnny-depp-gets-raped/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-04 16:30:21','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'johnny_depp_2011-210x190.jpg','image/jpeg',16129,'2011-10-04 16:30:21',0,'2011-10-04 16:30:34',1,'johnny-depp-gets-raped','Johnny Depp Gets Raped '),(80,'Kate\'s Wedding Dre$$ Breaks Records & The Bank ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Kate Middleton&rsquo;s wedding dress had been on display for 10 weeks when the exhibition closed this Monday. More than 60,000 people saw Kate&rsquo;s bridal gown, which generated an estimated&nbsp;&pound;10.5m.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Although Elizabeth II, being the Queen Bitch she is, famously described the Buckingham Palace installation as &ldquo;<a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/indie-newsroom-submit-to-sozzani-mcqueen-hits-half-mil-gaga-nails-blackberry/\">horrid</a>,&rdquo; people apparently went ahead and bought the&nbsp;&pound;17.50 ticket for it anyway. The money will not only go to new skirt suits for the Queen, some of it will actually go to charity too.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/kates-wedding-dre-breaks-records-and-the-bank/\">http://fashionindie.com/kates-wedding-dre-breaks-records-and-the-bank/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-05 10:54:22','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'katedress-210x256-1.jpg','image/jpeg',11310,'2011-10-05 10:54:22',0,'2011-10-05 10:54:35',1,'kates-wedding-dre-breaks-records-the-bank','Kate\'s Wedding Dre$$ Breaks Records & The Bank '),(81,'Love, Not Caution ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Pining for the one that got away -while poetic and needlessly dramatic- is no way to live life. But it can be intoxicating. Emotions are extreme, good music seems as though it was authored just for you and the artist within makes a cameo appearance. But anyone brave enough to have loved and cursed enough to have lost knows that the overwhelming unease and inner turmoil that accompanies such a loss is akin to serving hard time in a mental prison. I&rsquo;ve fallen in love twice, fallen out of love once, and I&rsquo;m single&hellip;&nbsp; you do the math. I&rsquo;m serving what seems like a life sentence, the crime for which I am now a repeat offender. But with my (generally) good behavior and prison overcrowding I&rsquo;m confident that I&rsquo;ll be paroled any day now.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The first time I fell in love I was in college. It was as if something inside of me recognized him although we were complete strangers: like I knew, before I could have possibly known, that he was going to play a significant role in my life. I let intuition be my guide and it lead me into the lions den. And I thank God that it did. Although we&rsquo;re no longer together, he bore witness to some of the most important years of my life and I did the same for him. How, then, could I ever regret him? Despite the fighting, tears and depleted self-esteem I know first-hand what it feels like to love someone more than I love myself and am, therefore, a better person as a result. It was only when I came to these realizations that I was able to repair after the demise of our relationship. No matter how much I hated him or how many other men I pursued -aimlessly and with reckless abandon- out of revenge, nothing laid my mind to rest quite like submitting to the belief that there was no way to know what life would have been like had I not met him but that, for all I knew, it could have been worse. So I resigned my memories of him, and of us, to my proverbial back pocket and moved on with my life. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">And now the present: the second attempt at love and ultimate exercise in loss. Little in life is certain but that my mastery of the English language</span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"> will fall short of a thorough and sufficiently eloquent expression of</span> <span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"> how I felt the first time I came across this person. I was intrigued, awestruck, and unequivocally disarmed: I was like Alice before the hole. Again, just as before, was this recognition of something otherworldly: something worth derailment. For him I experienced the entire spectrum of human emotion: lust, longing, love, loathing&hellip; and everything in between. Temporary insanity ensued after things ended and still persists now (in smaller measure) as I rebuild, but I can&rsquo;t help but be eternally grateful to know that I still have the propensity -and the ability- to feel with such ardor and conviction. I&rsquo;m single, I&rsquo;m imperfect, but I&rsquo;m brave.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I highly recommend falling in love as many times, and with as much intensity, as you can. Go down that rabbit hole because what is the purpose of such a capacity for human emotion if you&rsquo;re not going to use it? Falling in love is often times wrought with pain and characterized by a loss of control that is nothing short of maddening. But the potential payoff is immense beyond the wildest of imaginations&hellip; Not to mention <strong>sex is even <em>more</em> orgasmic if you&rsquo;re in love with the person</strong>. So, basically, I really needn&rsquo;t say more. I&rsquo;ll rest my case, and my troubled mind, with that. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-05 13:37:39','2012-01-09 21:21:51',5,'alice-falling-down-rabbit-hole-1cp1iga.jpg','image/jpeg',43330,'2011-10-05 13:37:38',0,'2012-01-09 21:21:51',1,'love-not-caution','Love, Not Caution '),(82,'Four Types of Weddings & How to Dress for Each One ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">You just got an invitation to a wedding, but you haven&rsquo;t a thing to wear. Perhaps you&rsquo;ve never been to a ____ wedding before and have no idea how to dress. Whatever the predicament, not to fear! We analyzed four types of weddings to fill in the above blank &ndash; black tie, cocktail, daytime and casual &ndash; and broke down an outfit for each so you don&rsquo;t have to. Now you have no excuse to underdress or look like a hooch. Read on, young ones.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/four-types-of-weddings-how-to-dress-for-each-one/\">http://fashionindie.com/four-types-of-weddings-how-to-dress-for-each-one/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-06 16:46:03','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'111099989-210x139.jpg','image/jpeg',10961,'2011-10-06 16:46:03',0,'2011-10-06 16:46:14',1,'four-types-of-weddings-how-to-dress-for-each-one','Four Types of Weddings & How to Dress for Each One '),(83,'Dumped for Someone Hotter? NBD','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">So you and your gf/bf/slampiece/FWB broke up. That sucks. Trust me, I know. Even if the involvement left a lot to be desired, just the loss of a regular supply of sex is mourn worthy. And then it happens: by way of word of mouth, Facebook stalking, or, worst of all, an in person run-in, you discover that not only has your former flame moved on but they&rsquo;ve found a shinier model with which to replace you. Ouch baby, very ouch. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">If you happen to find out that you&rsquo;ve been substituted with someone better looking, you really only have two options for how to deal: you could either take it as further evidence that you&rsquo;re unattractive and unworthy of love or you can see it as a positive. For the record, I&rsquo;m a fan of the latter. If you allow some footnote on your relationship history to convince you of your own inferiority and lack of appeal, you&rsquo;re weak minded, self-deprecating and your issues were likely the cause for why things ended. However, seeing it as a positive thing, while seemingly impossible, can be an all-important step in the process of moving on. Allow me to explain&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The fact that your ex (insert arbitrary title) has found someone more attractive means that you were in good (looking) company: by the way, your stand-ins so-called superiority in the looks department should be corroborated by at least one other non-biased individual, as your judgment is likely clouded at this time and this could all be much ado about nothing. But for arguments sake lets say they&rsquo;re hotter. Basically, this indicates that your past-tense lover maintained a certain standard level. This is a good thing. Congratulations: even if only for a short period of time you too were considered to be of sufficient caliber. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Additionally, be honest&hellip; if they left you for someone less attractive you must have been <em>that</em> bad.&nbsp; Humans are superficial beings, all looking for the next best thing so leaving one for a prettier other is logical to a certain extent. But switching things up for someone less attractive means that you were so unbearable that they would rather drop a hero and be with the zero. That indicates an extreme level of crazy and/or lack of quality on your part. Not exactly the &ldquo;accomplishment&rdquo; you should be aiming for. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This particular situation is less than preferable, whichever way you choose to look at it. But it makes sense and you&rsquo;d probably do the same thing. So, in a way, you really can&rsquo;t blame them. Don&rsquo;t get mad, get even&hellip; hotter. See it as a challenge to better yourself. And remember how your ex was insecure about xyz? Well, go find someone who is solid in those departments, stage another run-in and cut them back down to size. There&rsquo;s no reason why you shouldn&rsquo;t be with a perfect 10 as well. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-06 17:41:55','2012-01-09 21:21:26',5,'images-5.jpg','image/jpeg',13146,'2011-10-06 17:41:55',0,'2012-01-09 21:21:26',1,'dumped-for-someone-hotter-nbd','Dumped for Someone Hotter? NBD'),(85,' Real New Yorkers That Look (Really) Good: Part 2 ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Summer is donezo. How very, very sad indeed. It&rsquo;s finally time to say goodbye to long days, warm nights and sweaty men that are scantily clad. However, fall means layers, which translates to leaving more to the imagination. As can be seen above, Mr. October (once again) nailed it with his carefree, cool attempt at the quintessential autumn ensemble. For the record (ladies <em>and</em> gentlemen), he is not single&hellip; but feel free to stare -God knows I do. Let&rsquo;s break this outfit down, shall we? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">First of all, his pants aren&rsquo;t falling off his ass but they aren&rsquo;t cutting off circulation to his balls either&hellip; winning. Skinny jeans are an unequivocal &ldquo;no&rdquo;. Your boys will thank me. So show the sack some respect, maintain your fertility and stick to jeans that fall somewhere in the middle: between pants up your ass (crack) and pants on the ground.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Secondly, it&rsquo;s all about the shoes. In my humble opinion shoes can make or break an outfit, and the youthful yet sexy Van&rsquo;s pictured above are right on point. We&rsquo;re young and it&rsquo;s ok to look it&hellip; there&rsquo;s going to plenty of time to dress &ldquo;your age&rdquo; in the future, trust me. Obviously, the shoes should be of situational appropriateness but for a casual fall day something along these lines is perfect.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">And finally: the layering. The &ldquo;sweater over t-shirt&rdquo; look is not only fail-proof but pragmatic as well. One can adjust the outfit to the given temperature and still show off those God-given man muscles. Like with jeans, shirts and sweaters should be tight-<em>ish</em>, but we shouldn&rsquo;t be able to see every outline of your six-pack (or fat pack, should that be the case). When you leave a little to the imagination it allows our minds to wander and our eyes to undress you. &nbsp;Again&hellip; winning.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Mr. October is college-aged, exotic and lives in downtown NYC. His girlfriend is hot, foreign and not imaginary so don&rsquo;t even think about it&hellip; sorry. </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief <br /></span></strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-10-06 18:58:02','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'photo-6.jpg','image/jpeg',97371,'2011-10-06 19:01:56',0,'2011-10-17 20:31:32',1,'real-new-yorkers-that-look-really-good-part-2',' Real New Yorkers That Look (Really) Good: Part 2 '),(86,'Sex Positions 101','<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Many sexual partners reach a point in their relationship where they\'re ready to steer away from their boring positions and try out something more exhilarating and unique. If you\'ve managed to make it this far in a relationship, first of all, props to you. Second, chances are the sex didn\'t turn out the way you expected it to.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Don\'t lie.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">You weren\'t flexible enough, you got a cramp right between your thigh and butt cheek, or a really awkward noise came out of your vagina and you pretended like you didn\'t hear it. Yes, I\'m talking about a queef.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">There is no need to turn bright red after this happens to you girls, because you\'re not the only ones. When a penis moves in and out of you too quickly it is bound to create so much air pressure that it eventually needs to escape your vagina.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">If you feel too uncomfortable to continu