n.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">See more: </span><a href=\"http://www.fanpop.com/spots/guess/images/442443/title/adriana-lima-megan-ewing-photo\">http://www.fanpop.com/spots/guess/images/442443/title/adriana-lima-megan-ewing-photo</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>3. Alana Blanchard </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hawaiian-born professional surfer Alana Blanchard rips massive waves, rocks the thong bikini bottoms (see picture above) and still manages to garner the respect of the entire surfing world. Smoking hot blonde that charges, looks good in a bathing suit and comes laid-back, island attitude included? Can you really ask for anything else? Look out for this one because she&rsquo;s changing the world of women&rsquo;s surfing and board sports in general: and looking mad hot while doing it.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">See more: </span><a href=\"http://www.alanablanchard.com/blog/photos/?show=gallery\">http://www.alanablanchard.com/blog/photos/?show=gallery</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Watch more: <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RLJq70gND2M\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RLJq70gND2M</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>2. Mila Kunis </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">No. Explanation. Necessary. She&rsquo;s perfect. Well done Ukraine, well done.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">See more: </span><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/celebs/women/actress_100/135_mila_kunis.html\">http://www.askmen.com/celebs/women/actress_100/135_mila_kunis.html</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>1. Emmy Rossum&nbsp; </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">A lifelong New Yorker, she was nothing short of a child prodigy: singing in the Metropolitan Opera Children&rsquo;s Chorus at the ripe old age of 7 and breaking into acting by age 11. Today, you can see her play the leading role on Showtime&rsquo;s <em>Shameless</em>, which is hands down one of the best shows on television at the moment. She plays the feisty and independent Fiona Gallagher. Not only does her character make me want to <em>be</em> a better woman, she makes me want to <em>be with</em> a woman. That&rsquo;s an indication of some serious acting chops&hellip; or serious hotness. Either or.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">See more: </span><a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/media/rm1947778816/nm0002536\">http://www.imdb.com/media/rm1947778816/nm0002536</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-08 16:32:31','2012-01-09 21:20:20',5,'picture-16.png','image/png',164143,'2011-10-08 16:32:30',0,'2012-01-09 21:20:20',1,'top-9-girl-crushes','Top 9 Girl Crushes'),(92,'NAMBLA: My Top 11 Man/Boy Crushes','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">As a resident of New York I\'m treated to some truly stellar eye-candy on a (nearly) daily basis. This is the case in the city and the surrounding areas. The men are, for lack of a better word, hot.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I have a true respect for beauty, in both men and women. But I&rsquo;d like to give big ups to some of the XY chromosomes out there that have caught my attention and sparked my imagination. Some are boys, most are men but all are sexy, successful and deserve ample amounts of admiration. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>11. Dave Franco </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">He is the kid brother of mega-famous actor, James Franco, and has recently broken into the world of acting. He seems innocent, is in his &ldquo;almost famous&rdquo; stage of life and looks like the product of an Abercrombie model/Greek God combo. He is reminiscent of the kind of a guy I would have fallen head over heels for in college, and who doesn&rsquo;t love being brought back to the good ol&rsquo; days?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2002649/\">http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2002649/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>10. Simon Baker </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I really can&rsquo;t tell you what it is about this 40-something Aussie, but ever since he played the leading role in the show <em>The Guardian</em> (circa 2001), I haven&rsquo;t stopped fantasizing. Sure, he&rsquo;s more than a few years my senior but I suspect that has something to do with the fact that I&rsquo;m 100%, unequivocally in love. Mr. Baker is all man and with that down under accent I&rsquo;ll more than happily go down under&hellip; to visit, I mean. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0285370/\">http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0285370/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>9. Paolo Nutini </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This Scottish (yes, Scottish) singer/songwriter has an incredibly soulful, Tom Petty sounding voice and lyrics that can only be described as panty dropping. He&rsquo;s basically auditory napalm. Sure, he has a tendency to get so drunk before a show that he can&rsquo;t perform but he&rsquo;s young and this is rock n&rsquo; roll, good on him. Check out his songs &ldquo;Last Request&rdquo; and &ldquo;Jenny Don&rsquo;t Be Hasty&rdquo;&hellip; talented much? I thought so. You boo because you wish, John Mayer. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.paolonutini.com/photos.htm\">http://www.paolonutini.com/photos.htm</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hear more: <a href=\"http://www.mtv.com/videos/paolo-nutini/147448/last-request.jhtml\">http://www.mtv.com/videos/paolo-nutini/147448/last-request.jhtml</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>8. T.I </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This 31 year-old rapper began honing his craft at the age of 9. Now a mega-successful rap icon, his rhymes and stage presence have only gotten better&hellip; fame agrees with this HOTlanta native. He&rsquo;s a power playa in the hip-hop world, released a pretty dope album from prison and boasts a resume that is nothing short of impressive. He&rsquo;s also, not to mention, smoking hot. T.I, you can have WHATEVER you like&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Sidenote: How much better would Katy Perry&rsquo;s &ldquo;E.T.&rdquo; have been had T.I been featured, as opposed to Kanye? Think about it and get back to me. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.trapmuzik.com/photo/upscale-magazine-cover-i/\">http://www.trapmuzik.com/photo/upscale-magazine-cover-i/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hear more: <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nQJACVmankY&amp;feature=related\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nQJACVmankY&amp;feature=related</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>7. Zac Efron </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Yes, the boy from <em>High School Musical</em>. And you know what? I don&rsquo;t even care that the majority of his films suck. He&rsquo;s adorable. And while I have to admit that he was introduced to me courtesy of my 10 and 12 year old sisters -whom are also infatuated- it would appear that all girls, no matter their age, are the same and even the guppies out there can spot some truly impressive man-fish in this sea of ours. Give him a few years, throw in some five o&rsquo;clock shadow and that boy will nicely transition to man&hellip; don&rsquo;t say you weren&rsquo;t warned. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.zefron.com/\">http://www.zefron.com/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">6. Jake Gyllenhaal </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Yes, I realize he broke his back mounting a cowboy and rocked a Santa hat on his member for a dance scene in <em>Jarhead</em> (to watch, refer to the link below) but those baby blue puppy-dog eyes and mischievous smile have a power over me that is just uncanny. And I could listen to his voice until the day I die. As is evident in his choice of roles, Mr. Gyllenhaal is a risk taker. Plus he&rsquo;s 30, and that&rsquo;s a magic number. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.jakegyllenhaal.com/\">http://www.jakegyllenhaal.com/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Watch more: <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cDggufu2YG4\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cDggufu2YG4</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>5. Garrett Hedlund </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">He&rsquo;s a genuine farm boy straight out of Minnesota and first caught my eye when he played Brad Pitt&rsquo;s cousin, Patroclus, in the epically sexy film <em>Troy</em>.&nbsp; Since then he&rsquo;s starred in various other projects but I enjoyed him most recently in <em>Country Strong</em>, where he played a brooding country music artist (refer to the link below for a truly heart wrenching performance). Oh. My. God. SMOKE SHOW. He was rugged, masculine and all about the true love thing. Basically, he&rsquo;s perfect. And I love him. End of story. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/media/rm2338504192/nm1330560\">http://www.imdb.com/media/rm2338504192/nm1330560</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Hear more: <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pVUYmtMwSvo\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pVUYmtMwSvo</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>4. Ryan Gosling </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">He&rsquo;s one of the most talented actors of my generation and is as eclectic with roles as he is sexy as hell. Raised Mormon in a religiously zealous household, he has managed an extremely successful acting career and even released an album with his band, Dead Man&rsquo;s Bones, in recent years. He ranges from mainstream romance (um, who doesn&rsquo;t remember <em>The Notebook</em>?) to indie films. And I appreciate every second he permeates my big screen.&nbsp; Oh, Canada. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://goslingfan.com/\">http://goslingfan.com/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">3. Josh Duhamel </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Holy balls. Josh is a 6&rsquo;3&rdquo; former college football player and a native of North Dakota. He is virtually perfect looking and exactly what Michelangelo had in mind when he was creating The Statue of David. You can see him on NBC&rsquo;s <em>Las Vegas</em>, a show both highly entertaining and underrated. What he&rsquo;s doing married to Fergie of the Black Eyed Peas is beyond me, but I suppose the heart wants what it wants. And mine wants some of that. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: &nbsp;<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josh_Duhamel\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josh_Duhamel</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>2. Adam Scott </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Mr. Scott is literally the only reason to watch professional golf (see photo above). Like, the <em>only</em> reason. And while jealous guys out there will claim that he&rsquo;s not very good (who gives a shit it&rsquo;s golf), I am confident when I say that it&rsquo;s in the best interest of the PGA to keep this truly strapping man around. This Titleist athlete is tantalizing&hellip; to say the least. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:AdamScott1.jpg\">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:AdamScott1.jpg</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>1. Chris Hemsworth </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Yet another Australia native to make the list (We&rsquo;re at 3 now), I&rsquo;m not even sure what he&rsquo;s been in. He&rsquo;s an actor, I think. And you know what? Whatever. He could be an inmate serving 25 to life in a maximum-security prison for all I care&hellip; the boy is fine. A fan photo of his popped up in my facebook mini-feed and I haven&rsquo;t been able to see straight since. Goddamn, I said Goddamn! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">See more: <a href=\"http://chris-hemsworth.us/gallery/displayimage.php?album=topn&amp;cat=0&amp;pid=14744#top_display_media\">http://chris-hemsworth.us/gallery/displayimage.php?album=topn&amp;cat=0&amp;pid=14744#top_display_media</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-09 17:08:14','2012-01-09 21:19:34',5,'nov_scott06_299x407.jpg','image/jpeg',74796,'2011-10-09 17:08:14',0,'2012-01-09 21:19:34',1,'nambla-my-top-11-manboy-crushes','NAMBLA: My Top 11 Man/Boy Crushes'),(93,'All Hail the Schenkenberg: Worlds 1st Male Supermodel','<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">As October is our month of models, we figured it was important for you, dear reader, to know your model heritage. After all, how can you know where your models are going, if you don&rsquo;t know where they&rsquo;ve been. Enter&nbsp;Marcus Lodewijk Schenkenberg van Mierop, better known as <strong>Marcus Schenkenberg</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Born in Stockholm, Sweden of Dutch and Indonesian descent on August 4, 1968. Schenkenberg was discovered by photog <strong>Barry King</strong> while rollerskating in Venice Beach in 1989 after which he appeared in ads for <strong>Calvin Klein</strong>, shot with the legendary <strong>Richard Avedon</strong> and strutted on catwalks for <strong>Versace</strong>, <strong>Donna Karan</strong> and<strong> Giorgio Armani</strong>. Schenkenberg has managed to survive over 20 years in the modeling game &mdash; as well as a stint on <strong>Vh1</strong>&lsquo;s precursor to <em>Celebrity Rehab</em>, <em>The Surreal Life</em> and a much-publicized affair with <strong>Pamela Anderson</strong> &mdash; rightly earning him the title as the <strong>World&rsquo;s First Male Supermodel.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/all-hail-the-schenkenberg-worlds-1st-male-supermodel/\">http://fashionindie.com/all-hail-the-schenkenberg-worlds-1st-male-supermodel/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-09 17:24:03','2011-10-23 12:29:42',2,'2023_p_markus_schenkenberg_2-210x376.jpg','image/jpeg',16077,'2011-10-09 17:24:03',0,'2011-10-09 17:24:21',1,'all-hail-the-schenkenberg-worlds-1st-male-supermodel','All Hail the Schenkenberg: Worlds 1st Male Supermodel'),(95,'  ,  ... Translation: Greeks Have Style','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">It&rsquo;s that time again: time to honor those style-inclined gentlemen wandering around this city of ours. To those of you that are fashion forward, we thank you. And this Greek transplant is no exception. With his cool accessories and debon-air of mystery and intrigue, his look nailed it to say the least. OPA!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Mr. Greece&rsquo;s glasses are adorable. They do make him appear more intellectual (although he is in fact extremely intelligent anyway) and frame his face perfectly&hellip; a face that includes some seriously sexy stubble, I might add. His fresh watch and bracelets add a cool, un-expected twist and keep the outfit from falling into the &ldquo;run-of-the-mill&rdquo; category. Some people were born to stand out and their ensembles should reflect this. For the record, the cigarette is not an accessory that comes recommended but I&rsquo;m not one to talk. Plus, he&rsquo;s European. We all smoke there. I&rsquo;m not saying it&rsquo;s right: it&rsquo;s unhealthy but it&rsquo;s culture. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Obviously, I&rsquo;m a fan of shoes. And his are simple, fun and attract attention for the right reasons. He can go from day to night in these casual spiff<strong>*</strong> kicks, which means they&rsquo;re both effective AND functional. And I know that men, being the (generally) practical beings that they are, should appreciate items of clothing that will make for both good-looks and an easier, more efficient (dress) life.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Only a strong, secure and otherwise masculine man can pull off pink and he does it beautifully and with ease. The light pink collared shirt is contrasted with the gray sweater in a way that is nothing short of pleasing to the eyes. The stripes on the sweater emphasize his broad chest and add flare. This outfit indicates that fall is here to stay and that&rsquo;s a good thing&hellip; as long as you guys continue to dress in such a way to make us want to undress you. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br /><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Mr. Greece is also a model. Check out his work and the amazing NV Clothing Company @</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.nv-cc.com/de\">http://www.nv-cc.com/de</a></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>* </strong>As stated in previous articles, \"casual spiff\" = spiffy yet still casual. Therefore it&rsquo;s casual spiff. I&rsquo;m coining it. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief <br /></span></strong></span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-10-09 18:00:45','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'photo-7.jpg','image/jpeg',82269,'2011-10-09 18:00:44',0,'2011-10-17 20:32:04',1,'-----translation-greeks-have-style','  ,  ... Translation: Greeks Have Style'),(96,'Find Your Religion With Dilia Oviedo','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">When <strong>Dilia Oviedo </strong>got her first camera at age 10, she knew her religion would be photography. Originally from the Dominican Republic, she now finds inspiration from her surroundings in Barcelona where she lives and works. We&rsquo;re obsessing over her debut on <strong>Ben Trovato </strong>titled <em><strong>A Religious Experience</strong></em><strong>,&nbsp;</strong>featuring the gorgeous models<strong>&nbsp;Lauren Auerbach</strong> and<strong>&nbsp;Ann M&uuml;&uuml;rsepp</strong>. Styled by<strong> Ana Sting</strong>, we have faith in the church of Oviedo.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/find-your-religion-with-dilia-oviedo/\">http://fashionindie.com/find-your-religion-with-dilia-oviedo/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-10 16:23:07','2011-10-23 12:29:43',2,'are-dilia-oviedo_ben-trovato15-210x315.jpg','image/jpeg',30273,'2011-10-10 16:23:07',0,'2011-10-10 16:23:40',1,'find-your-religion-with-dilia-oviedo','Find Your Religion With Dilia Oviedo'),(97,'Occupy Easy Street: A Guide to Being Bought  ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The collapse of the world economy is in full effect. Need some extra cash, ladies? Sell yourself! There are plenty of men out there in the market for a good old-fashioned trophy. Why earn your love when he can buy it? We all know it ain&rsquo;t trickin if you got it. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">If you&rsquo;re new to the (human) stock market, here&rsquo;s a fool-proof guide that will have you to selling, trading and buying like a pro (hoe) in no time! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Have a dinner date outfit ready. Plan ahead, make sure to flaunt whatever assets you bring to the table and even spend an obscene amount of money on looking the part. From his perspective, the point of a trophy is to make other men jealous and think that he&rsquo;s the shit.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Prepare yourself. Get plenty of beauty rest throughout the day (it&rsquo;s not like you&rsquo;re busy with anything else&hellip; with the exception of lunch dates, of course) because he&rsquo;ll expect you to be up all night servicing him. Put on way too much makeup, flatiron your hair -and his shirts, should they require it- and be youthful looking. He has been with a lot of serious, complicated (translation: multi-dimensional) career women all day and likely wants something simple to look at. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Be a little more interesting and act a little more interested in him than you actually are. His job, although high paying, is boring and your personal anecdotes on insignificant pop-culture provide a much-needed break from reality. Pretending to be infatuated with him, despite his arrogant demeanor and receding hairline, gives him a rise and one of your many duties is to provide this. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- During that time of the month you should prepare to please him orally&hellip; a lot. And be sure to appear as though it is your pleasure to do so. After all, catering to his sexual needs will bring you immense personal satisfaction. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Maximize all noise&hellip; in bed. Just before the time of his orgasm&rsquo;s arrival, increase the volume of your moans and/or sobs exponentially, so as to make him think that he&rsquo;s pleasured you far more than he actually has. No one wants to buy it if they think it&rsquo;s broken. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Be happy to see him. Even when you aren&rsquo;t. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Greet him with a warm, genuine pageant smile and show sincerity in your desire to perform for him. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Like his employees, you listen to him. You may (or may not) have a dozen meaningful things to say to him but if he&rsquo;s speaking that is not the time to share. Should he desire to hear the sound of his own voice, let him- remember, his statements and opinions are more important than yours. This is based on the assumption that you have statements and opinions, admittedly. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Don&rsquo;t complain. Like, ever. Even if he&rsquo;s late for dinner or stays out all night. He&rsquo;s probably just working late with his college-aged female intern, no big deal. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- Don&rsquo;t question anything he says or does. He is the master of the relationship and can always, therefore, exercise his will. As a purchased commodity, you have no right to challenge him. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">- A good trophy always knows her place.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Article inspired by the following tips from a 1950\'s home economics textbook: </span><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><a href=\"http://www.snopes.com/language/document/goodwife.asp\">http://www.snopes.com/language/document/goodwife.asp</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">[For the record, yes I\'m aware that the above article is, in fact, a 1950\'s urban legend. But let\'s be honest: it\'s probably more-or-less accurate. We really have come a long way... right?]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-11 01:32:37','2012-01-09 21:19:13',5,'goodwifes.jpg','image/jpeg',20242,'2011-10-11 01:32:36',0,'2012-01-09 21:19:13',1,'occupy-easy-street-a-guide-to-being-bought','Occupy Easy Street: A Guide to Being Bought  '),(98,'Oktoberfest: HoliDAY Drink & Still Be Able To (Legally) Consent By Night ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Having grown up in Central Europe, where day drinking is religion and beer is God, Oktoberfest denoted the holiest of holy months. The bier garten was my childhood playground and the memories of lederhosen, w&uuml;rsten and cups that runneth over are as equally vivid as they are heartwarming. However, drinking to such an extent and in such abundance presents certain challenges in the longevity department. Maintaining ones seeming sobriety and composure while engaging in the age-old beer connoisseur&rsquo;s tradition is not only an exercise in survival but also a true art form. So for any day drinking novice with plans to step up to the big leagues this Oktober, here are a few tips for festing like a boss. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Beer Before Liquor&hellip; Rookie Mistake </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I must admit that I too have made this error in judgment once before and the result was nothing short of catastrophic. Drinking for hours on end is doable but only when the alcoholic beverage of choice is beer, or something of similar strength. Trust me when I say that adding liquor to the mix will lead you straight down the path to hell&hellip; and it&rsquo;s paved with vomit and poor life decisions. Stick to beer and save yourself, and those around you, the (literal and metaphorical) headache. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>The Best Defense Is A Good Offense: Eat Something </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Booze has a funny way of making smart people do dumb shit. But a full stomach is like kryptonite for the unpleasant, albeit hilarious, side effects of excessive alcohol consumption. If you line your stomach, preferably with something hearty and substantial, you&rsquo;ll not only last significantly longer in the consumption race but the next days hangover will be far less severe. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>If The Beer Is Aplenty, Then There Is No Need For The Double Fist</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">There&rsquo;s no excuse for being a greedy bastard. And, incidentally, there&rsquo;s also no need for it, as it&rsquo;s unlikely that the beer is going to run out during a festival dedicated entirely to said substance. Drink one, and only one, beer at a time and be sure to savor each glass. Drink with all five senses and enjoy one of Gods greatest gifts to man. Oktoberfest is a marathon, not a sprint and drinking with haste and in excess is gluttonous, self-destructive and overeager. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Don&rsquo;t Drink And&hellip;&nbsp; </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Drive, bone, dial, conduct business, make any major life decisions, facebook, operate heavy machinery, conduct a speech (actually, please do&hellip; and film it), text, and get a tattoo/piercing/haircut or any other permanent bodily alteration. Trust me: the above-stated advice is not only sage, but also inspired from actual incidents of day drinking gone awry. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-11 05:20:30','2012-01-09 21:18:52',5,'1-1.jpg','image/jpeg',150829,'2011-10-11 05:26:03',0,'2012-01-09 21:18:52',1,'oktoberfest-holiday-drink-still-be-able-to-legally-consent-by-night','Oktoberfest: HoliDAY Drink & Still Be Able To (Legally) Consent By Night '),(99,'Friend or Faux?','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">So please listen to the message that I send<br /> Don\'t ever talk to a girl who says she just has a friend </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">-Biz Markie (Hear the rest @ <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EbH3bAvTYjg\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EbH3bAvTYjg</a>)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">While it is true that men and women can, in fact, be just friends, potential suitors are not incorrect in being suspicious if their target in question seems to have a large number of men in their life that are (allegedly) &ldquo;just friends&rdquo;. Many women, myself included, use this designation in order to alleviate the, as it turns out, founded and rational skepticism of others when a male buddy is introduced as &ldquo;my friend ______&rdquo;. However, sometimes a guy is just that&hellip; a friend. But there seems to be a lot of gray area in that there are certain friends with whom you want to be friendlier. So, stop lying to yourself and to those around you and once and for all determine if he&rsquo;s the real friend deal or a future FWB. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Sidenote: unless you&rsquo;re in an exclusive relationship, you are free to have as many &ldquo;friends&rdquo; as you want. However, I have found that if you&rsquo;re honest about the whole friend vs. &ldquo;friend&rdquo; thing, the drama will be increased in the short-term but significantly less prevelant later on down the line. When you&rsquo;re upfront with people they&rsquo;re much more likely to be upfront with you. But again let me stress that as a single woman you don&rsquo;t owe anyone any explanations. <strong>If a man wants to keep tabs on you he&rsquo;s going to have to lock it down first. </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">He&rsquo;s just a friend if you&rsquo;ve never seen his penis&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: right;