bsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you find yourself searching for interesting topics of conversation that will reel your partner in and make them want to talk to you and instantly fall in love?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you often get responses such as, &lsquo;k,\' &lsquo;ha,\' or &lsquo;cool\'?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you have to constantly fight and resist your urge to Facebook chat your partner when you see that green circle next to their name on Facebook?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">6.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Have you ever randomly shown up at someone\'s door, just because?</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">7.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you crop pictures of you and your partner and Photoshop them so that your faces are inside a heart, then make the picture the background of your phone and computer and tell people that you\'re dating?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://www.ubspectrum.com/opinion/stage-5-clingers-stop-this-rising-phenomenon-1.2642970#.TpUI_t6a9tN\">http://www.ubspectrum.com/opinion/stage-5-clingers-stop-this-rising-phenomenon-1.2642970#.TpUI_t6a9tN</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Written by Keren Baruch</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-12 17:18:09','2012-01-09 21:17:42',5,'50256_5220239161_9268_n.jpg','image/jpeg',10079,'2011-10-12 17:18:08',0,'2012-01-09 21:17:42',1,'the-rise-of-the-stage-5-clinger-hide-yo-kids-hide-yo-wife-and-definitely-hide-yo-husband','The Rise of the Stage 5 Clinger: Hide Yo Kids, Hide Yo Wife... And Definitely Hide Yo Husband'),(103,'The Big 3-0h, Hell Yes','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Alert the media: 30 is the new black. I can&rsquo;t believe it&rsquo;s taken me this long to realize that dating men in their thirties is the way to go. While I&rsquo;ll never be one to turn down a honey in is twenties, men in this age bracket just seem to do it for me. Whether it&rsquo;s their cool, self-assured nature, apparent allergy to bullshit and superiority between the sheets, I find myself willfully falling victim to the thirty-something&rsquo;s power. However, as is generally the case, there are some drawbacks to dating men that came of age in the 90&rsquo;s&hellip; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>(According To Them) They Know <em>Everything</em> </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">From which band -Pearl Jam or Nirvana- is real grunge to predicting who will likely be president in 2012, their determinations are not opinions but, as it turns out, facts of life. They firmly believe that growing up in the 90&rsquo;s was simply better than growing up in the early 2000&rsquo;s and, due to this, their tastes across the board carry significantly more power of authority. It doesn&rsquo;t matter how intelligent, mature for your age or experienced you are, they&rsquo;re right&hellip; and you&rsquo;re wrong. For the record, Nirvana isn&rsquo;t real grunge, it <em>is</em> grunge. Pearl Jam is my jam but Nirvana wins out in that debate and I don&rsquo;t care how many of you in your thirties disagree. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Why this doesn&rsquo;t matter: Popular music was better in the 90&rsquo;s. We have to search for it nowadays. Facebook didn&rsquo;t exist and people could, therefore, do whatever they wanted without worry of having it permanently chronicled on the world-wide-web. And, at the end of the day, they&rsquo;re older and a certain amount of wisdom does come with age. But often times when someone is dating a much younger individual it isn\'t your youth they&rsquo;re seeking but rather their own. So, take advantage of this and introduce them to the youth culture of today. Even though they&rsquo;ll claim they had it better, they really do appreciate the behind the scenes expose. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Sex Will Be Better&hellip; But Those Prone To Starfish Need Not Apply </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Men in their thirties have been boning for much longer than guys in their twenties. Additionally, many of them have experienced several longer-term relationships, which means they&rsquo;ve had to actually learn how to please a woman. A lot of the boys our age stick to one-night-stands, which, truth be told, are seldom pleasurable. However, these older men have busy lives and that takes it\'s sexual toll. A lot of the time they&rsquo;ll be tired and unlike their younger counter-parts, who still think sex is the coolest thing since sliced bread, there will be times when going to sleep is the more attractive option than taking care of your sexual needs. Translation: You&rsquo;re going to have to pull your own weight in the bedroom. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Why this doesn&rsquo;t matter: I have found that not only is taking a more active role educational, but more pleasurable as well. You&rsquo;ll find yourself on top a lot of the time but on the rare occasions when they do get on top of you, it\'ll count. Instead of having multiple fast and furious sessions, you&rsquo;ll get one shot and it&rsquo;ll be better than a night of non-stop mediocre sex. Its quality&hellip; not quantity. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Who&rsquo;s Your Daddy? Apparently, He Is </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">They&rsquo;ll complain that your outfits are inappropriate, that you shouldn&rsquo;t have so many male &ldquo;friends&rdquo; and that partying is overrated and that you should, instead, stay in and chill out with them&hellip; away from the hungry eyes of the guys in their twenties that frequent our usual hang-outs. When they&rsquo;re angry with you it&rsquo;s reminiscent of that time you missed curfew in junior high and dad got pissed. And when you do argue the condescension will be palpable and instead of wanting some serious make-up sex post fight you&rsquo;ll worry that you&rsquo;ll be made to sit in the corner and think about what you&rsquo;ve done. Don&rsquo;t even get me started on the potential for awkwardness when he spanks you in bed&hellip;. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Why this doesn&rsquo;t matter: He&rsquo;s not your dad (hopefully). And unless he&rsquo;s a twisted pervert that once made a cameo appearance on <em>To Catch A Predator</em>, he doesn&rsquo;t think of himself as your dad. Which means it&rsquo;s in your head&hellip; and that&rsquo;s a little too Freudian for me. So, stop thinking about it. If you must (and I\'m really not sure why this would ever be a must but there are some damaged women out there), think of him as a dirty uncle instead... too far? Tough crowd.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></span></strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-12 18:44:44','2012-01-09 21:17:23',5,'128676422167869549.jpg','image/jpeg',35010,'2011-10-12 18:44:44',0,'2012-01-09 21:17:23',1,'the-big-3-0h-hell-yes','The Big 3-0h, Hell Yes'),(104,'Fashion Forewarned: The V-Neck & Other Faux Pas ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong>The Deep V-neck</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">The deeper the neck the deeper he&rsquo;ll want you to insert your finger into his rectum while giving him head [if that offended you at least keep in mind that I took a risk... and that should come with some credit included]. V-necks are inherently effeminate and while an ever so slight V is socially acceptable, if there&rsquo;s any chest hair protruding out of the top you&rsquo;ve simply gone too far. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong>The T-<em>shit </em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">T-shirts with graphics and/or glitter are a no. Actually, they&rsquo;re a hell no. I really don&rsquo;t understand why it remains necessary to inform certain guys that this is an egregious crime against fashion. I don&rsquo;t even wear shirts that include graphics or glitter and if I won&rsquo;t rock it, there is literally no reason &ndash;or excuse- for why you should. Any piece by Ed Hardy, for instance, is a perfect example of this. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Also, shirts with stupid clich&eacute; catchphrases, such as &ldquo;trust me, I&rsquo;m a doctor&rdquo; or &ldquo;sorry for partying&rdquo; are lame. If you&rsquo;re trying to appear as though you have a sense of humor, you&rsquo;re doing just the opposite&hellip; sorry. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong>Tattoos </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">I&rsquo;m a tattoo person (I have four of my own) and I believe they can look really hot on select guys. But anything commemorating another chick or a drunken night gone wrong is not even cute. Tattoos are permanent so I do not recommend defacing your canvas for others wry amusement. Furthermore, if your great-great grandfather&rsquo;s cousin twice removed was from Italy, getting the Italian flag inked on your forearm isn&rsquo;t proud, it&rsquo;s pathetic: go for the American flag, if you must. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">TWF\'s = Third World Feet </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">It\'s still warm enough to wear sandals on occasion and when you\'re flaunting some feet that resemble that of a troll, it\'s a turn-off to say the very least. Head over to the nail salon, sit in the back where no one can see you and get a pedicure. No harm, your feet are foul. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief </span></strong></span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-10-12 20:30:10','2011-12-09 06:47:37',3,'f9edd6c0e12bc40f_picture_22.xlarge.jpg','image/jpeg',19201,'2011-10-12 20:30:09',0,'2011-10-17 20:32:19',1,'fashion-forewarned-the-v-neck-other-faux-pas','Fashion Forewarned: The V-Neck & Other Faux Pas '),(106,'Betty White Still the Hottest Bitch on the Block','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">And she&rsquo;s not afraid to spit some lyrics to that effect. The Playa Formerly Known as <strong>Betty White</strong> drops a verse with Brit popper <strong>Luciana</strong> for <strong>Lifeline</strong>&lsquo;s incredibly entertaining commercial cum music video about being old and stuff&hellip;.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0.1pt 0in; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/betty-white-still-the-hottest-bitch-on-the-block/\">http://fashionindie.com/betty-white-still-the-hottest-bitch-on-the-block/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-12 20:35:16','2011-12-09 06:47:37',2,'screenshot-10_12_2011-11_59_22-am-210x116.png','image/png',50247,'2011-10-12 20:35:15',0,'2011-10-12 20:35:23',1,'betty-white-still-the-hottest-bitch-on-the-block','Betty White Still the Hottest Bitch on the Block'),(107,'CS Shout Out: Men That Are Stylish & Philanthropic ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\">Last night <strong>The Right To Play</strong> held a successful fundraising event in the UES. </span><span style=\"font-size: large;\">They\'re an amazing organization that seeks to improve the lives of disadvantaged children and bring about development, health and peace by way of sport and play.</span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"> You can read about their mission @ <a href=\"http://www.righttoplay.com/International/about-us/Pages/mission.aspx\">http://www.righttoplay.com/International/about-us/Pages/mission.aspx</a>.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The affair was swarming with present and former Olympians, professional athletes and a team of extremely good-looking catering staff. On a personal note, to the Mark Wahlberg look-a-like carrying the delicious eggplant hor d\'oeuvres: call me. But I digress... &nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Among the athletes that serve as Ambassadors for this noble cause was Dhani Jones, who had just retired from the NFL the evening before. Wasting no time, Mr. Jones lent his voice to the organization for the night and was rocking some seriously standout style in the process. Specifically, it was his festive bow tie that caught the eye among the slew of the tried and true black ties. When I asked about it he informed me that he founded and currently powers an organization called <strong>Bow Tie Cause</strong>, which boasts a cool collection of high-end bow ties that commemorate a wide selection of charitable organizations close to the former linebackers heart. Check them out (<a href=\"http://bowtiecause.org/\">http://bowtiecause.org/</a>), update your style and contribute to a good cause all at the same time.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Also in attendance was a handsome, twenty-something budding philanthropist who, although born and bred in Downtown NYC, currently resides in New Orleans, Louisiana. His glasses were so dope I couldn&rsquo;t help but approach with the weak opening line of &ldquo;can I try on your frames?&rdquo;. He humored me and in addition to being extremely cool, the glasses were also comfortable and didn&rsquo;t make me look like a dirty little hipster. Upon enquiring as to the designer I was informed that the glasses were apart of the <strong>Warby Parker Eyewear</strong> collection and that for every pair of eyeglasses sold the company delivers a pair to someone in need. See for yourself @ <a href=\"http://www.warbyparker.com/\">http://www.warbyparker.com/</a>: not only are the glasses stylish as hell; they&rsquo;re also only $95 (WTF?!). I&rsquo;ve feared the trip to the optometrist because the over-priced and bland selection of frames on the market today leave much to be desired and come at some truly outrageous prices. One should not have to mortgage their home to see straight and Warby Parker has you &ndash; and those in need- covered.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief </span></strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-10-13 19:26:16','2011-12-09 06:47:38',3,'peterb_driera4warbyparker.jpg','image/jpeg',70680,'2011-10-13 19:26:15',0,'2011-10-17 20:32:33',1,'cs-shout-out-men-that-are-stylish-philanthropic','CS Shout Out: Men That Are Stylish & Philanthropic '),(108,'HalloWEIRD: The Trick vs. The Treat  ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong></strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Trick</strong>, <em>noun</em>: (a) a broad term used to define a woman that is a tease and/or &ldquo;hoe&rdquo;; (b) a man that pays for sex. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I get it. Halloween is that one time of year when we can all dress like a slut and not be judged for it&hellip; but not really though. You&rsquo;re being judged: by other women but more importantly by the guys out there looking for a holiday pick-me-up. So, depending on your personal goals for the evening you should plan to adjust your costume accordingly. It isn&rsquo;t fair but it&rsquo;s the reality. If you dress like a Playboy &ldquo;cyber girl of the week&rdquo; wannabe, he&rsquo;ll aim for the hit n&rsquo; quit. Unless you are, in fact, looking to whore yourself out this year cover up a <em>little</em> and maybe even show some creativity in your guise. I&rsquo;m no prude and I firmly believe in playing up the ass(ets) but unfortunately we still live in a day and age where you will be asking for certain presumptions to be made about you should you forgo modesty on this highly overrated of &ldquo;holidays&rdquo;. So I dedicate this article to the ladies out there still engaged in the all-important Halloween costume selection process: avoid looking like the trick, take your standards up a notch and go as the treat. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">To any of you gentlemen reading, a quick note to begin and end: you are what you eat. That is all. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>You&rsquo;re presumed a trick if&hellip; </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Your costume came out of an all-in-one plastic bag, was purchased at a store for the over-18 set and is a </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">debauched version of one of&nbsp; the following uniforms: &nbsp;the policeman, French maid, fireman, girl-scout, sailor, soldier, border control agent&hellip; I could go on forever. </span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">That&rsquo;s been done way too many times before. The choice indicates that you aren&rsquo;t even trying to hide the fact that you want attention and you want said attention concentrated on your breast and buttock regions.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: right;\" align=\"right\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>You&rsquo;re actually a treat in a tricks costume if&hellip; </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The reason for donning that played out slut get-up has nothing to do with a desire for degradation or your attention seeking tendencies but rather the fact that you could care less about Halloween and simply did not plan ahead. So, at 7 pm the night of you ran to some pop-up theme store or Ricky&rsquo;s, waited in an obscenely long line and grabbed anything that was available in a size other than XS or XL. The only option left is the dirty little Bo Peep? Oh, well. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>You&rsquo;re presumed a treat if&hellip;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Despite the fact that you&rsquo;re hot enough to leave little to the imagination, you&rsquo;ve opted instead for the costume that is either of political/social relevance, extremely funny and/or unexpectedly clever.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: right;\" align=\"right\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>You&rsquo;re actually a trick in a treats costume if&hellip; </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">You spent way, way too much time and effort coming up with the concept. Anyone that has dedicated so much energy towards something as unimportant as a Halloween costume clearly wants&nbsp; -and probably needs- to get laid.&nbsp; And if the outfit was \"appropriate\" at the beginning of the night yet, somehow, conveniently depletes throughout the evening until you&rsquo;re left rocking straight lingerie, you fall into the trick category. At least your fellow tricks were straight-forward and just showed up with their intentions, and body parts, on display. You faked everyone out, yourself included. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>*</strong>In case you were curious, I\'m going as the anti-MILF: the \"I\'m Proud of My Honor Student\" t-shirt, mom jeans, fanny pack and scrunchie included. I thought it was funny and it\'ll make me look about as un-attractive as humanly possible. I\'m such a rebel. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">[<strong>Retraction</strong>: I\'m still going as the anti-MILF but I spent too much time thinking about my costume and I decided that instead I\'ll wear my \"My Kid Had Sex With Your Honor Student\" t-shirt, inappropriately tight jeans and too much make-up. That\'s the real anti-MILF: take note boys. However, the inconvenient truth is that this costume isn\'t really a costume for me but rather my look on occasion. Can you say wake-up call? I can... but I\'d rather not.]<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </span></strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-14 19:04:13','2012-01-09 21:17:03',5,'google-halloween-costume-11762-1257265444-8.jpg','image/jpeg',58595,'2011-10-14 19:04:12',0,'2012-01-09 21:17:03',1,'halloweird-the-trick-vs-the-treat','HalloWEIRD: The Trick vs. The Treat  '),(109,'Exclusive Interview: Babe Walker Talks Serious White Girl Problems','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Tweeting about anything from boyfriend issues to dramatic fashion malfunctions;&nbsp;<strong>Babe Walker</strong>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/#%21/whitegrlproblem\">White Girl Problems</a>&nbsp;is every girl&rsquo;s go-to guru on all of life&rsquo;s stressful questions. Thankfully FashionIndie got a one on one with Babe about everything any problemed white girl needs to know, especially all the info about her new internet venture-<a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/www.babewalker.com\"><strong><span style=\"color: blue; text-decoration: none;\">BabeWalker.com</span></strong></a>&nbsp;and all about the White Girl Problem memoir coming out in stores in January.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/exclusive-interview-babe-walker-talks-serious-white-girl-problems-3/\">http://fashionindie.com/exclusive-interview-babe-walker-talks-serious-white-girl-problems-3/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-14 20:44:18','2011-12-09 06:47:38',2,'whitegirlproblems-560x861-210x322.jpg','image/jpeg',20087,'2011-10-14 20:44:17',0,'2011-10-14 20:44:39',1,'exclusive-interview-babe-walker-talks-serious-white-girl-problems','Exclusive Interview: Babe Walker Talks Serious White Girl Problems'),(111,'I\'m Bringing Bitchy Back ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>I got 99 problems and they all bitches</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"> - Kid Cudi</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;m a fan of the word &ldquo;bitch&rdquo;. I think that while overused, there are occasions where someone is, in fact, being a bitch and no other word sums it up quite as definitively. However, I&rsquo;m not a fan of bitches and the girl on girl playa hating is needless, counterproductive and indicative of some deep-seeded issues with our gender at large. This whole &ldquo;proud to be a bitch&rdquo; non-sense confuses me as well. Since when is it cool to suck? I hear so many girls openly gush about being a so-called bitch and apparently for whatever reason all of us are supposed to be impressed. Well I, for one, am not. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;m blessed with some of the finest (in more ways than one) female friends available on the market but I can probably count on two hands the amount of girls with which I share a genuine and loyal friendship. I&rsquo;m a skilled listener who is more-or-less agreeable and always up for some quality female bonding so something isn&rsquo;t computing here. And I&rsquo;m not alone: many women I know complain that a BFF is hard to find and that guys are, on the whole, far easier to befriend. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">And <strong>bitches are to blame</strong> for this. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I had a recent run-in with one of these dastardly creatures. She was someone who I didn&rsquo;t know very well but had apparently spoken to on one occasion&hellip; at around 4 am. For the record: if I haven&rsquo;t held a coherent, semi-intelligent conversation with you sober(ish), we don&rsquo;t know each other&hellip; sorry. Anyway, she was making it clear that she wasn&rsquo;t a fan of mine and communicated this with shameless disregard, as I was well within earshot. I could honestly care less. She doesn&rsquo;t know me, I don&rsquo;t know her and she&rsquo;s probably jealous for some unknown reason- that or this was all over a guy somehow, which is generally the case. I&rsquo;m still a kid in some cultures so why, grown ass woman, do you care enough about me &ndash;someone you don&rsquo;t know- to stir up trouble? Her display was not only straight whack but also more than a little pathetic. She&rsquo;s lucky that I wasn\'t raised to throw hooks, although I must warn that my left is solid: better recognize, bitch. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Girls, we need to stop hating on each other. The world can be&nbsp; an un-forgiving place and the last thing any of us need is yet another person dead set on cutting us down, making us feel even worse than we, likely, already do. And it&rsquo;s even more distressing when the perpetrator is one of our own. If you&rsquo;re not going to chill out with the conniving tendencies and defamatory remarks towards your fellow woman for the sake of feminism than perhaps this will encourage a change in your behavior: guys find this bullshit incredibly un-attractive.&nbsp; Now do I have your attention? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">When you&rsquo;re talking smack about another female, unless she ran over you with her car, went down on your boyfriend or called you fat you&rsquo;re making yourself look like a total d-bag. And guys are taking mental note of this. If you can back stab one of your own with such ease and with such seeming pleasure (many girls <em>do</em> get off on gossip), they will begin to wonder what you&rsquo;re going to say about them should anything ever go down. Take a look at the standard male entourage: not only do they keep each other&rsquo;s business on the DL but even during times when they aren&rsquo;t getting along there is no shit talking&hellip; at least not in a public setting and for personal attention. Basically, when you make yourself seem petty and fake by lamenting about something stupid some other chick said, did or was wearing what he hears is that he can&rsquo;t trust you and without trust you basically have nothing&hellip; it&rsquo;s hard out there for a bitch. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">It&rsquo;s time to reclaim the word. Spread it. If a girl is acting up, call it like you see it. Ladies, we all know when we&rsquo;re crossing the line and if/when you do, you&rsquo;re being a bitch and not in a good way&hellip; as if there was such a thing. If you like some chick&rsquo;s outfit, instead of being envious ask her where she got it. If she&rsquo;s dating your sloppy seconds take solace in the fact that you got to the prize first, even if he was the one who ended things. And if he was the one to 86 the involvement hating her isn&rsquo;t going to make him want you back. In fact he&rsquo;s probably getting a nice ego stroke out of seeing you get worked up over it so don\'t give him that satisfaction. And stop telling everyone and their mom about that time you saw (insert girls name) get drunk and wall out. Unless you&rsquo;re perfect and never had a sip of alcohol before (lame), there&rsquo;s no way in hell you&rsquo;ve never embarrassed yourself while under the influence on at least one previous occasion. Stop being such a hypocrite, start acting like a lady and see how much more enjoyable life is when your feeling of self-worth doesn&rsquo;t require cutting other women down. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong><br /></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-15 21:00:27','2012-01-09 21:16:41',5,'bitchplease.jpg','image/jpeg',16349,'2011-10-15 21:01:39',0,'2012-01-09 21:16:41',1,'im-bringing-bitchy-back','I\'m Bringing Bitchy Back '),(112,'The Ex-Files: A Short Catalogue of Cool & the Men I\'m Forced to Accredit','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">They say that all is fair in love and war. And I&rsquo;m not one to argue. So, to be fair I&rsquo;ve compiled a list of cool stuff that people I&rsquo;ve dated<strong>*</strong> in the past have exposed me to. Every individual I&rsquo;ve been with has taught me things and expanded horizons that would have otherwise remained un-explored. This should be the case for everyone unless, of course, you just have really bad taste in people. They also say that there&rsquo;s nothing in life as tragic as a missed opportunity. And with that I&rsquo;d never argue. Despite the fact that none of the men from my past have stuck in any permanent manner (i.e. live-in arrangement and beyond), their moments of good taste are truly all the permanence I need. So, I guess that&rsquo;s the point of dating.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;d like to emphasize the fact that this list is in no particular order of importance. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Zac Brown Band</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;ve seen them live and they&rsquo;re nothing short of legit. A lot of people, especially in New York, love to hate on country music. While I will agree that a good country song is not exactly a dime a dozen (it&rsquo;s just that kind of genre), quality country is just that: quality. The Zac Brown Band hails from Georgia and the musical and lyrical talent is remarkable, which is made explicit by both the live and recorded sound. Zac Brown&rsquo;s voice is probably one of my favorites at present time. It&rsquo;s so good I could listen to his <em>live</em> vocals whilst hungover&hellip;. In my opinion that means a lot. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">One of my personal favorites:<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZD_H5KfbaM\"> http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZD_H5KfbaM</a><strong></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Prepstar** Fashion (Although I Don&rsquo;t Personally Subscribe) </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Alright. You got me. Preppy fashion is hot. If pulled off correctly, what results just works&hellip; on me at least. I will reiterate that it must be executed in the proper fashion (no pun intended), as this certain style has a tendency to be overdone. I don&rsquo;t need to see pastels, strange little animal embroideries or any monogramming (necessarily) but it&rsquo;s a clean-cut, ultra masculine way to dress oneself. So, I&rsquo;m a fan. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Self-Respect &amp; Discretion (2-For-1 Special)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Is it bad that a man taught me these things? No. As long as someone did, it really doesn&rsquo;t matter. Nor does it make me, or any other woman, anti-feminist to admit that an experience with a dude was actually enlightening and good for the health.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>The Surf Lodge- Montauk, NY </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Located right on a body of water, this hot spot boasts a large outdoor bar/chilling area, film screening space and the food is pretty good. Not to mention the fact that it&rsquo;s in Montauk, which is, hands down, one of the most beautiful parts of this incredible country of ours. I&rsquo;ve only been on a few occasions but every single time I go it&rsquo;s simply a pimpin&rsquo; good time. My first experience Iincluded an awesome live reggae band, a sunset that was absolutely arresting and about two glasses of mid-range red wine: clearly, the lodge made a good initial impression. And clearly, the guy who took me had a good time as well that night&hellip; as he should have, because he more than deserved it. Not many nights are <em>that</em> perfect. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><em>Entourage</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;ve heard people refer to this show as the man&rsquo;s version of <em>Sex and the City</em>. I respectfully disagree because the two shows are not comparable and this one is better. Like, significantly so. While I have been known to watch an episode or two of SATC, the humor, character development, dialogue and celebrity cameo&rsquo;s throughout each season of <em>Entourage</em> is top-notch. Once again, well done HBO. Showtime, I love you too. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>*</strong>Let&rsquo;s just say I use the term &ldquo;dating&rdquo; in a broad sense. Not too broad, but my usage of the word is one of the most liberal things about me. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>**</strong>For a thorough definition of &ldquo;Prepstar&rdquo; kindly refer to the article under Style Girlfriend entitled &ldquo;<strong>Be The Sack&hellip; She&rsquo;ll Come To You</strong>&rdquo;. It sums it up quite nicely&hellip; if I may say so myself. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-16 10:41:43','2012-01-09 21:16:19',5,'282185_10100526622965159_828624_58884235_505375_a.jpg','image/jpeg',14696,'2011-10-16 11:06:34',0,'2012-01-09 21:16:19',1,'the-ex-files-a-short-catalogue-of-cool-the-men-im-forced-to-accredit','The Ex-Files: A Short Catalogue of Cool & the Men I\'m Forced to Accredit'),(113,'You Dont Get Fit With Fads','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Diets are number one as far as the first thing that people think of doing when they are looking to lose pounds. The big thing wrong with a diet is you usually gain back any weight that you lost&nbsp;once you come off the diet! The solution is to practice balanced eating habits so your body loses fat and keeps muscle for the long term.<br /> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The Second most common weight loss fad, Cleanses, or &ldquo;detox systems&rdquo;, can be the worst because they primarily load your body with chemicals that make you piss and shit so much that you lose weight by losing fluids&hellip; are you shitting me (no pun intended)?!! You&rsquo;re not losing anything but water weight. And you&rsquo;ll cause your metabolism to crash resulting in weight gain! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">And of course the devices, like the infamous shake weight. Or the various so-called abdominal dream machines that swear they are the ultimate quick fix! Don\'t get me wrong, it\'ll do a little something for you, especially if you hadn\'t been doing shit to start with but it won\'t get you jacked like the dudes and hot girls in the ads! </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Written by Super Trainer Rick</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Edited by a.g, Editor-in-chief </span></strong><br /></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-10-16 17:55:29','2011-12-09 06:47:38',4,'burger.jpg','image/jpeg',1566867,'2011-10-16 17:55:23',0,'2011-10-17 20:25:09',1,'you-dont-get-fit-with-fads','You Dont Get Fit With Fads'),(114,'Lets Heel It for the Boys','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">High heels: they&rsquo;re not just for women, drag queens and the oft-misunderstood transvestite anymore. <em>The New York Times</em>&nbsp;&rdquo;Style&rdquo; section, the only news source of any import, chronicles a trend sweeping the nation &mdash; or at least a trend lightly dusting Los Angeles: the gentleman stiletto.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/lets-heel-it-for-the-boys/\">http://fashionindie.com/lets-heel-it-for-the-boys</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-17 20:50:58','2011-12-09 06:47:38',2,'16heels-popup.jpg','image/jpeg',52414,'2011-10-17 20:52:13',0,'2011-10-17 20:52:36',1,'lets-heel-it-for-the-boys','Lets Heel It for the Boys'),(115,'Beatles Biopic to Star Johnny Depp?','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Wait.. hold up, Beatles biopic?? Yes, please! It is frightfully true that there have been few cinematic tales of <strong>The Beatles</strong>, and even fewer with any commercial acclaim. <em>Across the Universe</em> was visually stunning, and box office friendly, but it did not tell the story of the Fab Four. <em>Nowhere Boy</em>, the young John Lennon story,&nbsp;got buzz in the Beatle world back in 2009, but no real ticket traction. However, the currently in-the-works film, <em><strong>The Longest Cocktail Party</strong></em>&nbsp;would cover the recording of <strong>Let It Be</strong> and the creation of <strong>Apple Records</strong>. With <strong>Johnny Depp </strong>in the works, you could call it a Beatles <em>bi-epic</em>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/beatles-biopic-to-star-johnny-depp/\">http://fashionindie.com/beatles-biopic-to-star-johnny-depp/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-17 20:54:53','2011-12-09 06:47:38',2,'johnny-depp-and-beatles-210x200-1.jpg','image/jpeg',14531,'2011-10-17 20:54:53',0,'2011-10-17 20:55:08',1,'beatles-biopic-to-star-johnny-depp','Beatles Biopic to Star Johnny Depp?'),(116,'Consistency, Consistency, Consistency ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">The first thing we notice when we find someone attractive is subjective. I mean, some guys&nbsp;are ass guys, others prefer the boobs&hellip; one thing is for certain; we all love or can appreciate a nice toned body! Getting that body isn\'t always an easy thing but one thing is for&nbsp;certain and that is it takes consistency to make that change. What usually happens when people start to get \"serious\" is they see a change and start reaping the benefits. Like looser fitting jeans because you&rsquo;ve lost a few pounds or tighter fighting t-shirts because you&rsquo;re gaining muscle!! Your friends and co-workers give you a few compliments and then the old &ldquo;I don\'t have time to work out&rdquo; excuses start popping up again! THESE ARE NOT BAD THINGS!! THEY DO -AND WILL- HAPPEN! But don\'t be lulled into complacency by a few &ldquo;you\'ve got a&nbsp;beautiful ass!&rdquo; or &ldquo;man your arms are looking awesome, bro!&rdquo; comments. Stay on course and keep changing your body. Realize that there will be interruptions but you know in the back of your mind that you will be back on point tomorrow...WITH NO EXCUSES!!</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Written by Super Trainer Rick</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: small;\"><strong>Edited by a.g, Editor-in-chief </strong></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-10-17 20:57:08','2011-12-09 06:47:38',4,'screen-shot-2011-07-30-at-11.59.32-am-1.png','image/png',35207,'2011-10-17 20:57:08',0,'2011-10-17 20:57:11',1,'consistency-consistency-consistency','Consistency, Consistency, Consistency '),(122,'Can You Hear Me Now?','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I\'m walking down the street with a friend when a deep baritone informs me, \"You know, you\'ve got great posture.\"</span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"> Tall, dark, handsome and one shredded bod under a grey henley tee-shirt. Sure, if you say so: I have great posture and anything else you want me to have.</span><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">After a couple minutes of curbside chatting, dude has my number stored. I am stoked to hear from him.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Days later (the standard 72-hour waiting period, topic for another blog post), a text comes in: \"Hey, its the guy from the street by union square subwy.we met on sat. wd love 2 c u for a drink.\" [sic] </span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Sigh. What a disappointment. Message deleted. It was as though our encounter never happened.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Why\'d I do that? Wasn\'t I curious?&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Was I nuts?&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family: arial,sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Didn\'t I just want to have a drink before showing him the ceiling of my apartment?&nbsp;He was hot. He was on the cusp of charming.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">No.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">He told me everything about himself in that one stupid decision to text rather than call.&nbsp;He showed me he was a loser who really didn\'t want to try all that hard&mdash;and if he wasn\'t working for me now, would he later, like, during the ceiling inspection, or as a boyfriend? Probably not.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Observing and analyzing the successful and pathetic strategies of courtship in my own experiences and those of my friends, here\'s a summary and free advice:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">Real (and really interested) men call.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">They don\'t (or rarely, we\'ll get to that) text.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Texting is for wimpy little boys.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Texting is for wimpy little boys who don\'t want to make an effort.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">To riff the adage, the medium truly IS the message.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">It\'s not difficult: when you take a number, you should use it to phone the girl, not stimulate your thumb pads.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">How much work is it to call? How nerve-fraying can it possibly be?</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"> Let\'s break it down from my (the girl\'s) side of the smartphone: I don\'t know you, or know you all too well. I\'m not 15-years old and therefore no longer have the time or inclination to yap with you for hours on end. In full disclosure, I\'m kind of way nervous talk to you, also. Be assured that my goal is your goal. It is&nbsp;to keep you on the line just long enough to have you execute three easy steps to see me:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">1. Say hi and state your name (you come off as an arrogant prick when you start running your mouth before introducing yourself),&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">2. Bullshit me for maybe three minutes about nothing and say how cute you think I am, and</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">3. Ask me when I am free so we can go out.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">Simple, right? Six minutes of your life up in smoke and you\'ve got a date.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">Natch, there are concessions to texting.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The Lord invented SMS to share data points. Don\'t think too hard, but it\'s 160 characters for a reason. \"Here early. At bar waiting for you,\" and \"Have movie tix\" are perfect examples. (Send me an emoticon and I will punch your face.) But if you are trying to pitch the woo because you like me and want to see where this can go, or simply would like to pull down my panties and want to charm me to make it happen, effort. Yes, it\'s a verb, too.</span></div>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">So call me. Be a man. Nut up. Be sexy. I promise that if you get my voice mail, I will phone you back. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"text-align: justify; font-family: \'trebuchet ms\', geneva; font-size: large;\">e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she is so over the cupcake craze.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','tipsandtricks','2011-10-18 23:31:21','2011-12-13 03:28:25',7,'screen-shot-2011-10-18-at-7.31.03-pm.png','image/png',83311,'2011-10-18 23:31:20',0,'2011-12-13 03:28:25',1,'can-you-hear-me-now','Can You Hear Me Now?'),(123,'American History (Rated) X: The Real Stimulus Packages ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Turn on the news and the catchphrase(s) of late have been &ldquo;stimulus package&rdquo; this and &ldquo;bailout&rdquo; that. Well, as far as I can tell the only truly successful stimulus packages have been those that personally belong to a select few of our Nation&rsquo;s very own Commander&rsquo;s in Chief. So enjoy this short list of stimulating President&rsquo;s and their (likely) stimulating packages: &ldquo;history lesson&rdquo; included free of charge. <strong>God bless America</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>5. George H.W. Bush </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">With deficits left over from the Reagan administration, Bush Sr. found himself between a rock and a hard place in that Republicans firmly supported curbing the deficit by cutting down on government spending while the Democratic controlled Congress sought instead to raise taxes. Bush relented and gave in to Congress, which sparked a series of unfortunate events in which he would continually bend to the Democratic will. Unemployment, poverty and welfare programs increased and the United States even experienced a &ldquo;mild&rdquo; recession, lasting around six months (those were the days): guess we should have curbed government spending. In any event, the original Bush was handsome as a younger man. While <strong>a bit of a little bitch as President</strong>, as a college athlete and member of an American royal family I doubt he had any issues getting laid back in the day. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">The Athletic Bush Senior: <a href=\"http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2007/baseball/more/06/14/bush.cws.ap/\">http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2007/baseball/more/06/14/bush.cws.ap/</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>4. Barack H. Obama </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Needless to say, President Obama&rsquo;s economic policies have been less than successful. At best misguided attempts at reparation, the American economy is now in a full-blown recession and the unemployment rate is at an all-time high: not exactly the change that the people, or the audacious President himself, had hoped for. Although seeking an increase in corporate governance and labor rights, in addition to a higher minimum wage, the American &ndash;and world, for that matter- economy has since collapsed, the ramifications of which we are all experiencing now. <strong>While it&rsquo;s neither fair nor is it accurate to place the entire blame on the current President, the only stimulus package that seems to have any vigor is the one that Mrs. Obama enjoys</strong>. Michelle, you&rsquo;re a lucky woman. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Well, ALOHA: <a href=\"http://www.reobama.com/Obama_Hawaii_American_Grandparents.jpg\">http://www.reobama.com/Obama_Hawaii_American_Grandparents.jpg</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>3. Franklin Pierce</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Franklin Pierce, the 14<sup>th</sup> American leader, was a relatively unknown, largely insignificant President who was -not to mention- incredibly un-popular during his reign supreme. However, he looks like a quasi-Johnny Depp character and for that I have no choice other than to pay homage. Many of his major decisions as President were both divisive and highly criticized, earning him the <strong>reputation as one of the Nation&rsquo;s worst Commander&rsquo;s in Chief</strong>. These unfavorable Presidential determinations include favoring the Missouri Compromise and effectively repealing the Kansas-Nebraska act, which continued the debate over slavery in the west. Not to mention the Ostend Manifesto, which was drafted as a proposal to purchase Cuba from Spain and to declare war on the European Nation should they refuse. He basically hammered the last nail in his reputations coffin when he came out in support of the Confederacy during the American Civil War: dude was from New Hampshire. While I respect the boldness, Mr. Pierce, that was &ndash;for lack of a better word- stupid (politically and morally, obviously). But the fact remains that <strong>President Pierce was a fine looking post-Colonial</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Pierce and his beloved head of hair: <a href=\"http://www.mindspring.com/%7Edbholzel/pierce/pierce.html\">http://www.mindspring.com/~dbholzel/pierce/pierce.html</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>2. George W. Bush </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">His administration was characterized by tax cuts, two wars and a free-market approach that intended to lessen the role of government in the private business sector. An advocate for ownership, he believed strongly in personal accountability, smaller government and the obtaining of property. Bush\'s fiscal legacy is one of a worsening mortgage crisis and massive government interventions that came in the form of the infamous \"bailout\" (I\'m&nbsp; not only referring to the financial institutions but also <strong>Fannie and Freddie</strong>). Additonally, the United States Armed Forces were fighting wars in both Afghanistan and Iraq- wars that, as we all know, continue today. The above-metioned plus the controversial Bush tax cuts made for a rise in the National debt. Although extremely un-popular, the fact remains that W. was good-looking back in his heyday. Not gonna lie&hellip; I would have dated him. He was a graduate of Yale University (like his daddy) and one thing is for certain: Mr. President knew how to party. <strong>Whether you jumped on the anti-Bush bandwagon or not you have to admit that he was eye-catching in his earlier years</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Bush the cute college coed:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><a href=\"http://images.library.yale.edu/madid/oneItem.aspx?id=1771848&amp;q=&amp;q1=0684&amp;q2=&amp;qc1=contains&amp;qc2=&amp;qf1=subject1&amp;qf2=&amp;qn=&amp;qo=&amp;qm=15&amp;qs=136&amp;sid=&amp;qx=1004.1\">http://images.library.yale.edu/madid/oneItem.aspx?id=1771848&amp;q=&amp;q1=0684&amp;q2=&amp;qc1=contains&amp;qc2=&amp;qf1=subject1&amp;qf2=&amp;qn=&amp;qo=&amp;qm=15&amp;qs=136&amp;sid=&amp;qx=1004.1</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>1. John F. Kennedy (see photo above)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">This top-honors designation should come as no surprise whatsoever. Upon being sworn into Presidency, JFK sought to loosen fiscal policy, lower interest rates and encourage the growth of the American economy. The Eisenhower administration left him with a steadily declining GDP and a steadily increasing un-employment rate, yet in his short duration as President the economy experienced an incitement of note. However, the stock market was not quite as healthy and the Kennedy administration&rsquo;s punitive actions against the steel industry can be said to have encouraged this decline. Whether you&rsquo;re a fan of Kennedy&rsquo;s economic policies or not, he was an ostensible heartbreaker, although actually a <strong>bona fide beauty of a man- on the outside as well as the in</strong>. Meeting an untimely death as a result of a successful assassination attempt, he will forever remain one of America&rsquo;s most beloved political and social figures. From his celebrated marriage to Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis to his well-recorded affair with the legendary Marilyn Monroe, it is <strong>entirely logical that some of the world&rsquo;s most eligible bachelorettes wanted a piece of that</strong> Presidential smoke show. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Honorable Mentions: </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Abraham Lincoln</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Dude abolished slavery... and never told a lie. Bringing the beginning of the end to the systemic degradation of African American\'s aside, his nickname was \"honest\" Abe. A man that doesn\'t lie is about as rare as a perfect 10 that isn\'t dumb as sin. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">William J. \"Bill\" Clinton</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Not my style but he did play the sax, which means he knows how to use his mouth. Ask any White House intern that served beteween \'93-\'01... and Hillary of course. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong><br /></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-19 01:36:26','2012-01-09 21:15:57',5,'the-jfk-mystique-1.png','image/png',287652,'2011-10-19 01:36:25',0,'2012-01-09 21:15:57',1,'american-history-rated-x-the-real-stimulus-packages','American History (Rated) X: The Real Stimulus Packages '),(124,'Stewart Heywood','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Stewart Heywood just moved to NYC from Canada, \'eh\'. He is a skateboarding, Vans wearing icon of Montreal pop culture who studied at UCLA film school.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Stewart made the move to New York \'to make a movie inspired by his life in NYC and the people I&rsquo;ve met since coming here\'.</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium;\">As he explains it, the challenges of feeding himself, finding a job, keeping a girlfriend and trying to cross the streets during \'Occupy Wal Streets\' are sometimes overwhelming.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium;\">Some of his favorite spots in NYC to date are: 1) The Top of the Brooklyn Bridge, 2) Stone Street, 3) Northern Central Park 4) Beer Specials at Maxwells 5) Schillers liquor bar 6) Watching awkward first dates.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">With his camera, quit whit and interactive experience he hopes to show the world, NYC through the view of his eyes.&nbsp;</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium;\">You can visit his Facebook Page at Made in New York Movie.</span></p>\r\n<div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; color: #333333; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 15px; font-size: medium;\"><br /></span></div>','localcelebrity','2011-10-19 12:59:19','2011-12-09 06:47:38',9,'screen-shot-2011-10-19-at-8.52.28-am.png','image/png',405713,'2011-10-19 12:59:18',0,'2011-10-19 13:01:35',1,'stewart-heywood','Stewart Heywood'),(125,'1990\'s Revival','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Last week I ventured into the great unknown (New Jersey) because&nbsp;<strong>Filter</strong>,<strong>Chevelle&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong>Bush</strong>&nbsp;were playing at the&nbsp;<strong>Wellmont Theater</strong>, which -to those city-centric folk out there-&nbsp;is a relatively unknown&nbsp; yet amazing venue in the quaint town of Montclair.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;\">Basically the 90\'s called and they wanted their bands back...</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The show was incredible and each band &ndash;with sounds that ranged from quasi-metal to post-grunge grunge- brought their all like it was Woodstock &rsquo;99. The crowd surfing, dry humping, marijuana clouds&nbsp; and hilarious attempts at a mosh pit made the experience all the more entertaining. Not to mention the fact that despite being well into his forties, Gavin Rossdale is still a bona fide hottie on the loose. Now there\'s a DILF if I\'ve ever seen one. Gwen, you\'re a lucky woman.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">For the first time in a while I was among the youngest in attendance, as the majority of the crowd were the older, more established fans of these bands of yore -and their styles reflected this. 90&rsquo; style doesn&rsquo;t get enough play in my humble opinion and I for one enjoyed the flannel shirts, pullover baseball jerseys and Adidas trainers. Men that pay homage to this particular decade dress with an &ldquo;anything goes&rdquo; frame of mind, which is a refreshing change to the overly thought out, complicated and slightly effeminate look that is pervasive today.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Final verdict</strong>: Men of the 90&rsquo;s look pretty fly&hellip; for white guys.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">*I&rsquo;d like to point out that Timberland boots, gold-chains and Members Only jackets are on my 90&rsquo;s shit list. Sorry, just not a fan.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">On the off chance that you don&rsquo;t know the bands, here&rsquo;s a&nbsp;<strong>playlist</strong>&nbsp;of some personal favorites. All three bands, by the way, have recent albums out that are top-notch and deserve the attention of all, even those of us that were still in Oshkosh and wearing shoes that light up when these bands were in their heyday. Please Enjoy...&nbsp;<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Hey Man, Nice Shot</em>&nbsp;by Filter</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpWlatljaI0\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bpWlatljaI0</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Vitamin R (Leading Us Along)</em>&nbsp;by Chevelle</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XEH7fw298CM\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XEH7fw298CM</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Machinehead</em>&nbsp;by Bush</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zjgdhr5fRUA\">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zjgdhr5fRUA</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Written by a.g, Editor-in-chief</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Photo courtesy of b.b-rian&nbsp;</strong></span></p>','music','2011-10-19 13:05:57','2011-12-09 06:47:38',6,'screen-shot-2011-10-19-at-9.04.38-am.png','image/png',122131,'2011-10-19 13:05:56',0,'2011-10-19 13:11:28',1,'1990s-revival','1990\'s Revival'),(126,'Lindsay Lohan Has To Mop Up Blood or Go To Jail','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Another day, another jail sentence for Miss Lindsay Lohan (insert unshocked face and continue to sip your coffee without pause). In LA this morning, prosecutors will be telling a supposedly no-nonsense judge that Lohan was kicked out of a women&rsquo;s center where she was supposed to complete her Red Cross community service based probation. &nbsp;A super peeved off judge immediately yanked her off of Red Cross duty and assigned her last 120 hours to <strong>morgue duty.</strong>&nbsp;That&rsquo;s right, the morgue, where&nbsp;Lilo will be mopping up blood and cleaning up well, dead people&rsquo;s garbage. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/lindsay-lohan-has-to-mop-up-blood-or-go-to-jail/\">http://fashionindie.com/lindsay-lohan-has-to-mop-up-blood-or-go-to-jail/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-19 19:59:23','2011-10-23 12:29:44',2,'lindsay-lohan-angry.jpg','image/jpeg',24220,'2011-10-19 19:59:22',0,'2011-10-19 20:00:15',1,'lindsay-lohan-has-to-mop-up-blood-or-go-to-jail','Lindsay Lohan Has To Mop Up Blood or Go To Jail'),(127,' Brazilian Slum Pulls Itself Up By Flip-Flop Strap','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">While we&rsquo;ve been busy handing out <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/and-the-naomi-goes-to-fashionindies-1st-annual-model-citizen-awards/\">Model Citizen Awards</a>, we found a real live model citizen in the rough slums of Brazil.&nbsp;One tough bid, <strong>Silvinha Oliveira</strong>&nbsp;found her way out, worked her way through fashion school, turned away her nose up at the frivolity of high fashion&rsquo;s industry and, instead, brought it back to the <em>favelas</em>&nbsp;to flourish. Upon imparting her sartorial&nbsp;knowledge to a few women in the community, she was able to start her own company:&nbsp;<strong>Retalhos Cariocas</strong>. She takes scraps of factories&rsquo; leftover fabrics and uses them to transform the country&rsquo;s ubiquitous Havaianas into gladiators, booties, wrap shoes and more. All at once, Silvinha is giving fabric&nbsp;<em>and </em>her neighbors a second chance at life.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: large; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/brazilian-slum-pulls-itself-up-by-flip-flop-strap/\">http://fashionindie.com/brazilian-slum-pulls-itself-up-by-flip-flop-strap/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-20 19:29:39','2011-10-23 12:29:44',2,'gladiadoras-retalhos-cariocas-210x157.jpg','image/jpeg',15384,'2011-10-20 19:29:39',0,'2011-10-20 19:29:48',1,'brazilian-slum-pulls-itself-up-by-flip-flop-strap',' Brazilian Slum Pulls Itself Up By Flip-Flop Strap'),(128,'I Can\'t Be The Only One Who... ','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks that certain <strong>jeggings aren&rsquo;t <em>that</em> bad</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; would rather be dumped than do the honors myself. <strong>Dumpers remorse is a bitch</strong> and can make you believe that breaking things off was a lapse in judgment&hellip; even when it wasn&rsquo;t. At least when you&rsquo;re dumped, you have no other choice than to move on. Plus everyone feels way sorrier for you.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; ranks missionary in my personal <strong>top 5 positions</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks that <em>some</em> of my 4 am texts are <strong>moments of literary genius,</strong> even the next day. But most are unfortunate. I\'ve sent some real doozies in my time. It\'s just that sometimes, especially when substances are involved, certain things (apparently) just need to be put out into the universe. Would I prefer that texts such as \"Hey jerk off, are you still up? I want to jerk you off\" not be out there for all to see? Well, yeah but at the end of the day it is kind of funny. My sense of humor ends at my drunk facebooking, though. There was a really bad incident back in 2010. Let\'s just say a certain status of mine went on about how an ex-boyfriend had green eyes that were mesmerizing and a touch that \"made me weak\", his name tagged in it and everything... I\'d really rather not talk about it. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; has kissed a girl and has liked it: <strong>almost as much</strong> as kissing boy.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; get&rsquo;s turned on when <strong>other girl&rsquo;s </strong>hit on the man I&rsquo;m with. But there is some fine print: this is only the case if I\'m secure in the relationship. If not, seeing other girls make their move makes me want to put eyedrops in their beverage and watch nature take its course. But, for whatever reason, in either scenario it still makes him appear more in demand, which is always a good thing for a partner to see. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; fears the future ramifications of my facebook actions. I <strong>thank God everyday</strong> that I didn&rsquo;t have it in high school.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; is a woman that <strong>loves the thrill of the chase</strong>. They do say that satisfaction is the death of desire, after all. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; wishes more than anything that I wasn&rsquo;t a woman that loves the thrill of the chase. What they meant to say was <strong>satisfaction is the death of <em>his </em>desire</strong>, after all. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks the new Jay-Z/Kanye album, <em>Otis</em>, is kind of <strong>overrated</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; finds neither Prince William nor Prince Harry even remotely sexually enticing. But if I absolutely had to pick one I&rsquo;d break my &ldquo;no gingers&rdquo; rule because not only is William balding but he seems boring as hell. Plus <strong>he&rsquo;s married and homie don&rsquo;t play that</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; is exponentially more likely to hook up the first two weeks post Brazilian wax. Sidenote: I have noticed an alarming trend, one in which people are actually hating on this particular waxing procedure. If you&rsquo;re lying there spread eagle waiting to have hair ripped out of the most sensitive region of your body &ndash;and, not to mention, paying way too much for it- you might as well get all of it removed. Trust me, it\'s worth having some little asian lady punish your nether regions for the Vietnam war because everything feels better when you\'re sans&nbsp; 70\'s playboy bush. <strong>It&rsquo;s bandwagon time</strong> and I&rsquo;ve been on it longer than I&rsquo;ve been sexually active... generational thing, I guess. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; get&rsquo;s aroused by the feeling of a man&rsquo;s breath on the back of my neck and his caresses on the back on my knees. But especially by the <strong>mere sight of him in basketball shorts</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; can more-or-less <strong>blame alcohol</strong> for approximately 90% of my regrets in life.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks that people who claim to have no regrets in life are annoying, and probably lying. Considering something to be a regret is not a &ldquo;negative, bad attitude&rdquo; thing: it&rsquo;s a <strong>smart and necessary thing</strong>. And do you honestly expect me to believe that you don\'t regret dating that guy who drunkenly took a shit in an alley and wiped with his sock (true anecdote)? Because I don\'t... <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; doesn&rsquo;t sleep completely sound <strong>unless there&rsquo;s a man</strong> (that I like) in the bed too. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; has determined that the <strong>opposite of love</strong> is not hate, it&rsquo;s <strong>indifference</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks it&rsquo;s kind of weird <strong>when a guy orders wine at a bar</strong> (unless it&rsquo;s a wine bar). Guys should drink beer or liquor... call me old fashioned, but a man throwing down a glass of pinot noir at a dive strikes me as odd.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; does feel more attractive in clothing that leaves <strong>a little</strong> to the imagination. But the most attractive in a bikini, hands down. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; feels that vibrators, while truly amazing, have actually caused women to know less about what gets them off. Unfortunately, no man is going to feel like a pocket rocket. However, incidentally, no pocket rocket is ever going to feel as good as a man. You <strong>have to use your hands</strong> in order to be able to help him out later on.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; has become too lazy to use the hand as opposed to the vibrator and is <strong>currently facing the consequences</strong>. Not only am I at a loss for how to get off manually these days, but the money spent weekly on AA\'s is ever-so-slightly shameful.&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; immediately looks for the Alpha male(s) in any new environment. They&rsquo;re the guys that stand out even when they&rsquo;re trying everything in their power to &ldquo;blend&rdquo;. Additionally, I have found that the Alpha males are, in general, the better looking ones&hellip; it&rsquo;s a <strong>no brainer</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; will never tell my kids that they should hold off on sex until marriage (not even my daughter, should I have one). Sex is a necessary obstacle in the relationship course. As is traveling together. But not comfortable, overly planned out, 5-star resort traveling. You <strong>want to know if your relationship can possibly withstand the institution of marriage?</strong> Go backpacking together for at least a month. Only then can you be sure because you don\'t know someone until you\'re in a third world country together with nothing but a backpack of belongings, a lonely planet guide and a serious case of dysentery. If you can make it work under those conditions, marriage should be manageable. <br /></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; has, honest to God, <strong>never cheated on a significant other</strong>. Go me. No really: I deserve to be proud of that because it can easily happen, whether you&rsquo;re a man or a woman. Even still, men cheat more.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; fears the <strong>loss of vaginal tightness</strong> as a result of childbirth way more than the pain of childbirth </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; never imagined what my wedding would be like when I was a little girl. I was too busy forcing my baby brother to perform *NSYNC songs for a live audience, <strong>crushing on Johnny Bravo, </strong>starting arbitrary \"clubs\" for the sole purpose of discluding other children and making Barbie and Ken sleep in the same doll bed naked to be concerned with such a matter. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; has used the <strong>online magic 8 ball</strong> to answer questions about my personal life.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; once got <strong>legitimately</strong> upset over an answer given by this so-called internet &ldquo;oracle&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; is open and honest about the fact that I <em>will</em> judge if a guy allows me to pay on the first date. I&rsquo;m not about using anyone and I\'ll&nbsp; certainly make an offer to contribute, but it&rsquo;s the first date&hellip; I <strong>don&rsquo;t even care if the whole thing was my idea</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; deems it necessary to reiterate to the men out there that if you want to have your cake and eat it too&hellip; then <strong>eat it</strong> too.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; has only looked through the phone of a guy that I was involved with on one occasion and felt so guilty about it&nbsp; that I swore I would never do it again, no matter how tempted or suspicious. But not because I&rsquo;m &ldquo;above it\", rather I&rsquo;m just acutely aware of my inability to be stealth in such situations. Basically, next time I&rsquo;m going to get caught... absolutely. And that sounds so embarrassing. Plus, karma is a bitch and you don&rsquo;t want him to do the same. Even if you&rsquo;re not hiding anything it&rsquo;s incredibly invasive. An ex looked through my phone once and the feeling is nothing short of unsettling. Just avoid doing it. Any evidence you find is evidence you can\'t really use because admitting that <strong>you stooped so low as to go through their phone</strong> is usually worse than whatever crime that they, allegedly, committed. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks the whole hot/cold game is entirely un-necessary. If I want to have sex with you, games are not needed. If I don&rsquo;t want to have sex with you, no amount of game playing is going to get you laid. I&rsquo;m easy&hellip; if I choose you. And trust me when I say that if we&rsquo;ve had sex, and you didn&rsquo;t shoplift the pooty, <strong>I chose you&hellip; not the other way around</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; moved from NYC to Westchester County and <strong>actually liked it</strong>. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; thinks that dimples on a man\'s face are two of the s<strong>exiest things on planet earth</strong>. And that dimples on a woman\'s lower back are a close second. &nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">&hellip; finds it funny when guys think that us women don&rsquo;t know when they&rsquo;re playing with our heads. Oh, we know. We just cant do anything about it because once we&rsquo;ve slept with you, un-controllable chemical reactions taking place in our brain somehow convince us to put up with your bullshit for much longer than we should. What you guys are enjoying is not the result of severe game on your part but rather a<strong> textbook biological advantage</strong>. But don&rsquo;t worry&hellip; things have an interesting way of evening out. Happy hunting, boys.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-25 08:25:28','2012-01-09 21:15:33',5,'324074-do_use_magic_8_ball_answer_questions.jpg','image/jpeg',44337,'2011-10-25 08:38:45',0,'2012-01-09 21:15:33',1,'httpwwwconnectingsexescomposti-cant-be-the-only-one-who','http://www.connectingsexes.com/post/I-Can\'t-Be-The-Only-One-Who...'),(129,'Words of Wisdom and Doddering Charm Courtesy of Iris Apfel','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Iris Apfel</strong> is a fashion icon. And she&rsquo;s 90 godddamn years old. Meaning that she can and will say whatever the hell she wants. In an amazing interview with<em> The Daily Telegraph</em>, Apfel gives her take on New York fashion, celebrity style and that time <strong>Lindsay Lohan</strong> asked her to be her Svengali. Hint: she said no.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Read more: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/words-of-wisdom-and-doddering-charm-courtesy-of-iris-apfel/\">http://fashionindie.com/words-of-wisdom-and-doddering-charm-courtesy-of-iris-apfel/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-10-25 10:56:06','2011-10-25 10:56:33',2,'iris3-210x315.jpg','image/jpeg',9201,'2011-10-25 10:56:06',0,'2011-10-25 10:56:33',1,'httpwwwconnectingsexescompostiris-apfel','http://www.connectingsexes.com/post/Iris-Apfel'),(130,'Ok, So Apparently Guys Dont Like These Things','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Girls who are too loud in bed</strong>. Apparently, they have neighbors. I blame porn, but fully recognize and appreciate the appeal of porn. It can be hot and when you\'re stuck in a London hotel with nothing to do (true story), it can be very handy -so to speak. I\'m not, however, into some of this crazy fetish stuff out there. But I&rsquo;m not one to judge&hellip; unless its kiddie. When you like watching kids in scenes that are nothing short of sexually explicious (now a real word), I judge. Hard. And if you actually <strong>have sex with children, I kind of stop caring about your rights.</strong> But that&rsquo;s just me.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Text messages</strong>. They like being able to send text messages themselves, as it&rsquo;s impersonal, efficient and allows avoidance should that be desired, but they do not particularly enjoy the ones we send. At least, not the rambling, interrogative and &ndash;truth be told- insignificant text novels that are sent in abundance. <strong>&nbsp;I have a problem with text messaging and I am not too proud to admit this.</strong> So, learn from my mistakes and never, and I mean never, send the follow up text. He got it, he is just either busy and/or ignoring you. Additionally, never text anything pertaining to your &ldquo;relationship&rdquo; that should, instead, be discussed in person. Once establishing this as the status quo, where important matters are handled via technology, intimacy is shot and arguments have a funny way of escalating. When you have to think about what you&rsquo;re going to say to their face, priorities and things of <em>actual</em> importance make themselves clearer.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Changing their facebook relationship status</strong>. And quite frankly, I agree. It sucks when you break up and make the dreaded switch from &ldquo;in a relationship&rdquo; to &ldquo;single&rdquo;, because there is bound to be a few &ldquo;friends&rdquo; that comment on it (with sympathy, regret and words of support that do nothing but make you feel worse) and even a few &ldquo;friends&rdquo; that &ldquo;like&rdquo; it. However, if the relationship is a longer-term one and your significant other tends to garner admiration from the opposite sex, it can be appropriate. <strong>But I think that if we all had to be honest, &ldquo;it&rsquo;s complicated&rdquo; is probably the more accurate status.</strong> Mine should read &ldquo;it&rsquo;s complicated&hellip; with myself&rdquo;. But instead, for now I&rsquo;m going with &ldquo;single&rdquo;&hellip; which is highly accurate as well.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong>Girls that are insecure about letting them go downtown</strong>. Yeah, I get that you like it and when she refuses it makes her appear like she&rsquo;s hiding something but unfortunately this insecurity can generally be blamed on the previous men she&rsquo;s dated. Not all dudes are like you. If you like wandering south, that puts you in a different category. Congrats. Your slacker fellow men are to blame for any inconvenient residual negatives that you may be dealing with. Vagina probably has an &ldquo;alternative&rdquo; smell, taste and or/texture. I can only imagine. Many &ldquo;men&rdquo; see giving oral as a special occasion and while I get that cunnilingus is more of a production than fellatio (I hate both of those words), the incredible discrepancy seen in many heterosexual couples can breed some insecurity. It&rsquo;s like one guy makes us feel as if there&rsquo;s something wrong down below and then the next guy gets mad that we don&rsquo;t feel 100% comfortable letting him put his entire face in that vicinity. Damned if we do, damned if we don&rsquo;t. <strong>Kind of how you boys feel when a girl you&rsquo;re involved with asks if you think her smoke show best friend is &ldquo;attractive&rdquo;. </strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong> </strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-10-27 08:55:56','2012-01-09 21:15:09',5,'cunnilingus.png','image/png',151812,'2011-10-27 08:55:54',0,'2012-01-09 21:15:09',1,'ok-so-apparently-guys-dont-like-these-things','ok...-so,-apparently-guys-don\'t-like-these- things '),(131,'Only the Lonely Text Back','<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Communication Breakdown II: Only the Lonely Text Back&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you read my last post, \"Communication Breakdown I: Can You Hear Me Now?\"&mdash;and if you didn\'t, you should&mdash;men phone, little boys text.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Likewise, women return a call with a call; little girls, with a text. Yes, some of us are total douches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Although I am sure some little boys return voice mails with texts, never in my experience has this happened. Amazing how 99% of dudes love to initiate texts, but get the whole quid pro quo thing. Props, gentlemen. You have permanent real estate in my heart.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But I digress.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A dear guy friend recently asked me for a pop-psych analysis of a girl he was super-excited about.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">\"I call. She doesn\'t pick up. I leave her a message. She sends me a text back. Why?!\" He was supremely annoyed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">From my friend\'s point of view, he liked this girl and was showing his keen, flattering interest by stepping it up&mdash;ye olde phone calls.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And in return, he exclusively received lousy, lame, step-down texts, which probably took her 15 minutes to script, complete with an emoticon.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Guess she was incapable of actually wording her feelings and thoughts&mdash;or maybe she couldn\'t be bothered&mdash;so sub in the appropriate little face.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Pathetic. Not cute. And definitely not (gag) authentic person-to-person communication, his goal.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My gut told me she was going to flake: texting back each and every time my friend left a message made her seem lazy, disinterested, arrogant, and signaled she was avoiding him. (And now I\'ll tell you what I didn\'t like about her habit.......)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Wake up, people: phoning in a day and age when an email is akin to a quill-and-ink-written love letter delivered by carrier pigeon indicates you are liked, and that your caller is trying for you. Why would you respond with anything less, if you aren\'t trying to say, \"I\'m not feeling you?\" (And if it is what you\'re trying to say, just say it.)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sure, I\'m all for smoke, mirrors, and aloof unavailability&mdash;do not pounce on your phone at the first ring, of course&mdash;but rudeness via \"my-text-to-your-phone-call\" is just tacky and no one wants to date that.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My intuition was correct. My friend is no longer calling his sad, sorry texter&mdash;whose swan song was delaying their date for a week before ultimately canceling not one hour before they were supposed to meet. For coffee. On a Sunday. In the afternoon. Her idea. \"I\'m sick. Call later? :-(\"&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">As if.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He is now happily dating the stand-up, phone-him-back women he deserves.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So girls (and boys guilty of the charge), if someone is doing the right thing and calling you, encourage and reward their effort. Be courteous; it\'s hot and distinguishes you from the lame losers who massage their touch-screens and Qwertys. Match the medium&mdash;if you must play a game, wait a few days&mdash;and phone back. It won\'t take long before your person of interest will push off if they\'re always trying, and you\'re not.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she wears four-inch heeled booties, and is therefore a sucker for a good foot massage.</span></strong></p>','tipsandtricks','2011-10-30 13:55:49','2011-12-13 03:27:51',7,'photo.jpg','image/jpeg',24734,'2011-10-30 13:55:49',0,'2011-12-13 03:27:51',1,'only-the-lonely-text-back','only-the-lonely-text-back'),(132,'Top 5 Interview Must Haves','<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Jon Mustich, CEO of www.evolutionofstyle.com, mission is to help men look (and feel!) better. He sent us his take on critical style elements for an interview. Jon can be seen on the beaches of Santa Monica and followed @evostyle.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You were called to come in for your dream job interview, now what? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Make sure you have these 5 basic items ready to go so you won\'t have to scramble the night before to get ready.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1. A clean pressed navy or charcoal colored suit. Black is for funeral\'s and formal events, so bring some color to the interview.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2. Solid white shirt that is pressed.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">3. Power Tie to complete the outfit, go with a plaid in either a light red or silver and blue to brighten up the outfit.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">4. A good pair of shoes that are polished. Make sure your belt matches the shoes as well.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">5. A simple leather portfolio case or briefcase to carry resumes, business cards, and notes.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-10-30 14:04:51','2011-10-30 14:13:46',3,'s2.jpg','image/jpeg',27469,'2011-10-30 14:04:50',0,'2011-10-30 14:13:46',1,'top-5-interview-must-haves','top-5-interview-must-haves'),(133,'Drink BEER. Look GREAT.','<div style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: #ffffff; margin: 8px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Do you like beer, well if so, take heed and enjoy the head on your favorite beer. It is now a proven fact that beer -- yes, BEER -- can provide the same&nbsp;<a id=\"itxthook0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrsta itxthook\" style=\"border-bottom: 0.075em solid darkgreen; font-weight: normal; font-size: 100%; text-decoration: underline; padding-bottom: 1px; color: darkgreen; background-color: transparent;\" href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/45_eating_well.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span id=\"itxthook0w0\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">health</span><span id=\"itxthook0w2\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrstspan itxthookspan\" style=\"background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; -moz-background-clip: border; -moz-background-origin: padding; -moz-background-inline-policy: continuous; font-weight: inherit; color: darkgreen;\">benefits</span></a>&nbsp;as&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/foodcourt/25_eating_well.html\">wine</a>. No matter what type of ale you prefer, studies show that drinking beer in moderation (up to 2 drinks a day for us guys) can and will reduce your chances of strokes, as well as heart and vascular disease.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It\'s called the&nbsp;<em>French Paradox</em>&nbsp;-- the link between the low rate of heart disease among the French and their fat-laden&nbsp;<a id=\"itxthook1\" class=\"itxtrst itxtrsta itxthook\" style=\"border-bot