I never get laid\"</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Barney: Jesus waited THREE days to come back to life. It was perfect! If he had only waited ONE day, a lot of people wouldn\'t have even heard he died. They\'d be all, \"Hey Jesus, what up?\" and Jesus would probably be like, \"What up? I DIED yesterday!\" and they\'d be all, \"Uhh, you look pretty alive to me, dude...\" and then Jesus would have to explain how he was resurrected, and how it was a miracle, and the dude\'d be like \"Uhh okay, whatever you say, bro...\" And he\'s not gonna come back on a SATURDAY. Everybody\'s busy, doing chores, workin\' the loom, trimmin\' the beard, NO. He waited the perfect number of days, THREE. Plus it\'s SUNDAY, so everyone\'s in church already, and they\'re all in there like \"Oh no, Jesus is DEAD\", and then BAM! He bursts in the back door, runnin\' up the aisle, everyone\'s totally psyched, and FYI, that\'s when he invented the high five. That\'s why we wait three days to call a woman, because that\'s how long Jesus wants us to wait.... True story.</span></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZkmheRE9zi4\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>','lifestyle','2011-11-06 15:19:19','2012-01-09 21:05:33',8,'screen-shot-2011-10-18-at-7.26.41-pm.png','image/png',141220,'2011-11-06 15:19:18',0,'2012-01-09 21:05:33',1,'lifestyle-3daysrule','lifestyle-3daysrule'),(147,'Limmie Terrell (Texan PHOTOG)','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We recently sat down with Limmie Terrell to find out why he is a \'Local Celebrity.\'</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: Where you from?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: Fort Worth, Texas Son!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: How long have you been in NYC?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: About 3 months. (Swigs Mr Daniels)&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: Why New York?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: My pony was getting restless. So one day, I saddled up with a duffle bag and my camera, kicked the spurs on my size 12 dogs and rode until the bright lights of NYC blinded me.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: How is the Big Apple treating you?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: Amazing. It has been a transformational experience of social amplification.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: What the fuck does that mean?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: Well, if James Dean was born and raised in TX he would have had my style. So I take the \'everything is bigger\' mantra and add some NYSizzle to it....I am rocking&nbsp;my first pair of skinny jeans, helped produce Fashion Week, call a handful of beautiful Aussie women my friends and have used my baritone voice and Texas swagger to rise above the top. It has been amazing.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: What inspires you?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: An ounce of home. Randomly hearing Jason Aldean blaring over the speakers at a bar</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: Okay LT, Why are you a Local Celebrity?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">LT: Well, on my first trip to NYC a stripper gave me the finger before a 300 lb. bouncer named Tiny booted me out.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS: Amazing</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Limmie can be found shooting beautiful women and stills all over NYC and can be friended at&nbsp;https://www.facebook.com/limmiet</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','localcelebrity','2011-11-06 15:45:05','2011-11-06 15:45:11',9,'187728_23929684_4355045_n.jpg','image/jpeg',11984,'2011-11-06 15:45:04',0,'2011-11-06 15:45:11',1,'localceleb-limmie','localceleb-limmie'),(148,'It not Personal. Its Just Pussy','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I&rsquo;m a life long guy&rsquo;s girl and I&rsquo;ve always had a healthy amount of male friends, only a few of which I&rsquo;ve slept with (go me). All of this quality male bonding has truly enlightened me and I&rsquo;ve come to a conclusion that I believe will be of benefit to both sexes. Ladies: when you make it clear to a guy friend that his only option is his left hand (not yours), don&rsquo;t get all bummed out when he doesn&rsquo;t want to hang out as much. You&rsquo;re still his friend, he still cares about you, but he needs to get laid. And since you&rsquo;ve removed your holiest of holes from the list of potentials he needs to switch gears and focus on another target.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Also, it is NOT fair to pretend to want to sleep with him after all when he starts to apply his attention elsewhere just for the sheer fun of it. If that&rsquo;s how you get your entertainment these days you are lame and you need to get a life. There&rsquo;s no reason why men and women can&rsquo;t get along but we need to meet each other halfway. So basically it goes like this: boy meets girl, boy befriends girl, boy makes move on girl, girl rejects boy saying &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t want to ruin our friendship&rdquo;, boy loses girl (and erection), boy finds girl 2.0, and the rest is history. Leave it at that. When a guy friend starts to branch out, just go with the flow- and depending on how good of a friend he is you might even consider enduring the rumor that the two of you drunkenly hooked up&hellip; the rumor he created of course. The male ego is delicate. That&rsquo;s just a fact.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-11-10 12:47:39','2012-01-09 21:14:58',5,'friends-with-benefits.jpg','image/jpeg',21530,'2011-11-10 14:05:04',0,'2012-01-09 21:14:58',1,'its-not-personal-its-just-pussy','its-not-personal-its-just-pussy'),(154,'Stand By Your Man... Sometimes ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Dating advice &ndash;and advice on men in general- from female friends should be taken with a grain of salt. They&rsquo;re women and, by no fault of their own, usually don&rsquo;t know what they&rsquo;re talking about. This includes me, so consider this my disclaimer: just because I choose to write about dating does not mean you should take all, if any, of my advice. I blog, therefore I am&hellip; most likely as clueless as anyone when it comes to the sex I wish to sex.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">I&rsquo;ve always found it funny how when I&rsquo;m single, many girlfriends express enthusiasm at the prospect of me becoming less than single. However, as soon as I couple up all conversations tend to come to the same conclusion: dump him. He doesn&rsquo;t &ldquo;deserve&rdquo; me and I can do &ldquo;better&rdquo; (allegedly). But, to quote the film <em>Clueless</em> (Amy Heckerling&rsquo;s epic coming of age tale that was both highly observant and socially relevant), &ldquo;If I&rsquo;m too good for him, how come I&rsquo;m not with him?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\">Sometimes, you should just stand by your man. Men are annoying as hell. They do, and say, some truly dumb shit. Putting their foot in their mouths is their favorite past time, and most &ndash;if not all- are extremely good at it. And let&rsquo;s be honest: women are no walks in the park either. But that&rsquo;s what keeps it interesting. Remember that <strong>there can be no spark with out tension</strong>. Obviously if he&rsquo;s &ldquo;abusive&rdquo;, truly a loser or the sex is bad then by all means&hellip; drop him like a bad habit. But if he misses his cue to feed you attention on occasion and doesn&rsquo;t heed to your every demand, this is not necessarily evidence of his inability to make you happy in the long run. It&rsquo;s just evidence that you&rsquo;re dating a man, a fellow human being independent to you, and that perhaps you may have to express your wants and needs verbally instead of banking on the fact that he&rsquo;s a mind reader. I&rsquo;ve dated a lot of guys but I&rsquo;m yet to experience a mind reader. And if a guy claimed to be a mind reader I&rsquo;d consider that flag to be red.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><strong><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></strong><br /></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-11-16 02:41:17','2012-01-09 21:14:46',5,'stand-by-your-man-clever-man-wynette-demotivational-posters-1311628812.jpg','image/jpeg',67028,'2011-11-16 02:41:17',0,'2012-01-09 21:14:46',1,'stand-by-your-man-sometimes','Stand By Your Man... Sometimes '),(155,'Tale Of Two \"Men\" ','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The following are two types of men, both of which are extremely misunderstood and ridden with dating potential. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">If you can honestly say that the guy you&rsquo;re dating falls into one, or both, categories then my advice is to stick it out, keep an eye on your investment and thank me later.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>The Good-Looking Semi-Douche </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Obviously, as is made explicit in the title he is an attractive guy. Other girls like to stare and this both arouses and infuriates you (a really healthy combo&hellip;. no, seriously). Because he&rsquo;s been a looker for some time, his looks are a part of his identity. Any good-looking individual that says otherwise is lying. In fact, appearance is a major part of an unattractive individuals identity as well. However, the masses only tend take issue with the hotties in the ranks. So yes, he acts like a douche on occasion and may seem narcissistic at times. But the key phrase is he acts <em>like</em> a douche, he isn&rsquo;t actually a douche. When he&rsquo;s mad at you and is trying to get a rise he may flirt with some dumb biddy in your presence. But because <strong>deep down he&rsquo;s a great guy that always seems to come through for you at times when you <em>actually</em> need him</strong>, it is likely that he is acutely aware of how unfulfilling that biddy probably is and his flirting will serve more as ignition for make-up sex with you and less as a means for post break-up sex with her&hellip; unless you&rsquo;re an idiot that can&rsquo;t see the glaring potential in a man that is good-hearted and good-looking. That doesn&rsquo;t happen often so if physical attraction and good character are things you&rsquo;re looking for in a partner, you&rsquo;re going to have to cut them slack at times. Trust me, they&rsquo;re doing the same for you.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>The Almost Alpha </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">We all know (and love) the alpha male. If you&rsquo;re more a fan of the beta, this does not pertain to you and nothing I ever say pertains to you because we disagree on a fundamental level. The Almost Alpha, however, is the guy that has been thrust into the role of alpha due to his God given charismatic personality and undeniable appeal to both men and women but still has some insecurity to work through (don&rsquo;t we all). Men, in general, have a lot of pressure placed upon them to be strong, confident and in 100% control of 100% of situations. And the alphas live up to these expectations day in and day out. If he&rsquo;s young, has a lot of baggage and/or has experienced the worst us women have to offer he is still getting comfortable with himself and can, therefore, falter as top dog on occasion. <strong>The key phrase there is <em>on occasion</em>.</strong> As in: if he&rsquo;s always failing to meet the alpha standard of manliness he is not an alpha in training, he&rsquo;s a wannabe showing some true colors.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva; font-size: large;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Written by a.g., special to connectingsexes.</strong></span><br /></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-11-16 02:49:36','2012-01-09 21:14:33',5,'samposter-1.jpg','image/jpeg',42667,'2011-11-16 02:49:35',0,'2012-01-09 21:14:33',1,'tale-of-two-men','Tale Of Two \"Men\" '),(157,'A Little Exercise Everyday','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Exercise should be a part of every day! So important to keeping our hearts strong and healthy! </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There are many ways to incorporate exercise into your daily routine and you might be surprised at how many calories one can burn. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If it\'s not a gym day for me, I still like to go for a brisk walk at some point in the day! Otherwise I work out at the gym for 50 minute<var></var>s 3-4 days a week. Worst case scenario, get on the floor and drive out some push-ups, do some free squat or shadow box! It is amazing how good you will feel!</span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-11-20 15:21:52','2011-11-20 15:22:38',4,'images.jpeg','image/jpeg',4595,'201