e; font-family: \'Droid Sans\', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: medium;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.evolutionofstyle.com/index.php/site/blog_details/450/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.evolutionofstyle.com/index.php/site/blog_details/450/</a></span></span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"color: #0000ee; font-family: \'Droid Sans\', Arial, sans-serif;\"><span><br /></span></span></div>\r\n<p><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. men in gingham make her weak in the knees; so make a note.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-12-05 03:32:46','2012-02-25 21:03:05',3,'gingham_stacked.jpg','image/jpeg',33072,'2011-12-05 03:32:46',0,'2012-02-25 21:03:05',1,'realmenweargingham','realmenweargingham'),(169,'Personal Climate Change: Recycling Sucks','<div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">I have two compartments in my dating life that get me into serious trouble.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Trash: Out of sight, out of mind. No offense, but really, what the hell was I thinking?&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Recycling: The relationships (a word I use loosely) that just won\'t die. It\'s over between us&mdash;but somehow, it isn\'t. These aren\'t the \"work\'s taking me to Dubai for nine months,\" or \"I don\'t want to date you or anyone else while I\'m taking care of my sick father\" dudes.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I soul-search for ever having dated some of my now-rubbish in the first place. I test the floors with my happy dance when I fling them into the dumpster.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Therefore, it\'s pitiful and pathetic when trash slips into recycling under my own watch and encouragement.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">These&nbsp;guys send the odd text or email&nbsp;(\"Oh man, HIM?! I\'ll write back in 19 days\")&nbsp;or will even call&nbsp;(\"Happy New Year to you, too, but I\'m sorry: WHO did you say this is?\")&nbsp;just so I don\'t forget about them. They play on our Roman-candle spark, our hot sex, a deep, deep down (like, buried, but glinting) optimism that of course we\'ll work, and their [fill-in-the-blank] problem? They are ON it!&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In this instance, recycling does not do one\'s personal climate change any favors&mdash;but save the males. &nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">After a couple email exchanges or phone calls later, I\'ve softened up, I\'m curious, I\'m flattered, and it\'s drinks, or it\'s dinner, and it\'s a dessert of a delicious make-out pressed up against the side of my building (he\'s not really in my life anymore, he\'s trouble, so he\'s NOT GETTING INVITED UP. Standards and boundaries, people!).</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Before I turn around, guess who\'s back, taking up mental real estate and eating up my nights? I\'m having deja vu all over again because I thought I\'d take another kick at that can rather than just junk it.&nbsp;Screw you, Greenpeace.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There have been times I have taken the extra step and emptied my love trash&mdash;a double-deleting of the heart and soul. When Mr. Drunkypants, Mr. Moron and Mr. Metro were triple-bagged and kicked to the curb, I was more open to and more focused for The New Guy.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That kind of merciless, incinerating housekeeping is something I should do more often.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Perhaps it will even help the polar bears.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. maybe her better dating decisions are what\'s causing such a pleasant winter.&nbsp;</strong></span></div>\r\n<div><strong><br /></strong></div>','lifestyle','2011-12-05 03:47:27','2012-02-25 15:17:36',8,'dumpster-dive_pic_web.jpg','image/jpeg',45628,'2011-12-05 03:47:26',0,'2012-02-25 15:17:36',1,'personalclimatechange','personalclimatechange'),(170,'I\'m Taken. What\'s Your Number?','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am a magnet for men who are in relationships.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Disclaimer: I do NOT date men who are attached.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Moving on.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Whether at the gym, ambling my beloved streets of New York, standing on line to buy movie tickets, even hovering over the tomatoes at the farmers\' market, if you\'re checking me out and then some, I am counting down til I get a flash of wedding band (it\'s just jewelry, right?) or til your honey bounds up to you (until you\'re married, you\'re single, right?).</span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Specific cases in point: your intrepid love-and-sex sleuth is on vacation.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am walking the white Caribbean sands in notawholelottamuch.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A couple bobs in the placid aqua waters under the bright sunshine. The woman has her arms wrapped around her man\'s neck, her nose nuzzling his ear, immersed in the romantic moment.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">His attention:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To riff the song, he is watching me watching him watching me, with a sly half smile as he whispers into his woman\'s ear, his penetrating eyes stripping me right out of my beachwear.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A few steps down the sand, a Daddy\'s gripping his toddler\'s hand as he marches his water-winged princess into the sea, not breaking his smile and stare as I pass, the poor kid stumbling around in the surf.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now this is where things get more interesting.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Paces later, I see two muscled frat-boy prototypes&mdash;white baseball caps, gold Ray Bans and swim shorts pulled down to there.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If it were not so curious, such a mystery, I would laugh before I cried.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I. Am. Invisible. They walk right by without so much as a glance.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Moi. See-through&mdash;after years of Pilates and a strict vegan diet. &nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So much for the face-off of the aviators I was expecting.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It is a puzzling phenomenon that the single men aren\'t the ones making challenging, x-ray eye-contact.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It could be a matter of cojones. Fear of rejection versus indifference, because after all, the attached dude has someone to go home to, anyway.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Or it\'s something of the opposite, that there is a diet mentality at play. \"You shouldn\'t have that!\" makes the involved man hungrier, but the single one under no pressure and therefore not compelled to nibble.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In the spirit of this metaphor and my next dinner date, single men, borrow the swagger of your (allegedly) attached counterparts. You would be amazed by the results of laser-like eye-contact, a tooth-flashing smile and (wait for it) a hello.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Dudes who are off the market, I encourage you to impart your bold, take-no-prisoners, aggressive tack. It would only be hotter if you were...you know.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Once you do, let go. Rein in your game, your mojo.&nbsp;Run along back to your women and use that same steely gaze.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">As a taken man, you are invisible to me.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she bakes. she has heard the word \"leftovers\" somewhere before.&nbsp;</strong></span></div>\r\n<div><strong><br /></strong></div>','tipsandtricks','2011-12-05 04:08:12','2011-12-20 05:31:25',7,'cheaters.jpg','image/jpeg',31454,'2011-12-05 04:08:12',0,'2011-12-20 05:31:25',1,'takenwhatsyournumber','takenwhatsyournumber'),(171,'Baby, It\'s Just You and Me and My Harem of Exes  ','<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Picture it:</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">New York City.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sunny fall weekend.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A young girl (this young girl) is off for a casual Sunday brunch with the guy who\'s been pursuing me to go out for nearly a year&mdash;A for effort.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No, I wasn\'t playing hard to get, though it looked that way.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">(Let\'s call him) PG rubbed me the wrong way when we met at a Christmas party&mdash;interrupting me mid-conversation with&nbsp;my manly model-turned-entrepreneur friend, trying to physically insert himself between us so he could talk at me. He proceeded to deftly ignore all of my graciously-delivered social clues to get lost. I had no choice but to grin, say goodbye and inch him out with shoulders and elbows. I unprofessionally diagnosed him as a narcissist.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Good ole Facebook: he promptly friended me. </span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Rather than just say, \"No,\" I was immediately, passive-aggressively, and creatively finding 900 excuses to slither out of drink and dinner and coffee invitations.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Eventually, curiosity and kindness with a twist of Darwin (not to mention admiration of his tenacity) got this cat.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Finally, I sent PG a YES.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I decided to ease up, and to observe him in another environment. He wanted so much to talk to me at that party, he cut right in&mdash;ballsy!&mdash;and he was trying just as hard for nearly a year later. Anyway, some people just aren\'t party people; maybe he\'d be more chilled out and socially astute over pancakes.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">PG looked cute and not metro waiting for me in dark jeans and black shirt with expensive shoes.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He gave me a kiss on one cheek, and as I pulled back, another on the second.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">\"Sorry,\" he said, not apologizing, referencing the double-kiss. \"I dated a European for a while.\"</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Bad move.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My two knee-jerk questions:</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Was this supposed to impress me&mdash;that he used to bang trans-Atlantic goods? Further,&nbsp;after he\'d been relentlessly trying to get me in front of him for the better part of ONE YEAR, were these seriously his best opening words?</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Unless he could recover from that one, PG was sunk.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Poor bastard, and by that, I mean me:</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The rest of the conversation (although \"conversation\" involves two people, and this half opened her mouth only to sip coffee and take bites of food) was right in line with party behavior and his gauche greeting.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It centered around him, his checkered romantic past and complaints about his exes.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I was entertained with more about his Euro double-kiss trainer, his drunken and substance-abusing bartender gal pal whom he hooked up with a receptionist job that eventually got her some nice IPOs (but not before she dragged him into rough guy, tough guy bar fights in Nolita), and most recently, his suburban artist who expected him to pick her up at Penn Station when she came to the city (he refused ever to leave Manhattan, yet he was disgusted that she thought him greeting her at the train station was a nice thing to do).&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">His captive audience, I sat, nodded, raised eyebrows, laughed, smiled and frowned at the few, appropriate pauses.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The kicker to my painful time with PG and the ghosts of ladies past was when he called a (real, live, female) friend to join us after his two bright hours in the spotlight.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What a superb exit: \"No, no. You two have a fun afternoon together! Don\'t want to third-wheel it!\"&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There are two lessons to be learned here.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The first:</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Don\'t talk about your ex, or harem of exes, especially on the first date. We\'re here to talk about just the two of us. We\'re at a table for two, or two bar stools shoved together. Observe. Count.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The second:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Who you meet is who they are, never mind the dog and pony show or Amazing Race production they may put on afterward to win you over.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Those were valuable hours of my brunch life I will never see again. I am happy to know my gut was right on, but I should not have turned the other cheek.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. it\'s always coffee o\'clock.</strong></span></div>','talesfromthedate','2011-12-05 04:19:36','2011-12-13 04:17:11',5,'harem.jpg','image/jpeg',75834,'2011-12-05 04:19:35',0,'2011-12-13 04:17:11',1,'harem','harem'),(172,'5 Accessories that will give you Wood','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I&rsquo;m really excited about this. I mean, I usually get jazzed around sweet accessories, but I&rsquo;m like,&nbsp;<em>really</em>&nbsp;excited. I&rsquo;ve got wood. I can&rsquo;t stop touching it. It&rsquo;s this wooden ring I got from&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.linhardtdesign.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Linhardt</a>&nbsp;this weekend. It got me standing at the attention of so many other wooden jewelry designers, and now I have to show you. You might want to go someplace private to look at them&hellip;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">http://fashionindie.com/these-5-accessories-will-give-you-wood/<br /></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-12-06 15:01:09','2011-12-09 06:47:38',2,'screen-shot-2011-12-06-at-9.58.33-am.jpg','image/jpeg',59963,'2011-12-06 15:01:08',0,'2011-12-06 15:01:25',1,'fashionindie-5accessories','fashionindie-5accessories'),(173,'Susan: \"I was taken home by a Penguin.\"','<p>Summary: Susan is our local celebrity this week because, \"I think I was taken home by a Penguin. But it was Freshman year, give me a break.\"</p>\r\n<p>ConnectingSexes: Welcome to another ConnectingSexes.com interview! I\'m glad you could come Susan, since most girls don\'t. That was lame. Let\'s get started. So if you could introduce yourself?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Hey my name is Susan, I\'m from Brooklyn. I\'m a Business Major at University of Vermont and I\'m 21</p>\r\n<p>CS: Good intro. Born and raised Brooklynite or what?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Born there, full-blooded New Yorker.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Always great to hear. So how do you like UVM?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Hm, it\'s like most schools, has it\'s ups and downs. Gorgeous setting though. Senior year here. Love it but wouldn\'t live here.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Excited to graduate?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Yes, about damn time I get paid for the papers I write.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Going to come back to New York?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Hopefully, wherever I can find work</p>\r\n<p>CS: Rough times, understood. So are you single or taken?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Single</p>\r\n<p>CS: Follow-up question, What are you doing Friday night? Totally joking. But not really. How\'s the dating scene in Vermont?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: It\'s like a giant swingers party. A few couples, very few. Great town, great variety, lots of girls and guy. Guys just don\'t like to date here though. They have a &ldquo;Bang and go&rdquo; philosophy. It\'s a candy store ideology.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Alright, have you ever been in a 1 on 1 date?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Like a normal date?</p>\r\n<p>CS: Yeah like they did back in the 60\'s. And if yes how was it?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: It\'s nice to find a guy who wants dinner before drinks and before sex.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Well any dating horror stories?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Actually...yes....in New York. A friend of a friend was in town. He was in his late 20\'s. It was obvious he was very foreign, but it was a bit obnoxious. A tight pink gap polo that</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;was so tight that his chest hair was popping out of the polo.</p>\r\n<p>CS: that\'s horrific. How do you feel about going dutch?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: I\'ll make the move and see how he feels about it, if he wants to go dutch I\'ll go dutch. It\'s the 21<sup>st</sup> century.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Kudos on that. So tell me a drunk fail of yours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Like fall on my face or....wake up next to some guy and having major regrets.?</p>\r\n<p>CS: Whichever floats your boat.</p>\r\n<p>Susie: My Freshman year Halloween, me and 3 other girls dressed as Greek goddesses, because we waited till the last minute. This was the first time I drank Bacardi 151 and I significantly underestimated how drunk it gets you. So we ended up getting very, very, very intoxicated. I went from Greek Goddess to Gladiator because I managed to fall 4 times. Skinned both knees. Bruised my fore</p>\r\n<p>head and arms. I managed to fall again in front of a friend, who yelled to my friend in a cat costume &ldquo;Kitty go save her!&rdquo; because at that point I was covered in blood. At that point it was decided that I should go home.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Rough. That wasn\'t even funny, what the fuck?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: I think I was taken home by a Penguin. But it was Freshman year, give me a break.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Just this once. So you\'re at a bar. Some guy approaches you. What are the top things he can do where you just know &ldquo;This guy isn\'t getting laid&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Susie:Hm...biggest turn offs....Talking about your ex. You can\'t do that. Being generally rude or obnoxious, screaming or spitting when they talk. It\'s loud here but you don\'t need to scream at my face. Bad breath. No job I suppose? The conversation matters the most, if he\'s boring, can\'t</p>\r\n<p>hold a conversation or has nothing interesting to say, well I\'m not going to be interested.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Best answer for any question in any interview. Have I mentioned I love you?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: You have, but I don\'t mind hearing it again.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Glad I can be of service. So more skankalicious questions. What is your Go-To underwear, I\'m a guy so I assume all these things, but you plan to go out, and you hope to see a guy you\'re interested in , so what do you go for?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Well I used to work at Victoria Secret, so I\'ve gathered quite a collection of their garments. I really like their lace boy shorts and hip huggers. Easy to wear, comfortable, don\'t ride up. If I have to keep fixing my underwear, huge turn off. You don\'t want to see a girl standing there pick underwear out of her ass.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Side note- I do like watching women pick underwear out of their ass.</p>\r\n<p>Susie: ...Whatever</p>\r\n<p>CS: Kidding a little I guess. Although I do love Whale-tail. So how do you feel about military boys?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: I like em, code of honor, physically fit, all that training and scheduling. And a bit of them gotta be pretty smart as well.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Cool cool, So what are some things you do when you\'re attracted to a guy? Better yet, how would the guy know you\'re attracted to him?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Laugh a lot. I can\'t help it, even if it\'s not remotely funny it\'ll crack me up. Smile a lot. Turn red. Hand fidgeting, means I\'m nervous. Keep looking at them.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Good answers. Looking for a closing question for this great interview. <strong>shuffles around blank pages. </strong>Have you ever been on a group date? Your group of girls purposely meet a group of guys and go out.</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Usually me and my girlfriends usually go to the bar and try to find guys. But I\'ve never done it prearranged</p>\r\n<p>CS: So when your girls go out, the overall goal is to find a corresponding group of guys, right?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Yeah we try to match it up to get the number right.</p>\r\n<p>CS: How does it usually work out?</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Well we usually designate roles, my friend will be the wing-man if one of us is interested in a guy. I\'m good at that since I\'m pretty fearless, I just try to talk to them, then my friends come over and if there&rsquo;s interest then it works out. A lot of times guys will come to us also.</p>\r\n<p>CS: I\'m basically engaged so I\'ve been an expert wing-man for a while.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Hahaha</p>\r\n<p>CS: Thank you Susan, best interview ever. Next time I see you, I\'m going to take you on a nice 1 on 1 date, old school style, suit, dress, flower on table. It\'ll be great.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Susie: Yes! I can\'t wait</p>\r\n<p>CS: Thanks again and take care&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Susie:Thanks, bye!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','localcelebrity','2011-12-06 15:12:46','2011-12-09 06:47:38',9,'screen-shot-2011-12-06-at-10.05.47-am.jpg','image/jpeg',33137,'2011-12-06 15:12:46',0,'2011-12-06 15:12:53',1,'localcelebrity-takenhomebypenguin','localcelebrity-takenhomebypenguin'),(174,'Snacks, Snacks, Snacks','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In order to stay fit and slim, one needs to plan meals and snacks at least with a little thought! The meals that you eat should be balanced and provide your body with good nutrition. Remember portion size is key here! Snacks too, should be healthy and not just something you mindlessly eat your way through while watching your favorite movie! (Of course, the occasional chocolate, or higher fat food is okay, as long as it is only once in awhile)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Some good snack choices:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">An apple</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">small yogurt and slice of fruit (melon or handful of blueberries)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">protein shake,</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Cut up veggies, dipped in hummus(i like baby carrots the best)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Whole wheat pita bread with can of tuna.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">http://supertrainernews.com/?p=63<br /></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-12-06 15:17:45','2012-01-09 21:03:47',4,'screen-shot-2011-12-06-at-10.14.42-am.jpg','image/jpeg',92592,'2011-12-06 15:17:44',0,'2012-01-09 21:03:47',1,'fitness-snacks','fitness-snacks'),(175,'My Date\'s at Late O\'Clock','<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>One of my biggest dating pet peeves is lateness. It gets my blood pressure higher than a popped collar.</p>\r\n<p>LN and I met at a destination wedding. From \"hello\" at the rehearsal barbecue, we spent every minute together (not bedtime minutes. Such restraint).</p>\r\n<p>The second we got back to the city from the New England getaway, he called me every single day, telling me how excited he was to see me again that weekend. He planned a marathon Saturday night date for the two of us. I was smitten and in full disclosure, hot off the heels of our friends\' ceremony, had a head full of fantasies. Yeah.</p>\r\n<p>I spent Saturday working backward from pick-up time (ah, picking me up: quel gentleman). Every minute was carefully accounted for: LN wouldn\'t and shouldn\'t be kept waiting! I was shaved, waxed and groomed, showered and perfumed, made-up, dressed&mdash;and pacing.</p>\r\n<p>Two minutes before the appointed hour, a text buzzed in.</p>\r\n<p>\"Running late. Getting a cab soon.\"</p>\r\n<p>My heart sank and my brain kicked into gear.</p>\r\n<p>A whole week of syrupy calls after being my shadow at the wedding, telling me all about the fun plans we\'d be making down the line, and now this? He would be texting me to say he was downstairs if he was into me.</p>\r\n<p>Besides, he must\'ve known he would be late much before now. Why not get in touch then?</p>\r\n<p>Something was going on.</p>\r\n<p>When he eventually rolled up&mdash;nearly an hour after his text and without apology&mdash;I was ready to see if I was right: that LN\'s tardiness signaled he wanted to be anywhere else. Because my date had now morphed into a social experiment, it was easy to smile and resist mentioning I was pissed for being kept waiting (well, maybe not that last one).</p>\r\n<p>LN put a couple feet between us when we walked down the sidewalk, talked to the food on his plate, flirted with the girls at the table next to us, and insulted my footwear: wedges and not heels? Do I like YSLs? Louboutins? Not that he had a shoe fetish&mdash;he was just asking.</p>\r\n<p>As LN dropped me off at the end of the night, he said he would phone me again. I knew he never would. I gave him a tight smile. No need to lie, bud. He rammed his tongue in my mouth (ugh, really? After all that?) Needless to say, I was delighted to run upstairs to fiercely make love to my couch and DVR, all before midnight.</p>\r\n<p>The scoop from our mutual married friends was that LN was actually casually dating a divorcee (complete with daughter). No wonder he was so standoffish, late and rude. I guess he wanted to take the easy way out by turning me off rather than tell me the truth.</p>\r\n<p>Sure, sometimes late happens. Not everyone who\'s running way behind is hiding A Major Secret, like LN. Subways get stuck between stations. Bosses unceremoniously demand a project within a project&mdash;due five minutes ago&mdash;and there goes the night. Sucks.</p>\r\n<p>But simply showing up late, or getting in touch minutes before (or right at, or past) meet-up time to announce a short (or long) delay says much about my date/boyfriend, how he values me and my time.</p>\r\n<p>And after careful searching, I have come to notice there is no Late O\'Clock slot on my iCal, or my Gmail calendar, either, so I now ask to reschedule for the first Thursday of possibly never.</p>\r\n<p>Does that work for you?</p>\r\n<p><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she invokes a 20-minute waiting rule, especially in the winter.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','talesfromthedate','2011-12-12 02:17:31','2012-06-05 18:12:42',5,'late.jpg','image/jpeg',25832,'2011-12-12 02:17:31',0,'2012-06-05 18:12:42',1,'late','late'),(176,'Dumbass With a Smartphone','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am hot and heavy with my new iPhone 4s.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We have been together all weekend long, yet it has at once uncovered and created neediness and attachment issues I had previously never known.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Wherever I am, my 4.9 ounce lover is in my tight, molesting grip, or in my eye line.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I wander the streets, eyes vacant, plugged into Pandora (which I wish would quit needing a reset). New Apps I can\'t live without are piling up, I text like it\'s my job, and I love to boss Siri around.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yet as close as we have grown, I know enough to put down my phantom-white sweetheart when it\'s not just the two of us. Tiny stab in the heart; it\'s fine.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">An ex of recent history loved that my (ha ha ha) Blackberry never emerged from my purse when we were together. He was equally courteous.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">\"I can\'t stand it when I\'m out with a girl and she\'s got her phone on the table, checking it and texting away,\" he told me. \"Like, why don\'t you just sit there and read a magazine?\"</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Never mind that I\'d have appreciated if he didn\'t tell me he was canoodling with women on our off nights&mdash;he was totally right.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you\'re not entirely with me when we\'re together, I am going to find someone who wants to be.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It is as irritating as cheap toilet paper to sit down with someone who plunks their iPhone, Blackberry or Droid on the bar or table with tremendous authority. I hear that loud THUNK, and I think, \"Hrm. Table for three? Or should I just excuse myself?\"&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It could be a matter of minutes before my dude is going to&nbsp;grope his lithium-powered princess in search of entertainment. Maybe my personal news feed is too slow for him (So...what else? Lemme show you these photos from the weekend!). Maybe he forgot to check how low the Dow closed (WSJ\'s right here!). No, I don\'t really want to see how he\'s doing on Words with Friends (I\'m kicking ASS!). And really, I wish he\'d leave work at work, if only for a few hours, or until I am in the ladies\' room.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Device addicts, if you haven\'t already, turn it to silent&mdash;or completely off if you know you can\'t help yourself&mdash;after you\'ve checked in to Foursquare, of course. Then tuck it away. You\'ll survive. Facebook won\'t break. Neither will Twitter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Give your girl or guy your focus rather than the top of your head&mdash;although, that might come later in a different context, if you\'re doing all the right things, like no compromised conversation because you\'re tapping your way through cocktails and crudo.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Little iPhone, iSurrender to your seductive powers. I think about you all the time and love to stroke your smooth face. But it has been a breeze to connect only when we\'re alone.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My new smartphone will not turn me into a real-life social-networking dumbass.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she is planting an iPad 2 in her apple orchard.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p>','tipsandtricks','2011-12-12 02:35:46','2011-12-13 21:43:07',7,'dumbasssmartfone.jpg','image/jpeg',38914,'2011-12-12 02:35:45',0,'2011-12-13 21:43:07',1,'dumbass','dumbass'),(177,'#4 Dating Song: Miguel','<div>\r\n<p>Song: Quickie</p>\r\n<p>Why? Straight-up hook-up. No mixed message here. Honesty\'s the best (most rewarding) policy.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lyrics: \"I don\'t wanna be loved</p>\r\n<p>I just wanna quickie</p>\r\n<p>No bite marks, no scratches, and no hickeys</p>\r\n<p>If you can get with that, mami come get with me\"</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: x-small;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/gt3QLI3XYtk\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>','music','2011-12-12 02:45:49','2011-12-12 21:30:51',6,'miguel.jpg','image/jpeg',33410,'2011-12-12 02:45:49',0,'2011-12-12 21:30:51',1,'datesong4','datesong4'),(178,'Here Comes Santa Claws','<div>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m pretty sure that there are many nail art enthusiasts out there, you know the ones who must always plan their daily nail art with their outfits? As we all know with everyone in the holiday spirit and the count down for yet another gathering of love, we&rsquo;ve put together 16 ideas of holiday nail art fun!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>http://fashionindie.com/christmas-daze-16-holiday-nail-art-ideas/</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;\"><br /></span></div>','fashionindie','2011-12-12 02:51:31','2011-12-12 20:51:20',2,'holidaynails.png','image/png',268124,'2011-12-12 02:51:30',0,'2011-12-12 20:51:20',1,'holidaynails','holidaynails'),(179,'Wanna Glue Sequins On Your Eyes? Not Us, Either.','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">We\'re stoked for New Year\'s Eve!</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">One party look involves gluing sequins on your upper and lower eyelids, as instructed by Into the Gloss.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">Open-eyed, it\'s a weird Pierrot effect.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">Closed, it\'s like tiny irises.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">From a distance, it\'s plain freaky.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">Does it say Auld Lang Syne to you?</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">Definitely a look that should be forgot and never thought upon, at least to us.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://intothegloss.com/2011/12/sequins/\">http://intothegloss.com/2011/12/sequins/</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. maybe for a million bucks.</span></strong></p>','lifestyle','2011-12-12 02:59:00','2012-02-25 15:14:55',8,'sequinseyes.png','image/png',94611,'2011-12-12 02:58:59',0,'2012-02-25 15:14:55',1,'sequinseyes','sequinseyes'),(180,'Kick-off 2012 in Navy and Gold','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">What a fresh look for the new year: navy pinstripe suit with gold liner. Dapper!</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\">It\'ll be ready January 1st at our friend Jonathan\'s showroom.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.evolutionofstyle.com/index.php/site/blog_details/453/\">http://www.evolutionofstyle.com/index.php/site/blog_details/453/</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-12-12 03:03:46','2012-02-25 21:00:31',3,'screen-shot-2011-12-10-at-4.59.35-pm.png','image/png',238607,'2011-12-12 03:03:44',0,'2012-02-25 21:00:31',1,'navypins','navypins'),(181,'Mark: \"I hunt gorgeous women.\"','<p>Summary: Mark is our local celebrity this week because, \"Some people get up at 5 am to hunt and fish. I stay out to 5 am to hunt and fish.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ConnectingSexes: Welcome to another ConnectingSexes.com interview being conducted at Daddy-O&rsquo;s in the West Village, one of the only bars that shows hockey, serves the garbage plate and plays Zeppelin and the Doors! We ran across this fellow Mark, offered him free beer in exchange for his life story.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Hey, grab a chair and a Bud. Wait, is that a flip phone?</p>\r\n<p>Mark: Yeah, man. Old school charm. It&rsquo;s classique!</p>\r\n<p>CS: Can you show me where Google maps lives on the phone?</p>\r\n<p>Mark: Who needs a map when you live in NYC?</p>\r\n<p>CS: Good point. So when did you make the trek down from Binghamton, and why?</p>\r\n<p>Mark: 17 years and counting. Just wanted to live the dream. Just like the movie Manhattan.</p>\r\n<p>(The table is silenced because no one understands this cultural reference)</p>\r\n<p>Mark: What? (swig). I screen old movie. Man-HATTAN is a classic! You haven&rsquo;t seen it? Listen chicks dig it.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Uh, no. Is Jennifer Lopez&nbsp; or Justin Beiber in it?</p>\r\n<p>(Mary spits out her beer)</p>\r\n<p>Mark: Are you fucking serious Mary?</p>\r\n<p>Stefan: Sorry Mark. Mary is obsessed with the Bieb.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Sorry Mark (motions to waiter &ndash; &lsquo;Napkin please&rsquo;). So, what do you do for a living?</p>\r\n<p>Mark: I play tennis, race cars and fondle women. I am generally available on weekends and I am my own boss.</p>\r\n<p>(At this point we can tell if Mary is annoyed or smitten)</p>\r\n<p>Mark: It&rsquo;s a classic movie you douche! Dudley!</p>\r\n<p>CS: Okay..moving on&hellip;so what do you do besides play tennis?</p>\r\n<p>Mark: Play hockey. Power left-winger. Wheels, tenacity, and a laser for a wrist shot. I lead the club in scoring.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Can you show me the stats on your phone? Oh wait&hellip;you can&rsquo;t! HaHa</p>\r\n<p>CS: So, what is your claim to fame my man?</p>\r\n<p>Mark: I was at the old Monkey Bar 12 ago, wearing a suit and tie, and there was some real obnoxious jerk there who had said something to me and I was stewing about it so I walked over to his table of 10 where he was sitting and I said very politely \"excuse me do you have an ashtray?, oh, I see that you do\".&nbsp; And I proceeded to put my cigarette out in his drink.&nbsp; I walked away and he got up from his table and started to fight with me and the piano player who was playing in front of a room full of people had to break it up.&nbsp; I ran out of there into the cold dark night and into the subway, my heart was racing and I felt so alive.</p>\r\n<p>CS: A-MAZING! Did you watch Manhattan after? Forget that&hellip;you seem very philosophical&hellip;define the perfect woman.</p>\r\n<p>Mark: \"Was it all so simple then or has time re-written every word, if we had the chance to do it all again, tell me would we, could we?\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Mary:&nbsp; &ldquo;Are you single Mark&hellip;.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>CS: Til next time! Shots!</p>','localcelebrity','2011-12-12 03:21:22','2011-12-13 05:09:17',9,'matt.jpg','image/jpeg',73175,'2011-12-12 03:21:21',0,'2011-12-13 05:09:17',1,'localceleb-mark','localceleb-mark'),(182,'Beware the 45-Degree Leg Press','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">According to our friends at Askmen.com, there is one machine at the gym they want to soak in napalm and hurl into an active volcano.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They have deemed the <a href=\"http://www.criticalbench.com/exercises/pics/leg-press2.jpg\">45-degree leg press</a> as utterly deceptive, masquerading as useful while actually being pretty useless.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What&rsquo;s worse, they claim it will mess you up.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> If you want to learn why you should avoid it, click here:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/tkUbxw\">http://bit.ly/tkUbxw</a></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. not to sound like your mother, but she really does want you to be careful, otherwise you\'ll never be able to keep up with her.&nbsp;</span></strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-12-17 16:18:47','2012-01-30 16:47:14',4,'fitness.jpg','image/jpeg',38343,'2011-12-17 16:22:30',0,'2012-01-30 16:47:14',1,'legpress','legpress'),(183,'#3 Dating Song: Lit','<p>Song: Miserable</p>\r\n<p>Why? What starts off sexy and sweet devolves into kinda mean and nasty by a resentful, co-dependent boyfriend. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lyrics:</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;You make me come</p>\r\n<p>You make me complete<span style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>You make me completely miserable.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/kMOeTLLeaDU\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','music','2011-12-17 17:57:14','2011-12-18 15:15:07',6,'screen-shot-2011-12-17-at-12.08.03-pm.jpg','image/jpeg',100291,'2011-12-17 17:57:13',0,'2011-12-18 15:15:07',1,'datesong3lit','datesong3lit'),(184,'Still Shopping? Help is Here','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We assume you may not be on top of your holiday gift-buying; our friends at Fashionindie.com are just as presumptuous.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Here&rsquo;s a link to their handy-dandy shopping compilation, 25 Days of Gifts Guides, so no one will wish a stocking full of coal on you come next year.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now start spending.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/vfDBFn\">http://bit.ly/vfDBFn</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-12-18 14:40:12','2011-12-18 14:41:06',2,'screen-shot-2011-12-18-at-9.37.50-am.jpg','image/jpeg',246551,'2011-12-18 14:40:10',0,'2011-12-18 14:41:06',1,'stillshopping','stillshopping'),(185,'It\'s What\'s Inside That Counts','<p><span style=\