trong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she has too many trigger words to mention.</span></strong></p>','lifestyle','2011-12-18 19:57:58','2012-02-25 15:13:45',8,'dictionary.jpg','image/jpeg',944090,'2011-12-18 19:57:50',0,'2012-02-25 15:13:45',1,'seriouslywhatever','seriouslywhatever'),(187,'Wall Street\'s Fastest Man','<div>\r\n<p>Interview with: Wall Street&rsquo;s Fastest Man</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Summary: Our local celebrity this week is a guy the &lsquo;Occupy Wall Street&rsquo; protesters will never catch&hellip;he is the reigning champ.&nbsp; He is Wall Street&rsquo;s Fastest Man.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ConnectingSexes: Welcome to another ConnectingSexes.com interview being conducted at Employees Only in the West Village, an upscale watering hole for those that love great drinks, a comfortable scene and chicken soup at 4 am. We invited our guest to Employees Only so he could claim his status over a few Cointreau beverages.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CS: Hey, thanks for the time&hellip;Dude you look big?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Thanks. Just finished the contest, been training hard, staying focused, now ready to let loose.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Yeah, I can tell&hellip;you and every other guys is FOCUSED on the blond at the bar.</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: (shrugs)&hellip;.Good drinks here.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Yeah, great burgers too. So where you from?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Arlington, TX, been here for 7 years.</p>\r\n<p>CS: A Texan. Amazing. We love you guys. So do Aussie girls!</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Seriously, there are a lot of Aussies here. Weird.</p>\r\n<p>CS: What brought you here?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: A small dream that morphed into a way of life.</p>\r\n<p>Stefan to Mary: Why are you Tebowing in the middle of the interview?</p>\r\n<p>Mary: IDK. While texting.</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: I love business. I love finance. I just wanted to put it all to work. Then I found a great group of friends, was able to explore my passion of working out, playing football and just found my stride. And New York is where it all plays out.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Are those pictures of dogs on your phone?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Hey, I have a soft side, those dogs represent everything innocent and pure, they produce calm in a sea of New York turbulence.</p>\r\n<p>Mary to CS: Can you please stop interviewing your friends I will fall in love with.</p>\r\n<p>Stefan (now owling): Shut up and check this out. (The Aussies are now interested in our table).</p>\r\n<p>Stefan: So, standard question, your sign?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Aquarius</p>\r\n<p>Mary: No one cares.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Okay&hellip;so, tell us why you should be our local celebrity.</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: I really love to compete. I mean, I grew up playing sports and I love the feeling you get just before stepping on the field. That feeling is the juice, but is so tough to recreate professionally. You know?</p>\r\n<p>CS: Absolutely. The feeling of having something on the line, a win, a slam-dunk, a big wave, finding the element is so hard as we get older.</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Yeah, so I found this event and thought it would be an interesting way to channel my energies and raise some money for charity. So, I made a few sacrifices, stepped up the training a bit, relied on my circle of friends for support and showed up on a brisk Saturday hoping for a good result.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Tell us more&hellip;How did you do?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: (Smiling) I think I may have surprised a few guys when I ripped off my sweats and displayed the green socks&hellip;haha.&nbsp; Seriously, there were some ex college athletes lining up for the 40 yard dash&hellip;.I was in awe, but knew I did everything I could up to that point to get the best result out of my body. I crouched down, waited for the whistle and just exploded out of the gate. It all happened so fast. When I finished the race, I looked over the to the timer and received a Cheshire grin.&nbsp; I think he was surprised of my time, but I jogged over and he proclaimed that I was the winner. I was exhausted and thrilled. I then got to race Willie Gault, in a ceremonious race, and beat him too. I definitely earned my beer that night.</p>\r\n<p>Mary: Can I feel your biceps again?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Is she serious?</p>\r\n<p>CS: Congrats on the huge accomplishment. That is really great.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Okay, before we dive into our next round of tasty Cointreau beverages, lets talk about dating, are you single, what are you looking for in a woman?</p>\r\n<p>WSFM: Yeah I am single. I am really just looking for someone who is intelligent, caring, down-to-earth, and attractive.&nbsp; Someone who has some of the same interests as me, but also enough differences that it broadens my horizons.&nbsp; Above all else, someone whom I feel a real connection with, because finding the right person is definitely not a science.</p>\r\n<p>Mary: Wanna dance?</p>\r\n<p>CS: That&rsquo;s all for now, check back next week for the interview of famed writer, doorman and Brazilian surfer, G-Money.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>','localcelebrity','2011-12-19 22:26:39','2012-03-21 19:58:05',9,'40yddash.jpg','image/jpeg',77477,'2011-12-19 22:39:04',0,'2012-03-21 19:58:05',1,'wallstreetsfastestman','wallstreetsfastestman'),(188,'Ho, Ho, Ho: Thanks for the Gift','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My gym has no privacy.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Treadmills and recumbent bicycles are right in the windows for passers-by to see the red-faced and the sweaty, doing damage control on food and drink. We gym rats watch crap TV, or gaze in an unfocused stare at the street, checking out what awaits after we&rsquo;ve put in our time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I was knocking out my miles this weekend, huffing and puffing my way to the never-here finish line, when an old flame strolled by.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">(Let\'s call him) SPE lives barely two blocks from me. &nbsp;He was fun, smart, funny, actually had hobbies, and was smooth in every way you care to think of. When things were good, they were excellent, and did I mention we scored a 12 out of 10 for location convenience? The typical New Yorker fears a long-distance relationship, which means having to switch trains. Our concern was catching one set of red lights.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">SPE looked at me. I looked back. He waved. And waved. And waved again. I was startled.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sucked that I was a hellamess with my ponytail fashioned like a puked-up hairball on top of my head and my face as glamorous as a saltine cracker (wearing make-up during a workout clogs your little pores, don&rsquo;t you know).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What caught me off-guard was that a girl was immobilizing his other arm, weighing it down like an anvil.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In our sweet yet tawdry off-again-on-again relationship&mdash;yes, SPE was a permanent recycling-bin dweller (see my last post on Personal Climate Change)&mdash;he was always in the background of my life, like wallpaper. I could and would summon him at any time.&nbsp; And vice-versa.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now, the insistent waving with his functional arm was to communicate that he had moved on.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Previously, only I had&mdash;by dodging his attempts to make plans, expressing that I was looking for something more/something else, and eventually, bottom line, flat-out saying that what he was able to offer was not &ldquo;My-Next-Boyfriend&rdquo; material. Eventually, I quietly faded out on him.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">However, it appeared quite clearly that he found someone who was happy to pick up what he was throwing down. His arm-flailing said, &ldquo;Yeah! A girl! That&rsquo;s right! Look! See? Do you?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Even though I got what I wanted, it felt weird to observe SPE with someone else (I&rsquo;m a bitch: she&rsquo;s pretty&mdash;pretty ugly). It confirmed that we are, at last, over. Foh rill. O-V-A-H. And although we have been neighbors these past million years, we have never once bumped into each other with anyone of romantic interest; just with friends, or alone.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now, having crossed into new, awkward territory, I highly doubt SPE and I will ever (though never&rsquo;s kind of a long time) phone each other again for dinner; and if we do, it would be as nothing more than pals. We&rsquo;ll finally start showing up on time for our reservations, imagine that.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So thanks, SPE, for fortuitously passing by my gym window with your &ldquo;You Mean You&rsquo;re with HER now?!&rdquo; girlfriend. It was a thoughtful, albeit unintentional, present and gesture. It enabled a little personal holiday housekeeping. The trash and recycling were both taken to the curb.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Tangentially, it also made me think twice about hitting the gym bald-faced.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Perhaps a quick slick of lip-gloss and sweep of mascara before hopping on the treadmill won&rsquo;t clog anything but my schedule.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she believes the calorie read-out on the treadmill low-balls her efforts.</strong></span></p>','talesfromthedate','2011-12-19 22:56:31','2011-12-20 15:19:16',5,'handwaving.jpg','image/jpeg',69284,'2011-12-19 22:56:30',0,'2011-12-20 15:19:16',1,'hohoho','hohoho'),(189,'Here\'s My Card. Later.','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A friend of mine met a boy at a Christmas party over the weekend. He is the brother of the hostess.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">KS gushed that they chatted all night long. He gave her his business card.&nbsp; When she went to hail a cab at the end of the night, she offered to share it with Party Boy (how, uhm, gentlewomanly of her). He took her up on it. Woo woo.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">She described that as he was exiting the cab (note that Mr. Entrepreneur did not give her money to cover his share, or the entire ride. Unimpressive. In fact, rude. Chivalry, I mourn you), he confirmed with her that she&rsquo;d be getting in touch with him. &ldquo;Oh, YES!&rdquo; KS enthusiastically assured him before he gave her a smooch (first one of the night) and slammed the door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am disappointed for her and in him.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When she told me that he gave her his card, I asked how that unfolded; she was a little hazy on the details and had pushed quickly through that part of the story.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;He was talking about his business, and gave his card to the guy we were standing with, and then, uhm, said to me, &lsquo;Oh, here, you take one, too,&rsquo;&rdquo; KS sheepishly stammered.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So, he passed KS his card when involved in a business conversation with her and someone else. He was already giving it out&mdash;to A DUDE&mdash;and figured KS ought to get a card, then never asked poor KS for hers. Ever. And he had plenty opportunity to do so. Quintuple whammy of minimal-to-no interest.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Party Boy didn&rsquo;t do much better during the taxi-portion part of the evening.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That one minute he spent exiting the taxi to ask KS to be sure to reach out means squat; why she was glowing over it baffles me.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If he (or any man) wanted her, a different question would have been posited as he was outside the taxi and saying goodnight:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Hey KS [whipping out Blackberry/Droid/iPod/pen and paper/chisel and tablet], just in case, what&rsquo;s your number?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Or better yet, while they were holding hands and talking about nothing in the cab (they were not, according to KS, putting on a show for the driver in the backseat), he could have asked her for her coordinates then. And made out with her, too.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not one to be coy, KS emailed Party Boy a &ldquo;nice to meet you&rdquo; note the next evening.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Hmmm&hellip;promising&hellip;but after New Year&rsquo;s?&rdquo; read part of her note over his reply, which she forwarded to me.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To his credit, he responded quickly, asking her out for a drink&mdash;in 2012.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s not even Christmas. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2012 is a long ways away for an anxious girl.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">KS is clearly eager to see him now, now, now. Not because she thinks he&rsquo;s so super and because she wants a boyfriend/husband/anything (which she does).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Come on: she wants A Date For New Year&rsquo;s, never mind that he&rsquo;s a total stranger. They can get to know each other while they tongue to the ball-drop (the one in Times Square, Smutpot).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Duh: Of course Party Boy (and any boy) knows that seeing a girl PRE-New Year&rsquo;s puts on the pressure to ask her out FOR New Year&rsquo;s. And how would he worm his way out of that one?&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Speaking to KS&rsquo;s situation, look to Party Boy&rsquo;s behavior; no one here&rsquo;s shocked he&rsquo;s not chomping the bit to make plans. He didn&rsquo;t even want her phone number. Her having his was good enough. He&rsquo;d leave the rest to fate and chance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Indeed, KS&rsquo;s Christmas party experience was rich with lessons for her and for the rest of us.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When a guy gives you his contact information without asking for yours, don&rsquo;t brag.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It says when it comes to seeing you again, he could take you or leave you.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If he really wanted to nail it down, he&rsquo;d make sure to have your number stored before the night is over. You wouldn&rsquo;t be getting away so fast and easily, Missy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Specific to this time of year, if you meet a guy NOW (ie: right, like, immediately before New Year&rsquo;s) do not get all hung up on him asking you out for The Big Night. New Year&rsquo;s Eve is an overblown occasion, one with way too much stigma attached. Do not care. Really. If you do, use that same energy more productively and party for three days in a row with your best friends. Then share your fab stories. You come off as more interesting because you are.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Only time will tell if my sweet, love-ravenous, earnestly optimistic friend KS is getting the classic, holiday fade-out and will be forgotten, or if Party Boy will make good and make plans in 2012.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To be continued. Maybe.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she doesn&rsquo;t blow sunshine at anyone.</span></strong></p>','tipsandtricks','2011-12-19 23:02:58','2011-12-19 23:30:24',7,'tips.jpg','image/jpeg',174144,'2011-12-19 23:02:57',0,'2011-12-19 23:30:24',1,'bizcard','bizcard'),(190,'Santa, I Need Flannel','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Ah, Christmas. It is a time for family, good cheer and elasticized waistbands.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our friends at Fashionindie.com have directed us to their preferred place for the most forgiving of clothes&mdash;in addition to other cool items&mdash;just the type that this season demands.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Follow us to Creatures of Comfort, and go ahead, eat another cookie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/ta1VA6\">http://bit.ly/ta1VA6</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2011-12-25 17:16:41','2011-12-25 17:18:34',2,'cookiesfashion.jpg','image/jpeg',162013,'2011-12-25 17:16:40',0,'2011-12-25 17:18:34',1,'cozyxmas','cozyxmas'),(191,'Drop Sets Means Drop Weight','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Never mind that data show people gain only four or five pounds on average between Christmas and New Year\'s: there is a certain solace in knowing you will fry off those suckers the moment you put down your Baileys and hit the gym.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">As soon as you manage to lumber your slovenly self there, we suggest you try our friends AskMen.com&rsquo;s awesome fat-burning tips, achieved by incorporating drop sets, which builds tons of muscle.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Come next year, Santa will ask for a six-pack like yours.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/uosMN7\">http://bit.ly/uosMN7</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays and dates in new york. she knows you can do it, you glutton, you.</strong></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2011-12-25 20:41:59','2012-01-30 16:45:47',4,'xmasfittodate.jpg','image/jpeg',26827,'2011-12-25 20:41:59',0,'2012-01-30 16:45:47',1,'xmasdrop','xmasdrop'),(192,'Tuck Your Shirt In, Young Man','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We were super-excited to read Details magazine&rsquo;s scolding rant on men who are above tucking in their shirts. We could not agree more.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s sloppy, unsexy, and smacks of laziness; not to mention, it&rsquo;s pretty pass&eacute;.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Time for an update, fellas: Take a minute and push the shirttails into the top of your pants.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Read your full dressing-down here, and you will never, ever dare do it again: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/v6Ze3a\">http://bit.ly/v6Ze3a</a></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she\'s happy to know she\'s not alone getting bent out of shape over this slovenly look.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2011-12-25 20:51:41','2012-02-25 20:58:39',3,'xmasshirttails.jpg','image/jpeg',71433,'2011-12-25 20:51:41',0,'2012-02-25 20:58:39',1,'xmastails','xmastails'),(193,'#2 Dating Song: The Wallflowers','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>Song: One Headlight</p>\r\n<p>Why?</p>\r\n<p>This song&rsquo;s profound words hit us right in heart. It&rsquo;s about lost love&mdash;this dude&rsquo;s woman is no more. He&rsquo;s coming to grips with her being gone and his depression.</p>\r\n<p>Lyrics:</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Hey, come on try a little</p>\r\n<p>Nothing is forever</p>\r\n<p>There\'s got to be something better than&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the middle</p>\r\n<p>But me &amp; Cinderella,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We put it all together</p>\r\n<p>We can drive it home</p>\r\n<p>With one headlight.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Zzyfcys1aLM\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p>','music','2011-12-25 21:13:08','2011-12-25 21:15:06',6,'-2wallflowers.jpg','image/jpeg',126469,'2011-12-25 21:13:07',0,'2011-12-25 21:15:06',1,'dating2song1headlight','dating2song1headlight'),(194,'Steamy Brazilian Writer+Surfer+Musician ','<p>Ladies take notice. Our local celebrity might make you want to get wet (in a bikini). Giulliano is Brazilian transplant in NYC who surfs, plays the drums for an Indie rock band and in his spare time writes for the Brazilian surf magazine HARDCORE. Simply put, he is pretty damn cool.</p>\r\n<p>ConnectingSexes: Welcome to another ConnectingSexes.com interview being conducted at Ward III in Tribeca, a speakeasy that caters both the after work downtown crowd and those seeking tasty sliders, homemade eggnog and live music on Sunday&rsquo;s. We finally caught up with Giulliano a few weeks ago over a few Maker&rsquo;s Mark Manhattans.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ConnectingSexes: G, thanks for making time for us today! I, m glad we could line up the interview at Ward III</p>\r\n<p>G: Totally. Such a great lil spot. Great staff, d&eacute;cor and a ton of attractive women.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Ummm, this one is with me!</p>\r\n<p>G: Whoops, sorry! Next one on me!</p>\r\n<p>CS: No worries. Did you get in the water today?</p>\r\n<p>G: No, was a little too cold today and have been working on our next album when not working. But damn, can&rsquo;t wait for next summer. Nothing like being on the beach on a hot summer day, catching waves.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Would you say surfing is your passion?</p>\r\n<p>G: Absolutely. Growing up in the small, cool city of Sao Leopoldo in Southern Brazil, surfing was an institution. &nbsp;And surfing in NYC led to my work with HARDCORE.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CS: Oh yeah, the article about surfing in NYC.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>G: Yeah.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Congrats! So, how long have you been in NYC?</p>\r\n<p>G: Just about half my life. 21 years.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Which is about the average age of most of the chicks I see you with? (smirking)</p>\r\n<p>G: HaHaHa, can&rsquo;t blame a man who has a diverse skill set.</p>\r\n<p>CS: True. Did I tell you I juggle? So, why did you move up?</p>\r\n<p>G: The culture, I always loved the music, the skateboarding and surfing scene, so when my ex girlfriend moved here, it was a perfect excuse to come and check it out. I have been able to explore all my passions in this beautiful city.</p>\r\n<p>CS: What is your best surfing story?</p>\r\n<p>G: You know, I have so many surfing stories, but my favorite one actually happened in my hometown. I was out surfing on a picture perfect day. Glassy 6 footers, long periods, just catching waves all day. And then on my last wave, I dropped into the barrel only to see dolphins swimming parallel to my board. As I cut, so did they. Amazing.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Wow. So beautiful. So, talk to us about your band and drumming career.</p>\r\n<p>G: Well, that is the only thing that keeps me out of the water. We have started to book gigs all over NYC and are hoping for some good news in 2012.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Congrats in advance! So, changing gears, what are you looking for in a woman, how do you define perfection?</p>\r\n<p>G: The perfect woman in my eyes, have to have style, and good looks as well, but what I love most is humor, adventure, a girl that loves music and knows how to dance. Someone you can have a fun conversation that lasts into the night.</p>\r\n<p>CS: So, besides having great hair, being a talented drummer, good surfer and skater, what do you have to offer?</p>\r\n<p>G: Ah, thanks man. I think generally I am a fun person to be around, a great friend and someone that will make you laugh and have a good time.</p>\r\n<p>CS: Well I can attest to all those. You are a good dude. Thanks for spending some time with us.</p>\r\n<p>G: My pleasure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Giulliano&rsquo;s article in HARDCORE can be found at http://hardcore.uol.com.br/17703-Surfistas_de_Trem</p>','localcelebrity','2011-12-26 00:39:35','2011-12-26 15:28:49',9,'g.jpg','image/jpeg',60753,'2011-12-26 00:42:30',0,'2011-12-26 15:28:49',1,'steamybraziliansurfer','steamybraziliansurfer'),(195,'Conquering the Champagne Bottle','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We are stoked for our New Year&rsquo;s Eve celebrations.&nbsp; We plan to surround ourselves with our old friends, some new ones (and maybe just one special one) and plenty of good cheer. And by good cheer, we mean quality booze and bubbly. Oceans of both.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So what happens when you&rsquo;re the one in charge of opening the Cristal, all eyes are on you, and you get performance anxiety?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Never fear, gentle reader. &nbsp;Your friends at Connectingsexes have you covered with this (hilarious) video.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now remember to watch and listen with rapt attention for the valuable lessons imparted. The first one is critical: Taking off the foil is a key step to getting at that good stuff.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Happy New Year!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/uCfrBQ\">http://bit.ly/uCfrBQ</a><br /></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><object id=\"videojugplayer\" classid=\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\" width=\"640\" height=\"382\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.videojug.com/player?id=cec52c83-15b1-1a5a-172c-ff0008c9e905\" /><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" /><param name=\"allowScriptAccess\" value=\"always\" /></object></p>','tipsandtricks','2011-12-27 03:26:10','2011-12-27 03:43:18',7,'little-boy-with-big-champagne-bottle.jpg','image/jpeg',41748,'2011-12-27 03:26:09',0,'2011-12-27 03:43:18',1,'champagne','champagne'),(196,'Day-After Face: Mirror, Mirror','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Woot!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You&rsquo;re licking the last from your glass, or woofing the final bite of your greasy hangover breakfast, or sneaking out the front door for your walk of shame (what did you say your name was, again? Who cares; dog needs a walk).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No matter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s mad-early, and you look like hell. Your eye-bags are packed and ready to go.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Thankfully, one of our favorite 2011 trends is the mirrored shade&mdash;on guys and girls. Hot.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We make a strong case that they&rsquo;ll go strong all through 2012, too, keeping your stalking glances under wraps and your better-now face mysterious.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So put them on after (or before) the party and keep them close all through the new year.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Have a happy one, gorgeous.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she is shopping for many sunglasses to enhance her 2012 look.</span></strong></p>','lifestyle','2011-12-29 14:41:56','2012-02-25 15:11:36',8,'xmassunnies.jpg','image/jpeg',63521,'2011-12-29 14:41:56',0,'2012-02-25 15:11:36',1,'mirror','mirror'),(197,'Gym Clothes That Prompt Resolutions','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We notice that come January 2, there&rsquo;s practically a velvet rope and a bouncer outside our gym because it&rsquo;s so packed with bloated, guilt-ridden resolution-makers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Given the overpopulation, it&rsquo;s a ripe opportunity to stand out in the crowd of stuffed-mushroom, whiskey and red-wine bingers: Why not wear something better than a ho-hum pair of black pants and a tank top?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our friends at Fashionindie.com have highlighted for us some mighty high-end, oh-so-fabulous-darling workout threads, courtesy of Vogue.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We know today&rsquo;