nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What&rsquo;s your pre-game song? We&rsquo;re on Twitter: @connectingsexes, or email us: <a href=\"mailto:info@connectingsexes.com\">info@connectingsexes.com</a>, and tell us why.</span></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/wyx6JDQCslE\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>','music','2012-02-03 13:54:12','2012-02-13 22:31:57',6,'-10lmfao.jpg','image/jpeg',46720,'2012-02-03 13:54:12',0,'2012-02-13 22:31:57',1,'pregame10','pregame10'),(221,'Mind Your Form, and Please Stretch','<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">By Super Trainer Rick</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The importance of form extends all across the fitness spectrum, from performance to aesthetics.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">One of the main foundations of proper form is your core, which includes your abdominals and your back. If you adopt proper form, whether you are a beginner, intermediate, or advanced exerciser, you will achieve a higher success rate at a faster rate.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you\'ve seen a performer in Cirque de Soleil, you understand how form plays a tremendous part in their success! If these incredible performers did not exercise with proper form, their routines would be greatly compromised, or better yet, they wouldn\'t have a routine.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Given what they do, there can be no weak links in their execution of exercises. They understand how all of their muscles work in synergy&mdash;biceps don\'t work without triceps, and backs don&rsquo;t work without chests, etc.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Another important component of good form is full range of motion. Knowing your range of motion means knowing a little something about biomechanics, body positioning, and how your core and stabilizers are always working.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And what about stretching? It is more than touching your toes!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What are the benefits of good form? When it comes to aesthetics, full range of motion will shape (or reshape) your muscles. It is also one of the ways to actively stretch your muscles.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The benefits of this change in your form starts with the&nbsp;strengthening of&nbsp;your tendons, your ligaments, and the tissue that covers and protects the muscles at their insertion points, which is called&nbsp;<em>fascia</em>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;BLAH, BLAH, BLAH,&rdquo;&nbsp;you say. &ldquo;How will that get me a six pack?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Well, first remember:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">THE MORE MUSCLE YOU INCORPORATE WHEN DOING ANYTHING THAT REQUIRES MOTION, THE MORE CALORIES YOU WILL BURN. IF YOU FOLLOW THE NUTRITIONAL ADVICE GIVEN IN MY COLUMN, THE MORE<em>&nbsp;</em><strong>FAT</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>YOU WILL BURN!!! IT\'S THAT SIMPLE!!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The benefits don\'t stop there!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When it comes to performance, you will definitely not only get&nbsp;stronger, but you will feel more powerful, which means you don\'t just have individual muscle strength but because you have been using good form and full range of motion in your exercises you will have&nbsp;evolved into having more flexibility&nbsp;and strength in your stabilizing muscles which equates too a higher performance level, which in turn helps you to burn fat and build muscle in the long term!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now, there are a myriad of exercises and techniques that will help you do this,&nbsp;and some \"fitness professionals\" will tell you that you should&nbsp;be beholden to one form of exercise; some swear only by kettlebells, or boot-camps, spinning<em>, ZUMBA </em>etc<em>.&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">These are all great programs, but solely relying on any one of these, at some point, you&rsquo;re bound to create or exacerbate an imbalance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So, just like with your diet, balance should be a part of your fitness lifestyle<strong>.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','supertrainerrick','2012-02-06 17:39:33','2012-02-06 17:40:06',4,'6fittodate.jpg','image/jpeg',184493,'2012-02-06 17:39:31',0,'2012-02-06 17:40:06',1,'form','form'),(222,'Porn For Ladies','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We might slum it on Sundays in our nasty Uggs, but don&rsquo;t be fooled: We have highly refined taste.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There&rsquo;s room in the closet for not just one, but two pair of Gucci&rsquo;s <span>Ophelie&nbsp;</span>open-toe, two-tone pumps. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why two?&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Because, silly, they come in black AND in cream. &nbsp;Variety is the spice of life.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The tantalizing T-strap boasts gold piping on the 4.5&rdquo; heel and gold chains that lie across your feet and ankles. Meow.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We get all hot in the bonnet looking at them on Fashionindie.com&rsquo;s site. &nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You will, too: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/y2hFzg\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/y2hFzg</a>&nbsp;</span></div>','fashionindie','2012-02-06 18:05:18','2012-02-13 23:38:21',2,'6f