an style=\"font-size: medium;\">Day before, I get an email: &ldquo;What&rsquo;s happening?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Permit me to decode.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>&ldquo;Hi EBK. We had discussed getting together a few weeks back. I wish I could sack up explicitly about whether it&rsquo;s a go, but I am unable because I am so deeply fearful of rejection. I write such a question because I know you, and you will likely reply with, &lsquo;Not much. Hey, are we still on?&rsquo; You&rsquo;ve always been so nice and responsible that I am confident you will. Besides, I love being chased; please chase me. Thanks for taking on the boy role and doing the heavy lifting! AA.&rdquo;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Too bad for him I didn&rsquo;t take the bait, now that <a href=\"polite2\" target=\"_blank\">things are different around here</a></span>.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I played dumb (okay, smart), only answered his question (\"Things are great.\"), and passive-aggressively drove him to frustrating heights until 5:00 pm the next night to force him to actually ASK ME OUT, like a man.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Note that playing dumb/smart yields superb (if not creepy) results.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Smoke blew out of his ears as he parsed my emails:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Why are you so wishy-washy? You don&rsquo;t seem to want to see me. Do you have a boyfriend? Why are you saying we COULD go for a drink? It&rsquo;s such non-committal language. And why a DRINK?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And on and on and on&mdash;until I canceled.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>&ldquo;Sorry our wires kept crossing today. I don&rsquo;t feel it&rsquo;s a good idea to see each other tonight.&rdquo;</strong> No more, no less.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why expose myself to him and his miffed poutiness, spawned by his initial ladylike, &ldquo;Come and get me&rdquo; e-handkerchief toss into my inbox? Remember that if you don&rsquo;t look out for Numero Uno, no one will.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">AA has not rescheduled our date. He is likely waiting for me to send him a bouquet of flowers (and/or perhaps a box of chocolates) with a note, apologizing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Chicks, man.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. quality, vegan, dark chocolate will make her forget whatever you did wrong.</strong></span></p>','tipsandtricks','2012-02-07 20:41:32','2012-04-27 17:39:04',7,'6oped.jpg','image/jpeg',143342,'2012-02-11 14:46:44',0,'2012-04-27 17:39:04',1,'dudelady','dudelady'),(226,'Stability: In Love, Life, and the Gym','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>By Super Trainer Rick</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">From hieroglyphics of warriors on the hunt to the Roman sculptures, to comic book superheroes and the predator in <em>Predator</em>, the one thing that they all had in common was&nbsp;six- and eight packs!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Nothing has changed over time. In most modeling ads, the models are usually posed in some type of position where you can see the streamline length of the torso leading to the chiseled sectioning of the abs. These images go across the board,&nbsp;male and female. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Women don\'t want muffin tops, and guys don&rsquo;t want spare tires and beer bellies. Sure, you do have some special people who are attracted to a nice big belly to keep them warm, but overall, we all can appreciate a nice firm mid-section.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That said, here\'s more about me:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">As of this writing, I am 46-years-old (doesn\'t feel like it!). I have been a certified trainer and massage therapist for 18 years, and in those 18 years, the recurring theme that has made me a successful trainer and helped my clients reach their goals&nbsp;is understanding&nbsp;that&nbsp;<strong>food and form are everything</strong>.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">One thing that will be extremely important for you to recognize in following this&nbsp;post toward getting a tight, defined core is that getting abs isn&rsquo;t just&nbsp;about doing abs. This is just one of the many myths.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Another big myth is about eating. Some people assume they can eat anything that&nbsp;they want and&nbsp;do cardio&nbsp;like crazy and lose body fat and get the results that they want. What usually happens is those people lose weight that is primarily muscle and they tend too look gaunt and drawn in appearance. It\'s also about living a nutritionally healthy lifestyle.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Bruce Lee once said, \"Be water, my friend.\" What he went on to explain in that statement was that water is without form, it conforms to the shape of whatever contains it, it adapts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That\'s deep!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This was the idea behind his self-created martial art, jeet kune do. He basically took a combination of martial-art disciplines and melded them so that he was not beholden to&nbsp;one style. But to master being \"formless,\" he had to master many different weight-training exercises to&nbsp;give him the powerful, explosive, flexible body we all admired.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Going forward, remember these three words: STABILIZE, STABILIZERS and STABILIZING.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your stabilizing muscles are the smaller muscles that lock your body in position while you are doing a specific movement; for example, when you are doing a standing barbell curl, you have to first position your body so that you are not going to cause injury by&nbsp;compromising your lower back, your shoulders or anything in-between! </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Once you adopt my techniques you will be on your way towards learning those techniques and building your dream physique!</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','supertrainerrick','2012-02-13 22:03:20','2012-02-13 22:09:49',4,'exercise.jpg','image/jpeg',16869,'2012-02-13 22:09:25',0,'2012-02-13 22:09:49',1,'8pack','8pack'),(227,'#9 Pre-Game Song: Pitbull with Chris Brown','<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Song: International Love</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s impossible to sit still, or walk without some sort of pop in your step. The duo kills us with song&rsquo;s energetic current. It is contagious. Not to mention, we love our city&rsquo;s top-billed shout-out. Holla.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lyrics:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You put it down like New York City</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> I never sleep</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Wild like Los Angeles</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> My fantasy</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Hotter than Miami</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> I feel the heat</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Ohh Miss International Love</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/CdXesX6mYUE\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>','music','2012-02-13 22:29:00','2012-02-13 22:33:09',6,'13music.jpg','image/jpeg',34083,'2012-02-13 2