en.com, and their well-intended decision to put out a video with tips on how to send girls better text messages.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our feelings on texting as an M.O.:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Impersonal.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Immature.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I&rsquo;m-hiding-behind-160-characters.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No-they-haven&rsquo;t-dropped-yet.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You wanna be that guy?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We sure hope the answer&rsquo;s &ldquo;no.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The AskMen.com instructional guide includes pithy advice such as to not shoot over useless texts (don&rsquo;t say &ldquo;hi&rdquo;), ones that require thoughtful answers (&ldquo;what made you pick your major?&rdquo;), or ones that cross over into Raunchville (&ldquo;wanna get into some trouble later?&rdquo;).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Although we applaud AskMen.com&rsquo;s effort to get dudes to leverage this medium the best way possible, we feel the need to point out the obvious:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Texting is not a substitute for conversation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s for sharing data points.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Rinse and repeat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your pals here ConnectingSexes also wish to remind you that if you&rsquo;re going back and forth with your lady via text, why not just make a time to meet up&mdash;you know, like, on a date&mdash;or talk on your iPhone/Droid/Blackberry/old-school clam for five minutes?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You&rsquo;ll get to know each other a lot better, a lot faster.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And besides, we&rsquo;re sure there&rsquo;s a greater chance you&rsquo;ll get a little sumsum from your date than your Smartphone.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Just sayin&rsquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/yzvRXS\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/yzvRXS</a></span></p>','tipsandtricks','2012-02-17 20:10:06','2012-02-17 20:17:37',7,'13dead-man-texting.jpg','image/jpeg',89738,'2012-02-17 20:12:04',0,'2012-02-17 20:17:37',1,'text101','text101'),(233,'Finishing Touch of Overt Cool ','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When we want accessories with a creative edge, we&rsquo;ve got a new favorite that bangs on that cylinder.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Hedging out the other necklaces and earrings in our bin of bling is Subversive Jewelry.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This line of mesmerizing hardware boasts cool touches culled from hunting- and antique stores, definitely making for a mish-mash of cool perfection.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Want to see more, and read up on the genius behind it, Justin Giunta?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Click to our good friends, FashionIndie: <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/designer-daily-subversive-jewelry-by-justin-giunta/\" target=\"_blank\">http://fashionindie.com/designer-daily-subversive-jewelry-by-justin-giunta/</a></span></p>','fashionindie','2012-02-22 15:24:10','2012-02-22 15:32:17',2,'21fashion.jpg','image/jpeg',34046,'2012-02-22 15:24:09',0,'2012-02-22 15:32:17',1,'subversive','subversive'),(234,'#8 Pre-Game Song: Rihanna with Calvin Harris','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Song: We Found Love</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Romantic words aside, the swells creating the sexy beats have us grooving all the way from the shower to our destination&mdash;and we hope they&rsquo;re playing this tune there, too.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lyrics:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yellow diamonds in the light</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> And we\'re standing side by side</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> As your shadow crosses mine</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> What it takes to come alive</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> It\'s the way I&rsquo;m feeling, I just can\'t deny</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> But I\'ve gotta let it go</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> We found love in a hopeless place</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/tg00YEETFzg\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>','music','2012-02-22 16:03:16','2012-02-22 16:05:31',6,'21music.jpg','image/jpeg',45728,'2012-02-22 16:03:15',0,'2012-02-22 16:05:31',1,'8wefoundlove','8wefoundlove'),(235,'Welcome Back, Tie Bar','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We hear you grumbling every time you wear a tie: It&rsquo;s a noose, you&rsquo;re choking, you&rsquo;re gagging, you&rsquo;re not breathing. Your list of discomforts is endless.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So we&rsquo;re hoping when you slide on a tie bar, these injustices will be somewhat lessened (or eliminated) by this elegant piece because you&rsquo;re so impressed (and therefore distracted) by how much more refined you look&mdash;dashing as you are already.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But it&rsquo;s not just about presentation: The little metal clip is actually functional, keeping your tie neatly on your chest. Never again fear getting flapped in the face when there\'s a bit of breeze.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Curious about this debonair, old-world accessory?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Evolution of Style is all over it: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/ywDsO5\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/ywDsO5</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. hermes ties, please.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-02-22 16:36:31','2012-02-25 20:41:39',3,'21tiebar.jpg','image/jpeg',82838,'2012-02-22 16:36:31',0,'2012-02-25 20:41:39',1,'tiebar','tiebar'),(236,'Star Light, Star Bright','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There are occasions your editor-in-chief thinks about other avenues I may have taken with my career.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What might life have been like as an interior designer? As an astronaut?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To riff the famous quote, it&rsquo;s never too late to infuse into your life what you might have been.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Direct to your front door from California is Uncle Milton&rsquo;s Starfield Projector.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You, too, can mesh your creativity with your inner NASA geek and have ten thousand crystal-clear stars rotate and beam on your walls.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So glad I don&rsquo;t have to quit my day job.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/xZYyqF\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/xZYyqF</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. notwithstanding this recent find, she tries hard not to project.</span></strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-02-23 19:38:35','2012-02-25 01:55:04',8,'21lifestyle.jpg','image/jpeg',16783,'2012-02-23 19:38:35',0,'2012-02-25 01:55:04',1,'stars','stars'),(237,'The Busy Mans Meal Plan','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>By Super Trainer Rick</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Breakfast is the most important meal of your day simply because it jumpstarts your metabolism, which will optimize how you going to burn fat. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Stumped for ideas? </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Here are a few easy morning quickies that are low in fat, but great for protein and energy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Frozen whole grain waffles;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Turkey bacon and a fruit salad;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Oatmeal. If it&rsquo;s instant, make sure it\'s low-sugar;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A whole wheat or whole grain bagel or toast with natural, organic peanut butter;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">An apple;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Protein shake or smoothie with lots of berries, or</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A carton of egg whites.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Drink plain water or coffee with any of these, and you&rsquo;re good to go.</span></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-02-24 22:59:45','2012-02-24 23:01:10',4,'21fit2date.jpg','image/jpeg',283263,'2012-02-24 22:59:43',0,'2012-02-24 23:01:10',1,'manmeal','manmeal'),(238,'Stone-Age Seduction ','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I love boys who don&rsquo;t waste time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You like me, you want to get to know me better, you immediately put on your hunting gear, and you&rsquo;re in pursuit.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My phone rings, or your email plops into my inbox within a day.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;When&rsquo;s our date?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Slam-dunk: you have my interest and respect&mdash;and it makes me think you\'re that much sexier, too.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I think it resurrects my inner cavewoman, who cleaned and cooked the meat, vegetables and berries hunted and gathered by her brave caveman.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Who wants the cave-loser sitting around counting his nuts in-between naps?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not this cave-bitch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In the past couple of weeks, I met two new boys at exactly the same time. Both are good-looking, are athletic, read books, appreciate culture, are successful, and have hobbies.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Take a moment and find a tissue to wipe your tears for me.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">One emailed the night of our date to ask me out again.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The other waited exactly one week to phone me, leaving a limp message.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s been a CRAZY week. And I have family coming in this weekend. So, give me a call after. We&rsquo;ll go out sometime.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Nowhere did I detect even the potential of a loincloth, a club, and a hair-drag to his secluded cave. My Paleolithic, hardwired desires were left dangling.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I had been super-intrigued by this guy&mdash;frankly, feeling far more of that \"click\" with him than the other, who\'s top-tier in his own right&mdash;but he let too much time pass.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Still, it was more than out of sight, out of mind.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">His passivity (a week to call? Doesn&rsquo;t everyone&rsquo;s busy day have five free minutes? Call when you&rsquo;re walking to the can, Mack) and his man-with-the-whatever-lady-you-make-the-plan-whenever message were like pouring water on the embers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You know he\'s not going to pick up the spear before dawn to find me a tiger to skin and roast.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">For boys tempted into setting that dumb three-day timer, you may wish to reconsider said strategy (I use the word loosely) with a glance back to your prehistoric forefathers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Don&rsquo;t lose your dreamgirl to some other dude who&rsquo;s faster at the club&mdash;and maybe with his own, too&mdash;in an attempt to look cool, and desired by many, or all. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It can be a jungle out there.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. tumak, where you at?</strong></span></p>','tipsandtricks','2012-02-25 01:21:11','2012-02-25 01:45:28',7,'21tips.jpg','image/jpeg',76884,'2012-02-25 01:21:11',0,'2012-02-25 01:45:28',1,'stoneage','stoneage'),(239,'The Rainbow Disconnection','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We love make-up and color as much as the next girl. And we admit, we have been known to get a bit carried away at times, achieving an almost paint-by-numbers effect on our faces when we daub on our blush or eye-shadow with too much enthusiasm, or in dim light. Ooops.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But we felt much better about ourselves when scrolling through a roundup of photos courtesy of our FashionIndie friends.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Even in the hands of make-up professionals, gorgeous models are vandalized with Kelly-green blush, tangerine lipstick, and electric eggplant eyeshadow swabbed near their crow&rsquo;s feet (if they had crow&rsquo;s feet, that is; they&rsquo;re only, what, like, 14-years-old?).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Take a look at the patchwork&shy;&ndash;quilt-like faces here: <a href=\"http://bit.ly/w9GIaR\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/w9GIaR</a></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. little satisfies as much as lipgloss and lipstick accumulation. wheeee.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-02-27 18:05:51','2012-02-27 18:10:14',2,'27fashionindie.jpg','image/jpeg',26185,'2012-02-27 18:05:50',0,'2012-02-27 18:10:14',1,'rainbow','rainbow'),(240,'Vive Le Bow Tie','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There were a few moments during Oscar Sunday we felt puzzled as we watched the marathon, self-congratulatory snooze-cast.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Something about the men looked a little bit different.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There was a certain regality about them not previously seen, at least not that we recalled.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What was it exactly that made so many of the Tinsel Town gents outshine their past efforts, and look so elegant?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This year, nearly every guy and his dog (seriously: way to go Uggie from &ldquo;The Artist!&rdquo;) decided to trick himself out with a bow tie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We applaud you for giving your respective stylists the green light.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To those Glitterati who played it dull and did not, just because your tie is black, or silver, or white silk, remember:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Dude, it&rsquo;s still a tie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Step it up, foh rill.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And you:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your Stylegirlfriend suggests you consider adding two bow ties&mdash;real ones that you will have to learn to tie yourself, not some lame clip-on jobs&mdash;to your armamentarium. One for day, one for night.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There is no telling what you&rsquo;ll be awarded with for looking so dashing.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she has always defended the bow tie as a sharp look. she wants a prize for being ahead of the trend.</strong></span></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-02-28 15:01:34','2012-02-28 15:05:48',3,'27style.jpg','image/jpeg',89382,'2012-02-28 15:01:33',0,'2012-02-28 15:05:48',1,'bowtie','bowtie'),(241,'#7 Pre-Game Song: Pharrell With Jay-Z','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Song: Frontin&rsquo;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why?</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This superb 2003 jam still has us popping and bumping, thanks to the phenomenal, scorching talents of Pharrell and Jay-Z. It will never, ever get old. Not to mention, we love the flirty, impish lyrics.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lyrics:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Don\'t wanna sound full of myself or rude</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> But you ain&rsquo;t looking at no other dudes cause you love me</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> (I\'m sorry but.. so sexy)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> So you think about a chance</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> You find yourself trying to do my dance</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Maybe cause you love me (Uh, you do it well)</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/wIBTrN5Odbg\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>','music','2012-02-28 15:51:20','2012-02-28 15:55:34',6,'27music.jpg','image/jpeg',19056,'2012-02-28 15:51:19',0,'2012-02-28 15:55:34',1,'frontin','frontin'),(242,'Daisy Dukes For Everyone','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Fashion dictates that the hemlines of our dresses, shorts and skirts should fall just barely below our unmentionables.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sad, but not everyone should participate. Just because it&rsquo;s in, doesn&rsquo;t mean it&rsquo;s your look.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">However, we&rsquo;re not ones to accept defeat for anybody.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Want to thrust out a thigh that would turn Angelina&rsquo;s face green with envy?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Here&rsquo;s the video that may just do the trick. Brad Pitt not included.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/wUbDc3\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/wUbDc3</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. as you live and breathe, she&rsquo;s on the mat.</strong></span></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-02-28 16:34:52','2012-02-28 16:36:06',4,'27fittodate.jpg','image/jpeg',24971,'2012-02-28 16:34:52',0,'2012-02-28 16:36:06',1,'daisy','daisy'),(243,'Desperately Seeking Chocolate','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You&rsquo;ve been there; we&rsquo;ve been there. Actually, we live there.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Mysteriously and without warning, you&rsquo;re gripped and are in the clutches of a deep and undeniable chocolate craving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You need a hit of that rich, dark stuff&mdash;stat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We know you can do better than simply strap on a feedbag filled with chocolate chips. This&rsquo;ll take maybe a second or two longer, and it&rsquo;s so very worth that extra time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Stir together a from-scratch brownie in a cup, then cook it in Mr. Microwave. The how-to&rsquo;s courtesy of our friends at Chow.com. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You\'ll be feeding that beast before you know it, and it\'ll be pretty special in your nice mug.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In fact, if you&rsquo;re hosting a date at home when your cocoa craving strikes, you can front all domestic, sweet and thoughtful, and make a second one.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Because we know you&rsquo;re not sharing.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/zaebFD\" target=\"_blank\">http://bit.ly/zaebFD</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. 70% and higher, please.</strong></span></p>','lifestyle','2012-02-29 17:50:28','2012-02-29 18:00:01',8,'27lifestyle.jpg','image/jpeg',176536,'2012-02-29 17:50:25',0,'2012-02-29 18:00:01',1,'brownie','brownie'),(244,'PS: Get Well Soon','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I have been out on a couple of dates in the past week.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">On both of them, I have been sick.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Disclaimer: Never would I foist myself if too ill and/or contagious onto healthy, unsuspecting, and virile gentlemen. Rude.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Okay, so, I was JUST getting sick on the first. I had the sniffles when he picked me up. As our evening together wore on, I was coughing and sneezing my way through a few terrific jazz sets&mdash;to say nothing about my incessantly watering eyes that blurred my view of the stage. I played it cool about my fast-onset flu, enjoyed the evening in spite of it, and let him know, as the clock struck midnight, it was time to get a cab.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">By my second date (different guy), I was much better. The worst seemed to have dissipated. I was ever-so-discreetly stuffy with a sore throat, although still somewhat deaf. By hour three together, I had to politely excuse myself from our rolicking good night, saying thanks, but the last strains of my flu had caught up with me&mdash;shame. I think he was okay with it; I couldn\'t really hear what he said and my lip-reading skills are weak.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In both cases, my cold/flu was an inconvenience. It was not a Drama Queen moment, and it should and will never be.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I wish I could say the same for these sweet and well-meaning boys.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Date One constantly asked me (loudly in a quiet jazz bar) if I was okay, giving me a million blessings (appreciated) for my marathon sneezing sessions. He relentlessly shoved a pocket-pack of tissues in my direction, and wondered if we should get tea, or did I want some from the bar? Was I sure? His email the next day wished me the best of health, and how was I doing? Remember: citrus and ginger tea, just like he advised me in the cab!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Date Two followed up to our date the next day with a sweet email&mdash;which applauded me for \"being such a trooper\" coming out with the flu, that he hopes I get better soon, and that he is sure I will be feeling much, much healthier the next time he sees me. This was after he joked (twice) while dropping me off that perhaps I was saying I was fluish so I would not have to kiss him goodnight.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Both boys are coming from the kindest and most caring place. I\'m really touched. Their concern means a lot. I am lucky to go out with such upstanding fellows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not to put too fine a point on it, but sometimes the best of intentions can actually make someone feel bad.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If someone\'s just a little bit sick, don\'t make a big deal about it. Don\'t call attention to it.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">While you\'re out, no need to hen-peck with, \"How are you now? How about now? What about now?\"&nbsp;Don\'t be annoying. Just let Sickypants know they\'re in charge: you\'ll hail them a cab (boy or girl; this courtesy knows no gender) when they give you a sign. Then drop it.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And there\'s no need to make the person feel like a martyr the next day.&nbsp;It\'s not romantic, or flirtatious. Simply, \"Good times last night. Let me know how you are when you\'re up for it, and if you need something,\" does a great job: you give a damn and you\'re still fun.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Just like your invalid will be again soon; so make sure they\'ll want to see you first.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she\'s at 95%.</span></strong></p>','tipsandtricks','2012-03-03 04:58:42','2012-03-03 05:13:31',7,'27tips.jpg','image/jpeg',303044,'2012-03-03 04:58:40',0,'2012-03-03 05:13:31',1,'sick','sick'),(245,'Go Out With a Bangle','<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The right accessory adds a lot of spirit to an outfit.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When we saw a gorgeous, colorful, beaded cuff, courtesy of our friends at FashionIndie, we instantly slipped into party mindset. Its pretty little picture was vibing good times right through our computer screen.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And at just $13.99, we have no trouble fantasizing that our bank accounts can easily accomodate a ticket to Ibiza for some all-night dancing, and all-day sun-bathing.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But because we are so responsible, we\'ll just wear the bracelet around town for an insta-fun wardrobe twist (until that air fare sale).&nbsp;</span>