',4,'13fittodate.jpg','image/jpeg',129844,'2012-03-13 15:27:43',0,'2012-03-13 15:28:04',1,'springcleanse','springcleanse'),(254,'#5 Pre-Game Song: Hot Chelle Rae With New Boyz','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Song: I Like It Like That</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why?</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yeah, this song&rsquo;s got as much pop and fizz as that can of Mountain Dew, but we love the smile it puts on our faces&mdash;and who doesn&rsquo;t run up to the person with the best grin in the room? The lyrics are so cheeky and cheery, and the New Boyz cut-in gives this jam that street edge we crave.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lyrics:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I like it like that!</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Hey, windows down, chillin&rsquo; with the radio on</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> I like it like that!</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Yeah, one more time, I can never get enough of everybody</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Sing it right back, I like it like that!</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> (I like it like that, I like it like that)</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/lbvzkdYqJDc\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she likes it like that, too.</strong></p>','music','2012-03-14 14:58:57','2012-03-14 14:59:23',6,'13music.jpg','image/jpeg',30206,'2012-03-14 14:58:57',0,'2012-03-14 14:59:23',1,'5likedat','5likedat'),(255,'The Leopard\'s Wardrobe','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am a cautious optimist.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In our last episode, <a href=\"dudelady/\" target=\"_blank\">AA seriously messed up</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He decided to take on the girl&rsquo;s role (that would be mine), expecting me to chase him about our date.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I canceled instead&mdash;not to teach him any sort of a lesson&mdash;but because I didn&rsquo;t want to be around his grumpy self. He was pissed I wasn\'t responding to his button-pushing, and his need to be the lady (in a manner of speaking).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Well, guess what, kids?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It didn&rsquo;t take long for someone to come knockin&rsquo; for another chance, and an explanation.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It was more than my pleasure, over his persisting emails, to clarify for him precisely why keeping company with him that night did not appeal&mdash;beyond that e.b.k. + Mr. Bad Attitude= no, never, ever.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Gentle male readers, I offer the clarification to you, too.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1. When you make plans with a girl (applause!), your work\'s not over.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2. Don&rsquo;t drop off the face of the earth until date night. Stay in touch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">3. Don&rsquo;t expect her to ping you to confirm. That&rsquo;s your job.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">AA paid very close attention. I think that&rsquo;s called listening.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Since then, he has been taking my pulse nearly daily, and impressing that he is looking forward to seeing me, and that he misses me. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Flattery doesn\'t get you everywhere, but it helps.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our date is upcoming, and the big litmus test will be immediately before.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Maybe AA will maintain this aggressive, manly tear I like so much. I want a plan out of him, not a &ldquo;What&rsquo;s happening?&rdquo; email by way of confirmation on the eve.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I have high hopes this leopard could morph just a little bit more.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. her bin of extra chances is nearly empty.</strong></p>','tipsandtricks','2012-03-15 21:41:50','2012-03-16 15:59:06',7,'13tips.jpg','image/jpeg',61090,'2012-03-15 21:45:43',0,'2012-03-16 15:59:06',1,'spots','spots'),(256,'Hows Tuesday of Never?','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you can believe it, a high-school sweetheart magnanimously put on his matchmaking hat for me.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;EBK, have you ever met my friend, RB?&rdquo; he asked, before going in for the hard sell. &ldquo;He makes piles of cash, has a Ducati, he&rsquo;s into extreme sports, and you guys both love to travel.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I bit. &ldquo;Dude, thank you. Fire it up.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Don&rsquo;t kid yourselves: looks fade, but at least for now, his &ldquo;I Make Ryan Gosling Look Ugly&rdquo; <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/ConnectingSexes/125066887588260/\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> photos boosted his stock even higher.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And then, there was The Crash.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">After we were e-introduced, it took precisely 22 emails to confirm a day, time and place. There was no casual, flirty banter. It was pure scheduling.&nbsp; See the crusted drool on my keyboard? It&rsquo;s from falling asleep due to boredom over his lack of e-courtship/warming me up to want to see him.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span>Get comfy.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A Thursday plan to meet at a pass&eacute; halfway-ish-ish place for a cocktail (not cool, but acceptable; see below) turns into a Tuesday plan, returns to a Thursday plan&mdash;which he cancels that day because he got swamped with work. Hey, it happens.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;No problem,&rdquo; I write, &ldquo;Another time.&rdquo; Perhaps the next Tuesday of likely never, at the rate we were going.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What a surprise: 20 minutes before the originally scheduled 9:00 p.m. meet-up time, my phone rings.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">RB could meet after all. Could I? Uhm, no. Last time I checked, I wasn&rsquo;t a surgeon on call. We settle on Sunday at 7:00 p.m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Saturday night, RB texts, requesting the pleasure of my company IN HIS NEIGHBORHOOD (nowhere near mine) for our date.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I interrupt my tale with some free advice.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"dudelady/\" target=\"_blank\">Guys, don&rsquo;t act like girls</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you will not be a full-court gentleman and either pick up your date, or meet her somewhere that&rsquo;s a block or three from her place, at least compromise and find somewhere halfway-ish&mdash;and closer to her.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Girls, do not accept girlish behavior from guys.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So, in my gracious and polite way, I refuse, by reminding him of his GREAT idea to meet at the &ldquo;meh&rdquo; compromise locale. He accepts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Be not shocked: 30 minutes before our rendezvous, my phone rings.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;I lost track of time,&rdquo; RB says. &ldquo;Can we make it 7:30?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Pause. &ldquo;Sure.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Great! I&rsquo;ll call you if I&rsquo;m any more delayed!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What a prince.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I make a decision (<a href=\"polite2/\" target=\"_blank\">on the heels of an earlier one&nbsp;</a>) that if a call comes in announcing further tardiness, we were going to enjoy cocktails, separately. Lawd, let RB nut up and show up on-time (whenever that was; who could keep track anymore?).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Alas, 7:25 p.m., and RB texts: &ldquo;In a cab. Going to be late.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You know that means he JUST slid his (no doubt perfect and toned) arse into a taxi, and was JUST making his way downtown.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">After several deep, yogi breaths, I reply:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;I&rsquo;m sorry to hear that. I value punctuality. I am kind of annoyed. Maybe we should reschedule.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He texts back something about bad traffic (which would not have mattered had he not left five minutes before show time) but more importantly, that he understood, and his apologies.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I know I will never hear from him again, and I will never reach out to him.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Look, you and I do not need another reason to hop on the group dating bandwagon (shameless plug!). It is a fab opportunity to meet many, and find the one, just like our Connectingsexes slogan says. You step into a room of potential first dates, and then you zero in on the cream of the crop, all in a fun, social environment.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">How might group-dating have saved me, personally, from wasting my Sunday evening, and from getting irritated, all things being equal?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Simple.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When mingling and socializing with maybe-dates, I also get to watch these same guys. I see how they interact with other girls, and with each other&mdash;yep: it\'s information-gathering, people; <span>not just from when the dude is hanging with me, or by hearing all about how super he is from a third party</span>.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Given what I learned the hard and time-wasting way about RB&mdash;he&rsquo;s flaky, he&rsquo;s inconsiderate, he is unwilling and unable to keep a schedule, and he&rsquo;s just not into dating right now, or he&rsquo;d have made a semblance of an effort&mdash;he likely would&rsquo;ve shown up with only five minutes left in the group-dating night, if at all. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. love is easy.</strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2012-03-20 19:57:45','2012-03-21 01:21:48',5,'19tales.jpg','image/jpeg',10746,'2012-03-20 19:57:45',0,'2012-03-21 01:21:48',1,'never','never'),(257,'The OTHER Sweat Suit','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Do you soak through your suit jackets and shirts with wet moons that run down to your belt?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Before you can say &ldquo;Old Spice,&rdquo; summer is going to smack your face, and it will only get worse.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our pal at Evolution of Style is here to help you navigate your next purchases. He has pointers and pictures for exactly what you must seek out so you won&rsquo;t destroy another sport coat with your juicy pits.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Click here, and get ready to wave hello with confidence.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\