m;\">Because sharing is caring, we encourage you to click below so you, too, can revive your coiffure.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/spring-hair-survival-revive-refresh/\" target=\"_blank\">FashionIndie Hair Help</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. sometimes, \"thank you\" just isn\'t enough.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-03-21 20:20:18','2012-03-21 20:21:43',2,'19fashion.jpg','image/jpeg',30866,'2012-03-21 20:20:17',0,'2012-03-21 20:21:43',1,'winterhair','winterhair'),(261,'Ice Coffee The Right Way','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Ah, spring. We love you profoundly.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You bring sleevelessness, thin jackets, and budding trees (achoo). We gratefully hail your arrival with the official switch from hot to iced coffee. And we love getting our buzz on first thing in the morning.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">On that tip, sure, we could keep opening our wallets every day to watch the dollars fly for a frosty, not-too-light, of our warm-weather kryptonite.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But thanks to our friends over at Imbibe Magazine, we don&rsquo;t have to.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They have saved us both cash and grief (how many weak, lackluster iced coffees do you wish you hadn&rsquo;t slurped?) with a fascinating how-to article on brewing the perfect one in the comfort and privacy of our own homes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now that we&rsquo;ve been schooled, we&rsquo;re rightfully super-picky about who, other than our fabulous selves, gets to make us one.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Click here for the DIY.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.imbibemagazine.com/Iced-Coffee-How-To/\" target=\"_blank\">Ice Coffee Like a Pro</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br />e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she needs a 12-step for coffee.</p>','tipsandtricks','2012-03-22 14:42:58','2012-03-22 15:08:08',7,'19tips.jpg','image/jpeg',9258,'2012-03-22 14:42:58',0,'2012-03-22 15:08:08',1,'icedcoffee','icedcoffee'),(262,'Im a Travelin Man','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why do girls seem to have the edge up on guys when it comes to toiletry bags?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our well-organized kits (fine, some weigh as much as a human head) have everything a body could want or need; no wonder you keep asking us for toothpaste, deodorant, lip balm, sunscreen&hellip;we won&rsquo;t go on.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">With weekend-away season on the short horizon, we kiss the hands of our buddies at Valetmag.com.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They have pulled together a page&mdash;complete with photos, making it all the easier&mdash;of dopp-kit musts, and recommendations for which bags are best. Blessings.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now we can breathe a little easier, knowing you&rsquo;re totally self-sufficient when you&rsquo;re gone with the boys.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.valetmag.com/the-handbook/personal-care/the-dopp-kit/index.php/\" target=\"_blank\">Dopp Kit Help</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she admires a man who\'s independent.</strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-03-22 15:58:08','2012-03-22 15:58:26',8,'19lifestyle.jpg','image/jpeg',27901,'2012-03-22 15:58:08',0,'2012-03-22 15:58:26',1,'doppkit','doppkit'),(263,'Hot Legs For Guys And Girls','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Okay, let&nbsp;me address a big problem I&rsquo;ve seen with a lot of guys.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They don\'t like to work their legs.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This is a bad thing for a few reasons, but let\'s start with the aesthetic ones.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">First, women love men&rsquo;s legs. They see a guy with sticks, and wonder if he had been wheelchair-bound to achieve such minimal proportions&mdash;and trust me, they are looking at our butts just as much as we look at theirs! (I\'ll get to your butts later, ladies.)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The next reason is performance-based. Your legs consist of your&nbsp;quadriceps (front of your thigh), your calves, hamstrings (back of your thigh), and the largest muscle in the body, the gluteus, or your butt.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">All of these muscles work together to basically stand you up and sit you down, and everything in-between, such as running, jumping and every other lower-body motion.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Let&rsquo;s go over the basic leg movements that use all of those muscles, always with the focus on 1. legs, and 2. how they will work your core to put you on your way to an<strong> </strong>eight-pack<strong>.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now: To the ladies.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Just as I tell guys that there no \"girl\" exercises, I tell women that the exercises that&nbsp;they thought of as &ldquo;guy&rdquo; exercises are the same ones that are going to strengthen, lengthen,&nbsp;and tone their legs, butt and calves. The myth that their legs will get big comes from&nbsp;the&nbsp;body making muscle faster than it starts&nbsp;losing body fat, and the legs seem to get bigger until the metabolism kicks in and body fat gets used.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The myth of the girl exercises comes from some of the old school \"isolation&rdquo; exercises like inner thigh and butt movements, but they are made more effective when done in conjunction with other exercises that incorporate those muscles with a full range of motion.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">SQUATS</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Squats are as important for your legs as water is to plants.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They involve all of the major muscles in the lower leg, yet most guys don\'t do them, and women usually think of them as a guy&rsquo;s exercise, or an exercise that will make their thighs big. This might be true if you\'re constantly lifting heavy weight, and eating enough calories to make that happen. That wouldn\'t happen overnight, so don&rsquo;t worry.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Another big reason why men and women don\'t do squats is because of&nbsp;back or knee problems, and/or a fear of causing back or knee problems; but standing up and sitting down are things that we do every day&mdash;basically a squat. Over the years, I have helped many a knee problem by simply correcting squat form.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> At the top of the movement, you are at an angle. Your feet are positioned slightly in front of your hips, so you are essentially&nbsp;leaning back so that as you descend, you are pushing your butt back as if you are sitting into a chair, bending at the waist and knees at the same time so that your shoulders stay in line with your hips, and your knees stay in line with your ankles, which helps you push through your heels, helping to engage the hips and not only the thighs.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This is important because a lot of knee issues occur from the quads being too tight or too&nbsp;strong, and the hamstrings too weak,&nbsp;which pulls awkwardly on the kneecap, often inflaming the joint, or the surrounding muscles.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Make sure as you make the transition&nbsp;ascending to&nbsp;put more focus on pushing through your heels. This&nbsp;mechanically tells your glutes and hamstrings to help your thighs in the process of standing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">FINISHING TIPS</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Keep your chest up nice and high to exaggerate the natural arch in the back. It tells the muscles along your spine to support you and your abs. This means your core is working. </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> As you come up out of the squat while pushing through the heels, put your brain in your butt and feel the engagement of your glutes. Don\'t worry: over time, the connection will become second nature.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">STRETCHES</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Another big issue when it comes to the legs is lack of flexibility, which will cause or exacerbate problems.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lower-body issues tend to stem from three places: back, knee, and hip problems. All three can usually be helped and prevented by a few simple stretches.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">First is the back. You have a muscle in front at the top of your thighs called the psoas, and you also have the hip flexors. These two muscles work to help to curl your hips up to your torso, and your torso to your hips. The psoas wraps around and attaches by your lower back; so if your thighs are tight, chances are the psoas will be tight, thereby putting pressure on the lower back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Here are a few stretches that will address that issue.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> First, position yourself in a lunge position. Keep your torso very upright, lean your body far forward, toward the forward leg, while contracting the glutes on the opposite side. (This will help relax the muscle you&rsquo;re trying to stretch.) Do this slowly and deliberately; you want to feel the stretch at the bend of your waist, not just in the thighs. You can also take this stretch to the next level by putting the trailing leg&nbsp;laces side down on a bench, which will elevate your leg behind you, or if you are home, on the couch. Follow the same steps, and you will feel the stretch more deeply throughout your thigh. Hold the stretch for a few seconds, release it, and repeat it at least twice, or until you can feel you are not getting any more range. These will help to stretch your thighs hip flexors and psoas muscles, helping to relieve lower-back tightness and knee tightness.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Second is for your glutes, hips and lower back.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Have a seat on the edge of a bench, or chair. Sit as if you were going to cross your legs, but only rest the foot and ankle of one leg on top of the knee of the opposite leg. Chances are you are going to be really tight when you try this stretch. You will improve with consistency. Don\'t hold your breath and use the same hold/release technique as described in the first stretch.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Keep in mind that the exercises you will be doing are primarily active-stretch exercises, which means your development of your full range of motion will be stretching your muscles as you strengthen them.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','supertrainerrick','2012-03-26 21:36:31','2012-03-26 21:39:53',4,'26fit2date.jpg','image/jpeg',68284,'2012-03-26 21:36:30',0,'2012-03-26 21:39:53',1,'hotlegs','hotlegs'),(264,'Miami\'s Fashion Vice','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Ah, Miami Beach.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We love your palm trees, your retro hotels, your beaches, and your mind-blowing shopping.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So what is it exactly about the fashion trends popping in our favorite American getaway that leave us stumped, trying to puzzle how we can look as