of my heart, for realsies, after countless failed and faked attempts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In our last episode, <a href=\"spots/\" target=\"_blank\">AA was doing things right</a> (or much better). My inbox filled with his witty emails. Daily. They were manly. He pursued me: &ldquo;I want to see you.&rdquo; Shivers!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">His magician-like disappearing acts, reemerging <a href=\"dudelady/\" target=\"_blank\">only to act all girly</a>, expecting me to chase him for our plans, also seemed a distant memory. He was confirming in plain English&mdash;none of this passive-aggressive, ask about another topic/send a link to a video to get me to plan our night out crap. Newp. My cautious optimism morphed into brazen confidence. &nbsp;At last, after years on a nauseating ride to Nowhere, we were on track to Somewhere.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Or not.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sadly, my ConnectingSexes Sweeties, your devoted editor is suddenly hit in the teeth with profoundly life-changing news.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I phone AA, Mr. Now-Dependable.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He comes over, and takes me out for liquid solace and some dinner to soak it up. He is wise and comforting and pragmatic and sweet and encourages me to cry. I am not one to shed tears (&ldquo;Blue Valentine&rdquo; a notable exception), so this is a major accomplishment.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When he drops me off, he says he will not harass me over the upcoming days, but he will be sure to email me to check on how I am. I tell him, Good. Passionate kisses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Then AA vanishes. He evaporates.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not into the night. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I mean, I don&rsquo;t hear from him.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My iBoyfriend shows nothing from AA. No emails. No iMessages. I understand he does not phone: He didn&rsquo;t want to disrupt me, and he hates the phone. It makes him choke.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">One week later, I log on to GChat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Pronto, an email hits: &ldquo;Hi. How are you doing?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That&rsquo;s it? After what just happened? After a week goes by? After our years?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span>I simply answer his question. He doesn\'t respond. Time has ticked away. Nuffin\'.</span><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Stab in my heart.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And yet, what a favor:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My crisis reveals how AA really feels about our relationship, and me.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Nevermind what he would be like as a boyfriend again when it&rsquo;s not all funsy-wunsy, AA gets an F as a friend.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It saves me the trouble of jawing any speech that involves the hollow, standard-issue BS of, &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s just be/I think we would work better as&hellip;&rdquo; if ever we should talk again.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"spots/\" target=\"_blank\">The leopard really does have just that one outfit.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. there is finally room at the inn.</strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2012-04-11 14:27:51','2012-04-11 17:44:41',5,'11tales.jpg','image/jpeg',29616,'2012-04-11 14:38:43',0,'2012-04-11 17:44:41',1,'silverlinings','silverlinings'),(273,'Andrew: \"Numbers Don\'t Lie\"','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Local Celebrity: Andrew Rivera, 21.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><em>We&rsquo;ve known Rivera (photo, right) for what feels like forever. Talk about your New York story: Rivera went from working retail to an internship at </em>Complex<em> magazine before his impressive gig today&mdash;managing rising-star Harlem-born rap artist, Perrion.</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">Connecting Sexes</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: So, Andrew, thank you for joining our Local Celebrity interview, brought to you by ConnectingSexes.com. Let\'s start off with, &ldquo;Where are you from?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>Andrew Rivera</strong>: New York City. It&rsquo;s the best city on Earth. I mean, I know I</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">haven&rsquo;t been to every other city on the planet, and I&rsquo;m sure if you&rsquo;re</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">not from New York, you&rsquo;re reading this and you&rsquo;re totally like, &ldquo;Typical</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">New Yorker arrogance!&rdquo; You&rsquo;re right, it is.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>CS</strong>: So you\'ve grown up near [rap artist] Perrion? </span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>AR</strong>: Yeah, I&rsquo;m from Harlem, 136th Street, west side. Some people don&rsquo;t</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">consider that Harlem, but it sure as fuck isn&rsquo;t the Heights, and I&rsquo;m</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">not calling it Morning Side Heights. That name is for Columbia University pitch/scout meetings. I&rsquo;ve never met another person who grew up in my neighborhood that&rsquo;s called it anything but Harlem, and somehow, everyone who isn&rsquo;t from here thinks it&rsquo;s something else.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>CS</strong>: How did you meet Perrion?</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>AR</strong>: I met Perry when he was a drummer for a band called 5 Cases of a</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Tragedy. It was like Screamo/Emo music. Perry was always the one of</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">the group who impressed me the most. The band was cool for me to see. It was a bunch of Hispanic kids playing rock and even just a few years ago. That was somewhat weird for dudes to grasp.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Anyway, Perry was dating this girl for like a week, and I ended up dating her for two years [Laughs.] We would go on to hate each other for years until we realized that we were destined to work with each other. I used to give this kid stink eye. Now I&rsquo;m shooting videos in France with him. C&rsquo;est la vie, hunh?</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>CS</strong>: How are you keeping Perrion front-and-center? Any shows we should look out for?</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">AR</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: We\'re currently working on putting together a set different shows in New York. Rather than do a bunch of shitty New York shows like a lot of up and coming artists, we try to do a few big shows every now and then. My main focus is always online presence, marketing and the music of course. Keep checking </span><a style=\"font-size: medium;\" href=\"http://www.highoffmusic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">highoffmusic.com</a><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: What do you consider your best accomplishments as a team?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>AR</strong>: Putting ourselves in a position where we can achieve the things that we have in such a short amount of time with only three people: Perrion, co-manager Olivia Newton-Atwell, and myself. A year ago, I was just listening to one of Perry&rsquo;s songs, but now he&rsquo;s got three projects done, his videos don&rsquo;t do less than 10,000 views&mdash;and dude, we have fans in Sweden. My personal favorite accomplishment is my parents saluting my work, but this first year has really been amazing.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>CS</strong>: What was your favorite performance thus far?</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>AR</strong>: It would have to be Atlanta. Perry opened up for A$AP Rocky, and at</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">one point, some haters started booing him. It felt like the longest moment of my life. It wasn&rsquo;t long at all, he would go on to rock the show, but for five seconds&hellip;man, my heart was in my throat. I couldn&rsquo;t breathe and it felt like hell. We weren&rsquo;t used to that at all. Perry did crowd-surfs in France and we were treated like rap stars, but Atlanta taught me so much in five seconds. I&rsquo;ll take an education over fun any day of the week, which is odd because I&rsquo;m a college dropout.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>CS</strong>: Dates. Advise. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>AR</strong>: I hate ordinary, boring mapped out dates. [They have] to be one of the most awkward things on the planet. Do what good Americans do, find a dressing room at some with your lady or flooz and get it goin\'. Nah, just kidding. I don\'t know, but fellas, of all ages, don\'t ever,&nbsp;<em>ever</em>,&nbsp;<strong><em>EVER</em></strong>&nbsp;take a girl to a movie on a first date. Forget the fact that that horse has been beaten to death: you can\'t talk at a movie. You can\'t get to know the girl, chances are the movie isn\'t worth your money, and from what I hear, the whole \"penis in the popcorn\" thing is illegal. Just chillin&rsquo; with a girl is how I roll.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: So most important question, </span><em style=\"font-size: medium;\">The Blueprint</em><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> or </span><em style=\"font-size: medium;\">Reasonable Doubt</em><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>AR</strong>: <em>The Blueprint</em>, no question. I know I put myself at risk for the backpackers and hip-hop heads who think they&rsquo;re better rap fans than</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> everyone because it&rsquo;s 2012 and they listen to KRS-One and EPMD over</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Drake and Wiz Khalifa, but that&rsquo;s bullshit. In my opinion, <em>The&nbsp;Blueprint</em> is the best album Jay-Z has done. It was the perfect moment</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">in his life and career. He achieved everything he wanted to when he</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">made <em>Reasonable Doubt</em>. Look at the album art of <em>Reasonable Doubt</em>. Does that look like some dirty-ass backpacker? No. Jay was chasing paper and luxury from Day One! Anyone who tells you different is an idiot.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Moving from that, the production is outrageous. You&rsquo;re talking about</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Just Blaze and Kanye West producing in their prime. You have Jay-Z</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> banging out club hits like &ldquo;H to the Izzo,&rdquo; &ldquo;Girls, Girls, Girls,&rdquo; and</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> street anthems like &ldquo;U Don&rsquo;t Know,&rdquo; &ldquo;Never Change,&rdquo; and &ldquo;Heart of the</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">City.&rdquo; His raps were developed. His sound was incredible. The flow of</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">the album was amazing and come on, &ldquo;Renegade.&rdquo; Enough said.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Men lie, women lie, numbers don&rsquo;t. In a time when people actually</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> bought records, <em>The Blueprint</em> sold 426,000 copies on 9/11! &nbsp;Sure, Jay had elevated status because he had done well before, but I don&rsquo;t care about Michael Jordan&rsquo;s first year, I care about his prime.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>CS</strong>: I lied. This is the most important question: &ldquo;Why are you a Local Celebrity?&rdquo;</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>AR</strong>: Damn, that&rsquo;s hard to answer without sounding like an arrogant</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> douche. It&rsquo;s dope to be mentioned as a Local Celebrity, and it&rsquo;s</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> awesome to do interviews, but I don&rsquo;t know, I&rsquo;m not there yet. I got</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> recognized by a kid in Starbucks, and in France at a meet and greet. That&rsquo;s cool. The other cool thing for me is how often people send me</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> their music, videos, and their other stuff and then ask me for my</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> opinion or ask me questions on how to push it. It honestly makes me</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> feel like I&rsquo;ve done something that someone wants to emulate and apply</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">it to their own career because Perry&rsquo;s career is doing well.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>CS</strong>: Let&rsquo;s go over this whole thing. You have been to France; the</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Mixtape, From Paris With Love, was incredibly well received; in April,</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Perrion is headlining his own show at the Velvet Jones in Santa Barbara, and 42,000+ hits on the &ldquo;Fire Ant&rdquo; video. What is your next set of goals?</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <strong>AR</strong>: Well, I&rsquo;m going to do what I do every night, Stefan: Try to take over</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">the world! I know that&rsquo;s a joke to a lot of people, but I interned at</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Complex Magazine for two years and those guys are really seizing the</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Internet daily. Over there they teach you all about numbers. Every</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> time someone clicks a Perrion song, video, link, etc. etc., it means</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I&rsquo;m doing my job right. Going into this a year ago, Perry had about</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">500 fans on Facebook, barely any Twitter followers, no music videos,</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">100 views on his songs, and no blog love. Now he&rsquo;s got almost 3,000</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Facebook fans, 1,800 Twitter followers, 42,000 views on a video,</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">almost 200,000 total video views. We&rsquo;re getting on music blogs that</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">we&rsquo;ve always loved: Hypetrak, Earmilk, HipHopUpdate, The Masked</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Gorilla and Vibe To This. Clothing brands fuck with us; Mishka</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> included him in their 2012 Spring Look Book. This sounds like me</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">listing off my accomplishments, and you may think, &ldquo;Who gives a fuck about how many people like you on Facebook?!&rdquo; But numbers don&rsquo;t lie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Giving a fuck about those numbers and figuring out ways to make them</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">multiply is what got me here. It&rsquo;s what got me to France, and it&rsquo;s what&rsquo;s going to get us our first million, I promise.</span><br /> <br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> My next set of goals is to double up on anything I&rsquo;ve already done. Okay, we did 42,000 on &ldquo;Fire Ant;&rdquo; let&rsquo;s do 84,000 or more on &ldquo;Gettin&rsquo; It.&rdquo; We hit five big blogs with this video. Let&rsquo;s hit 10 big blogs with the next one. We got shows done in France? Let&rsquo;s get a</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">European tour going.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To some people, it sounds like a stretch, but damn, I didn&rsquo;t think I would be here now, so why not? The worst thing that happens is I come up short, but in my own mind, I&rsquo;m ahead and I can afford to lose a little bit.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2012 is all about making calculated risks and gaining the most from any experience, whether it&rsquo;s successful or an epic failure.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>Stefan Dienstag is a born-and-bred New Yorker. He also thinks The Blueprint is the superior album.</strong></span></p>','localcelebrity','2012-04-11 18:45:58','2012-04-12 02:49:02',9,'11local.jpg','image/jpeg',128737,'2012-04-11 18:45:57',0,'2012-04-12 02:49:02',1,'andrew','andrew'),(274,'Feeling Loopy','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We get a little misty-eyed when we think back to that afternoon Dad taught us to tie our shoelaces.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Maybe because of the touching child-parent bonding moment.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Maybe because we remember how sore and arthritic our little fingers felt after 537 attempts at getting one bow&mdash;one bow that sucked.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Today, we are stepping it up several thousand notches.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Using our now deft opposable thumbs, our kicks are laced and looped in ways we&rsquo;d never previously dreamed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Want to trick out your shoes, and make them look all growns-up and cool?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Cheggit:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://lokwi.com/item/2956/\" target=\"_blank\">Make my kicks cooler.</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she is still fascinated by velcro.</strong></p>','tipsandtricks','2012-04-12 14:54:21','2012-04-12 14:55:08',7,'11tips.jpg','image/jpeg',64461,'2012-04-12 14:54:21',0,'2012-04-12 14:55:08',1,'loopy','loopy'),(275,'Hot-Bag Contest!','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What would summer be without music shows&mdash;and more to the point, the perfect handbag to take along?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Snaps go to Moni Moni, who make the ideal. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Brilliantly dreamed up in Southern Cali, and crafted in bella Italia, their latest for festival-going girlies has a 70s vibe with today&rsquo;s metal decals to bring it up to speed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And thanks to our awesome FashionIndie friends, there&rsquo;s a contest in full swing: You can win one!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Does life get brighter?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Click on their page for the deets.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/win-moni-moni-studded-gypsy-bag/\r\ntarget=\">I want that bag! Contest info, please. </a></span><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. there is always room for another bag.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-04-16 15:10:43','2012-04-16 15:13:50',2,'16fashion.jpg','image/jpeg',29695,'2012-04-16 15:10:43',0,'2012-04-16 15:13:50',1,'contest','contest'),(276,'Work Out And Mean It','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I would rather someone hit me repeatedly with a stick than make me do steady-state cardio.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Okay, a slight exaggeration, but not too far-fetched.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">For one thing, just sitting on a bike, elliptical, or simply walking on the treadmill will probably not get you lean enough to see your abdominals! Coupled with the fact that it\'s plain-old boring for most, this type of cardio doesn\'t do much to raise your fitness level, which is essential to really lose and/or maintain body fat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Put Your Back Into It</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Too many times, I see people in the gym just walking on the treadmill without even using a hint of an incline. People, come on: You walk every day. Your body has pretty much adapted to this workload. If you are able to read a magazine, or even a big, awkward newspaper, THEN YOU&rsquo;RE NOT WORKING HARD ENOUGH!&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your body is an adaptive tool. If this were considered exercise, it would have to be an intensified version of that walk&mdash;such as a big pump of the arms, use of the incline, etc.,&nbsp;so that your body says, &ldquo;Hey, I\'m doing something a little tougher than usual; I&rsquo;d better burn more calories because I&rsquo;m working harder!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I often hear trainers speak of how unnecessary it is to do \"isolation\" movements, such as curls or triceps, lateral raises and similar exercises. They usually preach this because they are speaking about moves that have more metabolism-boosting qualities, such as dead lifts, squats, presses, etc.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">These exercises are called multi-joint exercises simply because, just as you might assume, it means that more than one joint is working; therefore, more than one muscle group works. With an exercise like curls, only one muscle is working mechanically. Interestingly, you need many more muscles to stabilize the body to perform just one curl. Once you adopt and master the form that it takes to properly stabilize the body, you will burn a lot more calories performing this \"simple\" exercise.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Use Your Core, Use Your Mind</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">One thing that I consistently hear when people ask about working their core is, &ldquo;Which abominal exercises should I do?&rdquo; My answer is always a quick tutorial about how your body doesn\'t work WITHOUT using your core. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">One of my relatively-new clients who had given birth to a beautiful baby boy asked me what she could do to get her tight core back, because she was burdened by time constraints with the baby, was recovering from giving birth, and didn\'t have time to get back to training. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I asked if she was feeling her back when using the baby Bjorn carrier. She said she did. I told her to remember how I taught her how to feel the abs contract as she exhaled when doing her exercises. She remembered, but said it was difficult getting in touch with them now because the abdominal wall was stretched and weakened. I told her to focus on the support that she is naturally getting from her abdominals, and not on the tightness in her back, which will make her brain forget about her abs for support. She also had to make sure that she was doing the necessary stretches for her back so that the tightness wouldn\'t take over the feeling she should have in her abdominals.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Miracle of miracles, it worked! In no time, she got back in touch with her abs and made them work the way that they were supposed to. She started feeling her core tighten up like the girdle that it\'s supposed to be.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-04-16 16:04:24','2012-04-16 16:14:34',4,'16fit2date.jpg','image/jpeg',993032,'2012-04-16 16:04:19',0,'2012-04-16 16:14:34',1,'nofakes','nofakes'),(277,'Gee, Your Feet Smell Terrific','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your StyleGirlfriend is really into guys sporting the sockless look. Breezy, casual, elegant, summery&mdash;all that and a bag of potato chips.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sometimes, however, it can reek of one that&rsquo;s been left to rot since 2004 when a loafer gets kicked off, or dangled from a big toe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What is that stench? Our eyes are watering. Cue tripped gag reflex.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So blessings and hugs to our friends at ValetMag.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not only do they supply links on where to buy no-show socks (for dudes who are mad sweaters), they have a serious list of easy, odor-preventing tips for those who want their tootsies to smell like a meadow and not a sewer.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Intent on the former?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <a href=\"http://www.valetmag.com/style/how-tos/2011/summer-survival-skills-going-sockless-062411.php\" target=\"_blank\">We love you for clicking here.</a></span><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. bond. gold bond.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-04-16 16:43:49','2012-04-16 16:51:36',3,'16stylegf.jpg','image/jpeg',82998,'2012-04-16 16:45:26',0,'2012-04-16 16:51:36',1,'sockless','sockless'),(278,'First Sip of Summer','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We are (responsibly) toasting to what feels like the start of summer&mdash;and yes, we&rsquo;re over 21.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You&rsquo;d better be, too, if you&rsquo;re going to take a crack at the new, bubbly drink we\'ve just discovered. Think minty, lemony, refreshing, cocktail-meets-dessert.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What we love best of all is that it&rsquo;s so stupidly easy to throw together&mdash;but by no means should that license you to get carried away</span><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">There\'s no stirring/shaking debate, no need to blow dust off your blender, no special-shaped ice cubes to craft.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Thanks go out to brilliant Fresh365.com for getting our summertime off on the right, bare foot.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Champagne Cocktails with Mint &amp; Lemon Sorbet</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><em>makes 1 cocktail</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2 teaspoon fresh mint leaves, muddled or finely chopped</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> 2 large scoops lemon sorbet</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> 1/3 cup vodka</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> 3/4 cup champagne or sparkling wine</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In a tall glass, place a pinch of mint. Add one scoop lemon sorbet, another pinch mint and the other scoop sorbet. Pour in vodka, then top with champagne and the rest of the mint. Garnish with a mint sprig.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she is turning 21 again shortly.</strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-04-17 13:04:23',