size: medium;\">Some friends of mine don\'t date. They boyfriend-shop.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We dish post-The Event, \'cause we\'re girls. </span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">\"Soooo...talk: How was the date? You have fun?\" I ask.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I don\'t think they hear me.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They zip through, or skip, what actually happened ON the date, and get right to the end:</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Will he ask me out again, you think?&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He said X, Y, and then Z! </span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That\'s good, right?&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But he hasn\'t TEXTED!!!!</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It\'s puzzling.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What happened to the date being about, uhm, the date?&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why the forecasting, the worrying, then the label-slapping, and the direction-navigating?</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A date is an outing&mdash;a fun outing, presumably.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A date is not, in my humble, a first in a deliberate get-to-the-next-stepping-stone process&mdash;with the attitude of who cares who\'s taking you there: At least you\'re no longer alone.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A date is what it is. You\'re getting to know someone. Maybe a smidgeon, maybe deeply. </span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Obviduh: you\'d better be enjoying yourself doing it (or you\'re cutting out) each and every isolated time. </span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Maybe the dots will connect one day, maybe they won\'t.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And if they do, before you look around, boom: you\'ve grown an extra toothbrush in your bathroom&mdash;it just doesn\'t freak you out.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: x-small;\"><br /></span></div>\r\n<div><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she says, \"where is this going?\" to the bus driver.</strong></div>','talesfromthedate','2012-04-20 18:54:51','2012-04-20 23:12:22',5,'16toothbrushes.jpg','image/jpeg',25044,'2012-04-20 18:54:50',0,'2012-04-20 23:12:22',1,'date','date'),(282,'It\'s Easy Being Green','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It\'s Earth Week, beautiful people.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sure, you could do something responsible, like keep away from evil bottled water (bring your own refillable receptacles!) and bicycle all around town to reduce that carbon stiletto-print of yours. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Or you could show your solidarity with Mother Earth by wearing green.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not enough of the color in your wardrobe yet?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No frowning:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">FashionIndie\'s got a myriad of beautiful pickings in the gorgeous shade that will have you looking eco-chic year-round.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> <a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/green-fashion/\" target=\"_blank\">Chain Yourself to All of These.</a></span><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she\'ll happily shop to save the planet.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-04-23 13:58:20','2012-04-23 14:00:05',2,'23fashion.jpg','image/jpeg',16900,'2012-04-23 13:58:20',0,'2012-04-23 14:00:05',1,'ecochic','ecochic'),(283,'Time to Command The Room','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It suddenly occurs to your loving Style Girlfriend that she may be beating her he