',0,'2012-05-09 13:50:16',1,'9workout','9workout'),(300,'How to Gift For Girls','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A friend of mine is desperately trying to come up with what to buy his girlfriend for her birthday.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In an effort to guide him toward how to pick the proper gift for his woman, I counseled him with the following anecdote:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A couple of years ago on my own birthday, my then-boyfriend gave me a big, beautifully gift-wrapped box, complete with a bow.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Man,&rdquo; I remember thinking. &ldquo;This is an awfully large box for a bracelet.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My boyfriend was leaning over me. &ldquo;Open it! Open it!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I carefully pulled off the bow, and neatly tore the paper at the taping seams. It was some wrapping job. I was getting more and more curious.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Slowly but surely, the paper came away to reveal a cardboard box.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It appeared I was holding an electric contact lens cleaner.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">My boyfriend beamed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;No,&rdquo; my mind raced. &ldquo;He&rsquo;s so kidding. There must be earrings, or an Hermes scarf here. He&rsquo;s a joker. He&rsquo;s put it in this box to throw me.&rdquo; The box weighed several pounds. Perhaps he put popcorn kernels or bullets in as part of the gag.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I opened the box.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No bracelet. No earrings. No scarf. No bullets.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He truly did buy me (deep, deep sigh) an electric contact lens cleaner for my birthday.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Isn&rsquo;t it awesome?!&rdquo; he demanded. &ldquo;Like, best idea ever, hunh?!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He looked at me, eagerly expecting praise, and, quite frankly, like he couldn&rsquo;t wait for me to thank him properly after birthday dinner.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&ldquo;Wow,&rdquo; was all I could muster. &ldquo;That\'s something&hellip;uhm, Sweetie.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This is all to say, ConnectingSexes gentlemen, that presents women can actually use are generally the ones you should not buy&mdash;unless your ladies mention that they want them.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">See something at a store, and think it is stupid, frivolous, and/or nothing you personally would ever want or need?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Charge it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Get it gorgeously wrapped with a big, fluffy bow.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And ready yourself to be properly thanked after dinner.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. oooh. shiny.</strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2012-05-10 17:01:20','2012-05-11 12:16:24',5,'7tales.jpg','image/jpeg',97545,'2012-05-10 17:01:19',0,'2012-05-11 12:16:24',1,'gifts','gifts'),(301,'Peanut Butter: Love it Up','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We at ConnectingSexes have several food crushes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In our top-three is peanut butter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Creamy, or crunchy; organic, or chock-full of pesticides&mdash;we don&rsquo;t care. And any way it&rsquo;s served, we&rsquo;ll inhale it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">To that point, we also confess that we are terribly lazy, but you know this about us <a href=\"grilledcheese\r\n/\" target=\"_blank\">already.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So when we found a Mexican riff on our beloved Elvis-style sandwich (fried bacon, peanut butter and banana), we were intrigued. So simple, so fast!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We were also ashamed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">How come WE didn&rsquo;t think of a PB quesadilla first? We&rsquo;re only killing about a jar a week! Had we already run out of ideas?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Nevertheless, our new BFFs at FineCooking.com deserve credit, praise, and a mountain of thanks.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Theirs is bacon-free, so just fry some and proceed if you&rsquo;re having a coronary thinking it&rsquo;s a sacrilege to eat this without the swine. And definitely douse with maple syrup.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Live it up, Amigos. Recipe\'s right here:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Peanut Butter and Banana Quesadillas</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1/3 cup natural peanut butter (preferably chunky)&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> 4 5-inch corn or flour tortillas&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> 1 large ripe banana, halved crosswise, then sliced lengthwise into thirds&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Kosher salt&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> 2 tsp. grapeseed or canola oil&nbsp;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"> Maple syrup or honey, for serving&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div><hr align=\"left\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"0\" width=\"100%\" /></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Heat a small (8- to 9-inch) skillet over medium-high heat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Meanwhile, spread the peanut butter evenly the tortillas. Arrange the banana slices over half of the tortillas, sprinkle with a pinch of salt, and top with the remaining tortillas, peanut butter side down. Press gently to help them stick together, and then brush both sides lightly with oil.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">When the skillet is hot, add one of the quesadillas and cook, flipping once, until browned in spots on both sides, about 2 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board and repeat with the remaining quesadilla.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Cut each quesadilla into halves or quarters. Serve with a drizzle of pure maple syrup or honey.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. it\'s a bad romance.</strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-05-11 13:16:01','2012-05-11 13:25:01',8,'7lifestyle.jpg','image/jpeg',25048,'2012-05-11 13:16:01',0,'2012-05-11 13:25:01',1,'peanutbutter','peanutbutter'),(302,'Nail a Better Manicure','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">ConnectingSexes is mad for manicures.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But we never, ever get plain-Jane hands. Pale pink or apple red? Yawn.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We need all 10 fingers tricked out some kind of special&mdash;zebra, glitter, rainbows, rhinestones, you name it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Understanding us, as always, is FashionIndie.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They&rsquo;ve assembled a slideshow of dreamy, blingy nails (and one kickin&rsquo; pedi) that we&rsquo;re taking with us to the salon. You bet we&rsquo;re copycats.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/extreme-beauty-bling-your-nails/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here when you&rsquo;re ready to say au revoir to your ho-hum French manicure.</a></span><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. right now, she\'s sporting a minty glitter ombre manicure.</strong></p>','fashio