: medium;\">If you were trying to sweet-talk your way into a free upgrade to business class, would the suit, or the drawstring sweats and T-shirt ensemble, be more persuasive?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Chances are that we are not going to motivate you to don your finery for your flight, but Jonathan&rsquo;s post may.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.evolutionofstyle.com/index.php/site/blog_details/463/\" target=\"_blank\"> At least, that&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;re hoping.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she only wants you to have an open mind.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-05-21 17:15:19','2012-05-21 17:27:26',3,'21stylegf.jpg','image/jpeg',34851,'2012-05-21 17:15:17',0,'2012-05-21 17:27:26',1,'flightduds','flightduds'),(310,'Beach-Ready in 15 Minutes','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Is Memorial Day Weekend really almost here?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Are we really almost ready to shed our clothes, and parade publically in our swimsuits?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Uhm&mdash;sort of?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Helping us out in the short few days until the holiday are our good friends at AskMen.com.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They&rsquo;ve truncated our workout down to 15 tight little minutes. Think weight selection and training splits. Then think of your quivering arms and legs, and how stellar you&rsquo;ll look come Friday.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">If you&rsquo;ve never seen the inside of a gym, don&rsquo;t try this. Yet.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">However, for you GI Joes who need to melt off the last of the winter fluff, <a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/bodybuilding/15-minute-workout.html/\" target=\"_blank\">suit up.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she attempts to stay beach-ready year-round.</strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-05-23 20:49:19','2012-05-23 20:53:21',4,'21fit.jpg','image/jpeg',15195,'2012-05-23 20:50:21',0,'2012-05-23 20:53:21',1,'15mins','15mins'),(311,'#7 Workout Song: We Are Young With Janelle Monae ','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Song: Fun.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Need a song that&rsquo;s the perfect musical wallpaper for your interval training&mdash;upbeats and downbeats, yet consistently inspiring?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This indie pop ballad and anthem for our generation is it, Gymbuff. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It will propel those feet of yours to eat up the ground, then chill you out just enough to catch your breath before you do it all over again.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /> <iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Sv6dMFF_yts\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she likes fun.</strong></p>','music','2012-05-24 16:50:45','2012-05-24 16:51:54',6,'21music.jpg','image/jpeg',123175,'2012-05-24 16:50:45',0,'2012-05-24 16:51:54',1,'7workout','7workout'),(312,'Read The Wall','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A friend of mine just dumped her small-b boyfriend.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">After months of dating (i.e.: hanging out several nights a week), and feeling she was running in place romantically&mdash;or more to the point, not wanting to acknowledge that awful truth aloud to him&mdash;she decided, at last, to quiz him on THEIR state of the union.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Not liking his answers, she decided it was time to pull up stakes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Her heart is broken, but she will be okay, especially after anything on the rocks, and a few good cries.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I say, Kudos, my sister.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Why waste time and feel aggravated (at worst), or run around with low-level annoyance (at best)? Get what you want and need, either from whom you are with, or someone else.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I like to put the same spin on garden-variety casual dates. In a hot minute. That Grey Zone is quicksand. Do not hog my nights and waste my time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Case in point:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I have been out a bunch with a very interesting dude. Smart. Cultured. Tall. Multilingual. Handsome. Gainfully employed. He is a resume with feet.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We will talk for hours. Like distant relatives. No flirting&mdash;until he does something date-like, such as grab my thigh, my shoulder, my arm, or offer a compliment with a sexy smile. So I think, NOW, now we&rsquo;re growing LEGS here.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Then it goes back to feeling like family.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Initially, I thought his restraint meant respect, which I very much appreciated.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Then I thought I was perhaps off-putting, as NOTHING happened at the end of the night.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But he kept asking me out. Same routine with every date.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Let&rsquo;s face it: Many guys are not looking to accumulate new lady friends at this stage in life.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Deductive logic quickly swooped in.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Dude is a wuss.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I don\'t want a wuss.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I love my time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I want to give my time to a dude with a big pair.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It will suck to have The Awkward Conversation, but why waste his time, too?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Let him find a girl who may enjoy playing Not Kissing Cousins.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. at least there were no fist bumps.</strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2012-05-29 22:57:36','2012-05-29 23:05:27',5,'29tales.jpg','image/jpeg',338336,'2012-05-29 23:05:12',0,'2012-05-29 23:05:27',1,'wall','wall'),(313,'Leave On a Jet Plane','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We have a real wanderlust here at ConnectingSexes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sure, home is where the heart is, but there&rsquo;s a whole world out there, and we love exploring it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Especially when it&rsquo;s so stupid-easy, and we&rsquo;re getting deals left and right.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Travel&rsquo;s a breeze, Adventurers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And because everyone can track your journey when you hit the road, who needs to officially stay in touch with, like, uhm, emails?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Snapshot:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Between checking in to our new locations (Foursquare), finding a cheap flight (Expedia), nabbing values on where to crash (Hotels) after sussing them out (TripAdvisor), and now getting the skinny on exactly when and where our plane&rsquo;s taking off (GateGuru), travel&rsquo;s morphed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">How did anyone ever do this before? Shudder.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s crazy to see how skipping around the globe has evolved (literally), and to chec