oof. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The funkalicious beats and very sexy lyrics don&rsquo;t hurt a bit, either.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /> <iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/d0vXxH1IEmQ\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\"></iframe><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. aggravation ain\'t satisfactioning her, either.</strong></p>','music','2012-06-05 15:17:09','2012-06-05 15:17:24',6,'4music.jpg','image/jpeg',51931,'2012-06-05 15:17:08',0,'2012-06-05 15:17:24',1,'5workout','5workout'),(325,'Safe and Sound','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We would truly be lost, as we bike, run, and walk the streets, if we were not plugged in to our beats. We adore our tunes. And we love them more when they are loud. Louder. Loudest.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Although sometimes drowning out ambient noise is a good thing (such as on airplanes that carry anyone younger than, say, 10-years old), it&rsquo;s generally ill-advised when navigating the city.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We admit that we have on too many occasions had a close call with traffic because our jams are cranked so high we&rsquo;re oblivious to what&rsquo;s going on around us.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So how happy are we (and our parents, best friends, and sig others) to have found earHerosport? Hugely.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s a very cool set of tiny headphones, developed by an audiologist. It permits the outside world to enter our ears, along with our music, so we won&rsquo;t get mowed down as we bop along. Presumably.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Ready to stop taking your life into your hands when you rock out on the road, cranked up to 11?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.earhero.com/earherosport-0\" target=\"_blank\"> Cheggit, for $149.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. what?</strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-06-06 16:01:10','2012-06-06 19:09:25',8,'4lifestyle.jpg','image/jpeg',76686,'2012-06-06 16:01:09',0,'2012-06-06 19:09:25',1,'earbud','earbud'),(326,'Macarons Pour Moi: Dana Loia','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><em>How much does ConnectingSexes love gorgeous baking queen, Dana Loia? This awesome gal picked herself up and moved to New York City 12 years ago, then transformed her private baking habit into a full-time gig. And check her out: She won&rsquo;t feed you a brownie, or a cookie. Our newest Local Celebrity is peddling her own brand of unique, fancy-pants macarons from her venture, Dana\'s Bakery.</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>ConnectingSexes</strong>: Where are you from?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Dana Loia</strong>: Originally from New Jersey, but I have been in NYC for 12 years now.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">:&nbsp;How old are you?</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">DL</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: 30 years awesome.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">:&nbsp;Are you a baker in your private time?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: I used to be. Now I bake full time!</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: Describe the macarons-baking experience: You bake \'em yourself, or is there a team of elves in the kitchen?&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: &hellip;. Who told you about the elves&hellip;&hellip; ?</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: Why macarons, and not, say, ho-hos? Or madeleines?</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">DL</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: Macarons are very temperamental and not everyone can make a macaron. I love a good challenge!</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: Do you hope macarons will unseat the cupcake as the new it-dessert?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: I feel that already happening. There are macaron shops popping up all over Manhattan. However, they all serve standard, French-flavored macarons. I wanted to do something a little different; so I created a line of American-inspired flavors. USA!</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: medium;\">CS</strong><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">: Your favorite flavor is/because?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: Fruity Pebbles. Cereal + macarons. Does it get any better than that?!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>CS</strong>: Tell us about getting your macarons into NYC stores, and opening your first shop. You GO, girl!!!</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: We are currently online only; however we have a few pick-up locations. Check them out at <a href=\"http://www.danasbakery.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.danasbakery.com</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>CS</strong>: What&rsquo;s your favorite dessert?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: Anything marshmallows. And twizzlers. Oh, I love twizzlers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>CS</strong>: What would your last supper be?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: Thanksgiving dinner.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>CS</strong>: Tell us about your favorite cocktail.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>DL</strong>: Grey Goose dirt