sing me. I don&rsquo;t impress.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">However, for all the closeness, the warmth, and the fuzziness swaddling me more and more each day, I am also tightly bound in a big old chastity belt. But don\'t think for a moment it\'s an enjoyable accessory.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He leaves to go home after we make out on my couch, and I want to open the freezer door to take a seat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yep. No nookie. For now. S&rsquo;what it is, pal.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So, darling ConnectingSexers, why not swing from the chandelier?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">He&rsquo;s got it going on. I&rsquo;ve got it going on. We&rsquo;ve got it going on&mdash;so far, anyway.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And that&rsquo;s why.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Too often, when I have (sometimes very seriously) liked a boy and thought I was on the threshold of My Next Meaningful Relationship, we&rsquo;ve leapt into bed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Cue the retractable swing. Clear the kitchen countertop. Dim the lights.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Attachment on both parts would ensue before we ever really got to know each other deeply, or at all.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Then, once the Roman candles stopped firing, the marching band retired, and we started leaving the bedroom/kitchen/laundry room to rejoin the world, we (okay, I) realized we weren&rsquo;t such a hot mental match. Awkward pauses became painful silences, and damn, it was agony.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But the premature attachment because we dropped trou too soon made it harder to let go, and things would limp along miserably until the terrible breakup.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Reality check 