c on his left deltoid. It was not even a ping-pong ball&rsquo;s diameter. And it was in pen-ink blue, though he assured me it was professionally done.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Those tattoos never really did it for me. Not to judge, but to judge, there was almost a metaphor-like quality to them. The size and scale were wimpy, and seemed to have a &ldquo;don&rsquo;t look&rdquo; air about them because they were just a hair larger than microscopic. Therefore, to me, both were ironically non-committal.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">As with most of life&rsquo;s choices, why barely go for it? Especially when you&rsquo;re talking about permanently wearing your decision? I don\'t think a lacrosse-playing Yoda covering the surface of that guy&rsquo;s thigh would have been aesthetic magnificence, but at least it would have been apparent it meant something to him, enough that he was going to go all in for it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Respect.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And that\'s hot.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she commits to staying as pristine as the day she was born.</strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2012-06-27 18:43:27','2012-07-17 22:11:18',5,'25tales.jpg','image/jpeg',42808,'2012-06-27 18:43:26',0,'2012-07-17 22:11:18',1,'words','words'),(347,'The No-Fly Zone','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">At last, you&rsquo;ve followed our advice and <a href=\"tiebar/\" target=\"_blank\">bought a tie bar.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">You are ready to tame the beast when there&rsquo;s a gust of wind&mdash;not to mention, you&rsquo;re more elegant than the rest of the tie-wearing crowd.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Now there&rsquo;s a new dilemma in town: placement. The hell does the damn thing GO?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Never fear, handsome.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Style Girlfriend and our trusty friend Jonathan over at awesome blog Evolution of Style are here with advice on just the perfect positioning of your new little friend.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.evolutionofstyle.com/index.php/site/blog_details/468/\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for how to find it.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. more dapper with every occasion. go you.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-07-15 13:16:14','2012-07-15 13:17:21',3,'16style.jpeg','image/jpeg',89540,'2012-07-15 13:16:13',0,'2012-07-15 13:17:21',1,'nofly','nofly'),(348,'Lets Get Physical','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">With it being summertime, we find ourselves concerned with how we fit our bathing suits. So if you\'ve noticed, we\'ve also encouraged you to get yourself to the gym. Often. And with enthusiasm.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Being so alluring means your itsy-bittsies are bound to come off. Who wouldn&rsquo;t want you?&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But of course, it&rsquo;s more than just looking the part.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No one should ever accuse you of secretly being a 90-pound weakling who deserves sand kicked in your face because you can&rsquo;t hold your own in the bedroom, though you look like you could last for hours.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Pant, pant. Wheeze. Ow. Limp.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">With the excellent two-pronged benefit of sculpting your bod, and giving you stamina and strength, is a killer sexercise program courtesy of our buds at Askmen.com.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yeah, the target may be for dudes, but girls, you will rock your bikinis, then blow his mind with how your perfect legs just don&rsquo;t quit.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.askmen.com/sports/bodybuilding/sexercise.html/\" target=\"_blank\">So go on</a>. Sprint to the gym, then get busy with some hip lifts.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she is off to work out.</strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-07-15 14:07:05','2012-07-15 14:08:49',4,'17fit.jpeg','image/jpeg',78653,'2012-07-15 14:07:04',0,'2012-07-15 14:08:49',1,'sexercise','sexercise'),(349,'Ho Un Ragazzo','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I am back, kids, back to reality (aka New York, the center of the world) after two weeks in Italy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your devoted editor took a tiny bag, and a purse, and journeyed multiple towns all by her little self.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Si.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It was molto spectaculara. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">I have the peace of mind, crocodile smile, jet lag, and 220 photos to prove it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Before my solo adventure, several well-intentioned married, shacked-up, and single friends (guys and girls alike) were egging me on for a raucously raunchy good time once I crossed the pond.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The hot Italian men! The Vespa rides! Pack condoms&mdash;line that bag! Was my return-date flexible? You never know! [Dot, dot, dot.] And did they mention the men?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No doubt a tremendous part (or all) of their wishes was for their own vicarious living.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">That trip activity wasn&rsquo;t really about ME, you know&mdash;clearly evidenced by their ignoring that I have a new boyfriend, and cheering for me to play hide the salami. A lot. And then again.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Too bad for them, I returned without a single, salacious, spicy sex story, or even a mild and boring one.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sure, eye candy abounded. And said eye candy was flirtatious, pointed, and appreciative of female beauty. American men, do yourselves (and American women) a favor: Trail an Italian man for a few days, and take notes on how to flatter and pursue a girl. You&rsquo;ll be busy six hundred ways from Sunday. There were elderly gentlemen stooped over walkers who had more game and swagger than some of the &ldquo;players&rdquo; (ha, ha, ha) I&rsquo;ve seen here.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Truth be told, I was unaffected by the overtures. I did not need, or have interest in, a string of Vespa (or any other kind of) rides.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It was cool&mdash;and enough&mdash;to share with my US-based babe the details of my days and nights via email, text, and a couple of long (and what will prove expensive, but who cares?) phone calls. It made me happy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Hardly what some select friends wished in their bon-voyages before I set out, but I think ultimately, and deep, deep, down, are now glad to hear.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she wonders where she will go next.</strong></p>','talesfromthedate','2012-07-16 18:33:57','2012-07-16 18:58:01',5,'16tales.jpeg','image/jpeg',129620,'2012-07-16 18:35:17',0,'2012-07-16 18:58:01',1,'italia','italia'),(350,'No Buckling Up','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Transform a ho-hum accessory using innovative engineering genius plus beauty, and we at ConnectingSexes sit up a little straighter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Take the belt, for instance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It isn&rsquo;t something to jump up and down about. It&rsquo;s functional. Period.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Some designers try to defy this fact by tricking it way, way out.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They add bling, grommets, and a buckle that could double as a dessert plate (\'cause it looks VINtage), and the item itself is made from an exotic skin&mdash;hippo! ostrich! panda!&mdash;but whatever. We&rsquo;re passed out and drooling. We&rsquo;ve seen it all before.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Or so we thought.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Like, how about a belt with no buckle at all, of plain, well-oiled cow leather?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Stunning, cool, simple. We love not fussy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/m-i-a-found-buckle-less-belt/\" target=\"_blank\">Give a kiss to FashionIndie for culling the find</a>, created by Rowena Sartin.</span><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. no fuss, no muss.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-07-16 22:36:05','2012-07-16 22:36:59',2,'16fashion.jpeg','image/jpeg',119155,'2012-07-16 22:36:05',0,'2012-07-16 22:36:59',1,'belt','belt'),(351,'#1 Workout Song: Calvin Harris','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Song: Feel So Close</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It gives us warm fuzzies. It gives us a one-minute-plus warm-up. Then after the wind-up, we are off to the races&nbsp;with a tune that puts us over the moon with thumping beats and euphoric sirens.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Yes, our No. 1 workout song is none other than Scotsman Calvin Harris&rsquo;s Feel So Close.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">No lyric is too insipid or repeated, and we could not care less.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The melody is what we&rsquo;re after to charge us up for the last of our 10-set playlist to drive us (and you, Hotness) to physical near-perfection.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /> <iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/dGghkjpNCQ8\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. some days, she could use a forcefield.</strong></p>','music','2012-07-17 13:51:40','2012-07-17 13:53:16',6,'16music.jpeg','image/jpeg',45114,'2012-07-17 13:51:40',0,'2012-07-17 13:53:16',1,'workout1','workout1'),(352,'Big Kids Love Floats','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Don&rsquo;t you hate coming across things so brilliant, yet so easy&mdash;so obvious!&mdash;you can&rsquo;t believe you weren&rsquo;t the first to come up with them? </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Totally embarrassing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">This week at least, our discovery happens to take the edge off our personal disappointment.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">ConnectingSexes&rsquo; stunning example of &ldquo;I Would Have, I Swear&rdquo; is the very over-21 root beer float&mdash;which offers slurpers a nice hit of vodka under a thick cap of whipped cream and maraschino cherry.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Our cutting-edge mixologist friends at CreativeCulinary.com deserve the credit for beating us to the finish line with the grown-up bevy that masquerades as a kiddie drink.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Cheers to them&mdash;but kudos to us for tossing on a scoop of vanilla ice cream to gild the lily.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Oh, snap.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Ingredients</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2 oz. vodka</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">5 oz. root beer</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1 scoop of vanilla ice cream [ed: we\'ve thrown that in there to make it ours.]</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Whipping cream for garnish</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Maraschino cherry</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><strong>Put it Together</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">1. Fill glass with ice</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">2. Pour vodka over ice and then fill with root beer</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">3. Scoop out vanilla ice cream and lay on top of root beer/ice</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">4. Garnish top with whipping cream and cherry</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. mmmmmm. ROOT beer.</strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-07-19 20:49:13','2012-07-19 21:06:57',8,'16lifestyle.jpeg','image/jpeg',38144,'2012-07-19 20:49:12',0,'2012-07-19 21:06:57',1,'float','float'),(353,'Rescue Your Tresses','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We are horrified at what the summer has done to our otherwise silky, shimmering hair.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The ends are fried. No amount of conditioner is helping tame them. We&rsquo;re talking straw, people.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s thanks to all the nasty split ends we&rsquo;ve incurred from the sauna we&rsquo;ve been walking around in. Gross.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But no need to stress, and run to the salon every time we see something that shouldn&rsquo;t be on our heads, but in a barn.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Lovely FashionIndie schools us on how to identify, and snip&mdash;using the best tools&mdash;our way to shampoo-model perfection.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/how-to-trim-split-ends-without-visiting-the-salon/\" target=\"_blank\">Summon your inner Rapunzel here.</a></span><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she\'s happy to try a DIY.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-07-23 22:12:49','2012-07-23 22:16:56',2,'23fashion.jpeg','image/jpeg',84967,'2012-07-23 22:12:48',0,'2012-07-23 22:16:56',1,'hairdiy','hairDIY'),(354,'Snack Like a Champ','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We&rsquo;ve loaded your playlist with the best workout jams.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We&rsquo;ve cobbled some ass-kicking (and sculpting) routines so you&rsquo;re the hottest of them all on the beach.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And now, in time for the Olympics, ConnectingSexes has unearthed a list of foods that will have you eating all healthy over the coming weeks&mdash;perhaps dropping some poundage while you&rsquo;re at it.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It is thanks to good ol&rsquo;Dr. Oz. He&rsquo;s tallied up some of his favorite diet foods for us. Ninety-nine of them. Hollah. That&rsquo;s a serious grocery cart of goodness.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Don&rsquo;t even bother asking us: it does include dessert.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.doctoroz.com/videos/dr-ozs-99-diet-foods/\" target=\"_blank\">Just remember you&rsquo;re not getting a gold medal for your approved-foods eating competition; so go easy on woofing your treats.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. popcorn. nuff said.</strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-07-24 14:39:31','2012-07-24 15:31:59',4,'23fit.jpeg','image/jpeg',30384,'2012-07-24 14:39:30',0,'2012-07-24 15:31:59',1,'champ','champ'),(355,'Kick It Casual','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We know, we know: it&rsquo;s tough to find a decent shoe that goes with your hang-out wear.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Sick of your Sperrys?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">What a coincidence. So is your Style Girlfriend.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">And we love that you know better than to wear those mandals. Again.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So we are super-stoked to show you some of the coolest kicks we\'ve seen around to complement your casual side.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Picture the love child of penny loafers and sneakers, and that&rsquo;s your new, laid-back-you footwear.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.ubiqlife.com/ProductDetail.aspx?ID=8316/\" target=\"_blank\">Make it reality for $75.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. casual, and elegant. quite the cocktail.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-07-25 20:38:28','2012-07-25 20:40:09',3,'23style.jpeg','image/jpeg',169223,'2012-07-25 20:38:28',0,'2012-07-25 20:40:09',1,'casual','casual'),(356,'Glasses That Do Tricks','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We are still in the heat of wedding season. Makes it easy to plan our weekends for the next couple months.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">In addition to our time, we also know where our dollars are going&mdash;often toward stuff that has us either yawning, or thinking, &ldquo;Seriously?&rdquo; when we look at the registries. It can pain us&mdash;not that we&rsquo;re judging.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So to depart from the traditional wish list, and the boring check, we at ConnectingSexes are stoked about gifting some awesome wine glasses from Sempli instead.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They swill the vino around all on their own &lsquo;cuz they are stemless; when you set them down, they perch on an angle. Their cool shape makes them perfect for cocktails, too, so the lovebirds aren&rsquo;t limited to red, white, or rose.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://sempli.bigcartel.com/product/cupa-vs-wine-glass/\" target=\"_blank\">Snatch &lsquo;em up here</a>, and let someone else buy those ho-hum bath towels.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. why the sudden need for cake stands upon marriage?</strong></p>','lifestyle','2012-08-06 18:13:11','2012-08-06 18:13:22',8,'6lifestyle.jpeg','image/jpeg',10945,'2012-08-06 18:13:10',0,'2012-08-06 18:13:22',1,'wineglasses','wineglasses'),(357,'Channel Your Inner Olympian','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The Olympics. Lawd help us. Could this not be on television every day, every year? We are addicted.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We at ConnectingSexes are so utterly inspired watching the games.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They get our butts off the couch, desk chairs, wherever we\'re planted. They up our ante on whatever machine we&rsquo;re (now) destroying at the gym, our eyeballs glued to the TV set. Inspiration abounds.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So how happy are we to find further incentive to break the fitness equipment with our focus and rigor than from our awesome pals over at HuffPo?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They&rsquo;ve compiled an article and slide show that has us lacing up our sneakers five minutes ago.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/03/calories-olympic-athlete_n_1735846.html?ref=topbar/\" target=\"_blank\">Race you!</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. gold in elliptical and pilates.</strong></p>','supertrainerrick','2012-08-06 18:50:54','2012-08-06 18:56:37',4,'6fit.jpg','image/jpeg',70421,'2012-08-06 18:50:53',0,'2012-08-06 18:56:37',1,'olympics','olympics'),(358,'Summer Sweaters, So to Speak','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Your Style Girlfriend knows you&rsquo;re rough guy, tough guy.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Like, in the dead of winter you show up, shivering, without a jacket, all like, &ldquo;Cold. It&rsquo;s cold?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">It&rsquo;s one of the many things we adore about adorable you.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We&rsquo;ve got extra love in our hearts for our smart(er) friends at Valetmag, who know that with the end of summer comes the start of that unmistakable fall breeze (a/k/a, &ldquo;chill in the air&rdquo;).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">They&rsquo;ve found for you some cotton sweaters from Gant, Jack Spade, and J. Crew that are nice and soft and not too thick, with a kind of rugged appeal. Like you, baby.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">We want you to have them, not only because we know you will wear them all year-round and be snug.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.valetmag.com/style/products/2012/enduring-classic-lightweight-summer-sweater-080612.php?style_top_lead/\" target=\"_blank\">But also because we want to borrow them.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she always returns what she borrows. really, she swears.</strong></p>','stylegirlfriend','2012-08-07 15:52:01','2012-08-07 15:57:51',3,'6stylegf.jpg','image/jpeg',44567,'2012-08-07 15:52:01',0,'2012-08-07 15:57:51',1,'lightsweater','lightsweater'),(359,'Be Consciously Cool ','<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">The words &ldquo;post-consumer polyester clothes and home goods&rdquo; may not exactly inspire mental images of fabulousness.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">But listen to us (and our wonderful friends at FashionIndie who made the discovery): In reality, we have a totally different story for you.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">A cutie-pie Portland couple sews scraps of old duds themselves (we smell the trendy word &ldquo;sustainable!&rdquo;) into fashion and d&eacute;cor. Think dresses, tea towels, leggings, and pillowcases, to name but a few of the items they&rsquo;re peddling.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Want yet another cool factor?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Some of their textiles GLOW IN THE DARK! Wowza. How\'d they do that?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">So you can be all enviro-chic, anti-sweatshop, and even phosphorescent, too.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://fashionindie.com/m-i-a-found-portlands-printed-post-consumer-polyester/\" target=\"_blank\">As if you needed any improvement.</a></span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /> <strong>e.b.k. lives, plays, and dates in new york. she wonders how good her butt would look if it glowed in the dark.</strong></p>','fashionindie','2012-08-07 16:48:56','2012-08-07 16:54:34',2,'6fashion.jpg','image/jpeg',46510,'2012-08-07 16:48:55',0,'2012-08-07 16:54:34',1,'envirocool','envirocool');
